{"product_id": "48190", "page": 5, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-08", "text": "A truly remarkable adventure and history game that takes place in a mystery environment of 15th and 16th century Italian penninsula. Beautifully designed graphics enriched with numerous (optional) descriptions of known and less known buildings, paintings, personas etc. A lot has already been said about Assassin's Creed, but with such truly unique screenplay, it will always be my pleasure to play it again, and again.", "hours": 2.5, "user_id": "76561198411113147", "username": "Petrushkica", "products": 7, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 5, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-01-08", "text": "A sequel to Assassin's Creed II, Ezio on his quest to restoring Roma is beautiful. Creating your own guild of assassins is great. Side missions are great except Leo's...those are a pain to execute 100% synch. Money system is a bit more balanced, a more reason to spend money. The Sequences got shorter though, so the story is a bit short, emphasizing more on activities than the story.(sidequests, collectibles, etc.) 10/10 Last game I got issues with controls, this is a bit better.", "hours": 30.7, "username": "\u239b\u239dGoldberg\u23a0\u239e", "products": 503, "early_access": false}
