{"product_id": "48190", "page": 9, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-12-09", "text": "Assassin's Creed Brotherhood is a great but short game (fully finished it in 14 hours). I can't play it now because every time i try to open it it says it can't find the Ubisoft Game Launcher. Don't waste your money on it. If you do, NEVER delete it or you won't be able to play it again because Ubisoft wants you to use Uplay.", "hours": 14.3, "user_id": "76561198165640595", "username": "Nope'd", "products": 11, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 9, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-08", "text": "Props :\n* Altair\n* Graphism\n* Coherent Ambiance but one city ( Rome )\n* Manage your assassins\n* Custom your armor\nCons\n* Story is less interessting than Assassin Creed 2\n* Ending ...\n* Repetitive quests\n* Flags and  feather again and again ...", "hours": 23.8, "username": "ULINA", "products": 281, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 9, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-07", "text": "AC2's initial release didn't include sequences 11 and 12, and it seems like the only reason sequence 13 was kept in was to segue from Ezio's investigation of the motives behind his family's deaths into this game, where Ezio finally brings the fight to the Borgia within Rome. The map difference is nice, being able to go from packed buildings in the commercial district to open grass plains and/or ruins, without ever needing to leave the city walls. Chain kills, a new indestructible armour, a DLC that's all about making up for missed screen time with Da Vinci, achievements that mean nothing, a memory sync meter for unlocking certain secret memories (honestly not worth the extra time to 100% a lot of memories). This game should be played immediately after finishing AC2, but still be aware that it plays significantly differently.", "hours": 57.3, "username": "<Kl0n[d1k]E>", "products": 510, "early_access": false}
