{"product_id": "48190", "page": 11, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-25", "text": "The best assassins creed to date. 100% Syncronization will take around 30-40 hours depending on how good you are. A new mechanic that was added is being able to have your own assassins. They help a lot when doing hard missions but sometimes make it too easy. Controls seem a lot smoother than its predecessors but I do recommend using a controller as I had a hard time adjusting to the mouse and keyboard controls. I used an Xbox one controller and it worked well. Overall the main plot is interesting and hypes you up for assassins creed revelations and 3.", "hours": 16.5, "user_id": "76561198051006138", "username": "Professor Sad", "products": 252, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 11, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-25", "text": "I've been a big fan of Assassin's Creed series since the second game came out. It's really the best series in my opinion.\nHowever, over these years with many new games of the series came out, I still find this Brotherhood is the best of the series (Well for now I still didn't try the new Origin for some reasons.) It's also the best in the Ezio story.", "hours": 7.8, "user_id": "76561198254081430", "username": "kevinyin991201", "products": 95, "early_access": false}
