{"product_id": "48190", "page": 26, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-19", "text": "Control's are hard to play with. But fun game! Loved the pirate one! Called, Assassin's Creed: Black Flag!\nBut in all 9/10 the 1 that is not making it 10/10 is the controls part!\nBut yes would recommend it to everyone to play with a controller unless you like inverted controls on keyboard!", "hours": 1.8, "user_id": "76561198169182290", "username": "Arkaruth", "products": 79, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 26, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-18", "text": "This game is pretty good   it took me 38 hours to beat the game this was including me doing everything in the game for most part upgrading all buildings and stuff.\nStory while not as interesting as AC2 I give it 7.5 out of 10\nArt 6 out of 10\nMusic 7 out of 10\nOverall I give this game a B it was well worth the time put into it and good value for the $6.79 I paid for it.\nI would wait until this is on sale 20 bucks is a little too much. I havent tried multiplayer yet will soon.", "hours": 39.4, "user_id": "76561198063269581", "username": "Kaname", "products": 401, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 26, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-07-18", "text": "okay wtf why do i keep buying ubisoft products? i love assassin's creed but their games are always buggy as all hell on PC. this game takes the cake for bugginess, i can't use my mouse *at all* to look around, mount horses, or fight people--it's just a bunch of bashing the buttons until they work.\nit's not even a good game, really. it's basically like if AC2 had 100 extra hours. AC2 was a really long game, man. longer than it needed to be. i loved it, but i was glad when it ended. i don't want to pick up another of the same old.\nand after playing Syndicate and Black Flag, you can't really return to something like this in terms of plot or script--it's basically a bunch of trite hollywood\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665where every side character is either kissing Ezio's\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665or cursing him comically.\nthe gameplay is boring as all heck as well like..... honestly? the one thing that kept me playing for 10 hours? the horse-riding. love that thing. every time i tapped V to call my horse and saw it tumbling through a crowded market at light speed like unbounded madness, my heart just skipped a beat.", "hours": 10.7, "username": "ribqueen", "products": 173, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 26, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-16", "text": "Honestly this is probably the best AC game to date other then the first one, i didnt really have any flaws with this game except the combat which could sometimes be glitchy, other then that amazing game. 10/10.", "hours": 50.5, "username": "snow", "products": 50, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 27, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-13", "text": "Assassin's Creed Brotherhood is better than ever. The main charater Ezio returns in an epic struggle against the powerful Templar Order. people who like the idea of being a building-climbing, sword-swinging assassin,hide-the-bodies stealth adventure. The best new feature in the series. Players can recruit citizens to fight for Ezio, amassing up to 12 trainees who can be summoned with the press of a button. Assassins gain experience over time, earning better weapons, armor and tactics. This crew can also be dispatched on assignments throughout Europe to do cool things off-screen.", "hours": 126.7, "user_id": "76561198387348183", "username": "REPOMAN420", "products": 7, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 27, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-13", "text": "Great video game, I'm very satisfied :)", "hours": 63.7, "username": "Adhita Dea Kharisma, S.E.", "products": 33, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 27, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-11", "text": "After returning to the game three months later, the problems seem to have largely disappeared and I haven't had trouble with the game so far. I'm still not sure what fixed it; whether it was uninstalling, remapping the keys, verifying files, or just leaving it alone for a while, it's up and running properly now. With that, I'm pleased to be able to change my review to \"Recommended\" :D\nOriginal review:\nI really wanted to be able to recommend this game, but I just can't. Bugs strewn everywhere: people walk into walls, people get stuck on flat surfaces, people walk right through me during cutscenes. Ezio is afraid of stairs, lets go of ledges and immediately grapples the next one down, immediately re-sheathes weapons upon drawing them, keys are \"sticky\" (eg. can't stop sprinting), mouse sensitivity is whack. So far seen, the setting is unsatisfying and feels like a watered down version of ACII. I may give it another go in a few weeks, and will update this review if my experience improves.", "hours": 28.4, "username": "Aryore", "products": 71, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 27, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-11", "text": "Not much different from AC II. Just some additional outfits, weapons and things like that. The story is not so good, but has its moments. AC Brotherhood looks more like a big DLC from AC II, since the map is so much tinier. The biggest problem, was the gameplay, who decreased a lot by giving Ezio the \"killing spree\" ability, that when you kill someone, you just have to press one button to kill other, and another and another. This made the game insanely easy. But i loved how they gave Leonardo more space in the story to appear and make big and importante things to help the brotherhood. The game is good, but it's not even close to be as good as AC II or AC I.", "hours": 17.1, "username": "John Winchester", "products": 311, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 27, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-11", "text": "I intend to write a book about you one day -Niccolo Machiavelli\nIf you do make it\n-Ezio Auditore da Firenze\nSo Ubisoft present you Assassins Creed Brotherhood with a short storyline but amazing gameplay compare to any of AC series.", "hours": 29.4, "username": "\ud83c\udf41Yoo Bro\ud83c\udf41", "products": 57, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 27, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-11", "text": "Assassin's Creed Brotherhood is another direct continuation of the AC franchise and further continues the dual modern/historic storyline. The engine and gameplay elements have been even further improved, which is appreciated. The gameplay can be repetitive and frankly easy, but at it's core, it's good. The storyline, while not quite as impactful as ACII, is memorable in its own way, and the entertaining cast of characters helps with that.", "hours": 28.1, "username": "IronicRobot", "products": 164, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 27, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-09", "text": "very fun game with minor mechanic issues.\nyou'll sometimes find yourself trying to climb walls but instead ezio will run up the side as if there were no ledge and drop back down. when there's a low climbing spot he'll sometimes run up the wall over the rooftop ledge like there's an invisible wall above the roof. its also difficult to change direction on a rail to try and jump off. most of the time you have to come to a complete stop and turn ezio the direction you want him to leap for him to actually do it or else he'll keep running straight on the rail even though your camera is clearly facing the direction you want him to go. the a and d keys really had no effect on this problem. in ac2, this problem was non existent. other than that, this game is very fun.", "hours": 47.1, "username": "stink", "products": 157, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 27, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-08", "text": "The story was good in the end. But the controls made it an infuriating ride. Its taken 4 years to complete this game as I did keep losing interest due to the severe number of side missions in this game. But finally pushed myself to avoid them and focus on the actual story.\nCombat is even easier than previous games with the addition of crossbows and guns.", "hours": 33.1, "username": "General Kysieran", "products": 420, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 27, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-07", "text": "By far the shortest gameplay in the AC franchise.\nBut it being short doesn't mean you'll not enjoy it.\nWhat personally annoys me is how these games have an abrupt climax, which is told in a riddle. You'll have to go through an intensive search throughout blogs to have perhaps a basic understanding of what you've just seen.", "hours": 39.5, "username": "NanoNewton", "products": 66, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 27, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-07", "text": "I enjoy playing AC Brotherhood but it's buggy a.f. I wanted to recruit a citizen which was on the rooftop. I sent an assassin to kill one of the guards while I jumped to assassinate the guard that citizen held. It bugged out and Ezio flew to the river which is like 70-100 units away. One time I was just running over the rooftoop then suddendly I fell through it all an found my self swimming in the water below the city. in sequence 9, I couldn't trigger the animation to start a fight with Cesare (if someone has this problem just go down the tower and try to go back as much as you can... It triggers shortly after that). Overall, I really like the story and the gameplay but the bugs and the bards are so fricking annoying xD.", "hours": 30.4, "user_id": "76561198090964750", "username": "interpid2", "products": 38, "early_access": false}
