{"product_id": "48190", "page": 31, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-23", "text": "Let me make this short for you: it's AC2, but better looking (at least compared to the AC2 you'll find on steam) and in Rome. If not for hardware limitations and/or business/development considerations, it could have been all part of one game.\nPros: story | music | graphics (looks much better than I expected)| improved gameplay| horse riding inside the city walls\nBIG PRO: you CAN use your Xbox One controller, unlike in AC2.\nCons: Maybe a bit shorter than one would expect.\n8.9/10\nRecommended to AC fans and casual players, like me, who like a good open world game, with nice story and fitting music, to relax.", "hours": 30.8, "user_id": "76561198297180925", "username": "theonewhoknocks", "products": 20, "early_access": false}
