{"product_id": "48190", "page": 34, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-05-18", "text": "Hall of Fame.\nThe best of the Assassin's Creed games, it built upon the world and gameplay of its predecessors, developing one of the most fleshed out and interesting stories found in a game franchise, not even bested by its own successors. Easily one of the best protagonists in any game, the experience of being a part of his development from early life to hardened veteran is a unique and well-made one. Coupled with awesome multiplayer, which was later killed in the coming games, AC:B makes for the peak of a legendary franchise.", "hours": 50.5, "username": "Folle", "products": 499, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 34, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-05-15", "text": "The epilogue of this game is mindblowing.\nMutiple new and fun elements were added in this  one, sync challenges, liberation of sections, new weapons and command within apprentice assassins.\nThe main storyline was firmly executed, side missions had all sorts of style, the DLC missions were fabulous\nOverall, a great game\nP.S collectibles and perfect sync were both annoying and time-consuming, so I chose to ignore them :P", "hours": 35.9, "user_id": "76561198337503770", "username": "MiX7", "products": 146, "early_access": false}
