{"product_id": "48190", "page": 39, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-03-11", "text": "I had forgotten the AC franchise didn't get good until ACIII. The early Assassin's Creed games (and Chronicles) make me cuss at my computer more than any other game series. Your character never moves the way you want him to, the combat is wonky, block is the same button to run so there are times where your character will just stand there. Parts are fun sure, and I'm going to beat it but damn, it doesn't deserve the 89% it has on Steam. The controls ruin it. ACIII and ACIV are where it's at.", "hours": 27.8, "user_id": "76561198022039830", "username": "Monroe", "products": 515, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
