{"product_id": "48190", "page": 43, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-28", "text": "I love this! I like it !\nI cant stop playing Brotherhood before I finsih the full game\nIt is a really fun game and there have more fighting action//\nI also play assassin's creed I and I think brotherhood Is more more more better//\n=======================================================\ngood things:\nmemory use very little\nyou can swim( AS1 cant )\ntexture is very great\nand you can play without good computers\n=======================================================\nBad things:\nThe story is too short\nAlways show the mouse icon in game\nStop's items are too little\n=======================================================\nLast one:\nI wish Ezio May come again", "hours": 48.4, "username": "Crezy", "products": 49, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 43, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-25", "text": "Initially, you get the impression that this should have been the DLC for Assassins Creed 2, but then they decided to stretch it into a full game. However, that is quickly shaken off and Brotherhood is a solid entry in the Ezio series. Playing as Ezio is as fun as always, possibly more so as he's got more gadgets than Batman.\nTheres quite a heavy emphasis on management, with rebuilding rome or recruiting your own assassins. I like this sort of thing, but if it doesnt set your world on fire you can pretty much ignore it once the training wheels are let loose. The graphics are good, especially considering this was released nearly 7 years ago.\nRome can sometimes feel overwhelming, with there literally being tons of stuff to do - hundreds of side objectives are available. And this is where I feel it has overstretched itself, content for the sake of content. The plot is quite thin and tends to jump around, with no real sense of flow, just a series of disconnected objectives.\nI hold my hands up and admit that I found Assasins Creed skull-crushing difficult at times, with Altair dying more times than I could count. Ezio seems almost overpowered in this game, and sometimes battles can feel a little too easy when you perform a 15-count execution streak.\nOverall, Brotherhood is an enjoyable game with possibly too much stuff in it, but saying that, I suspect I will lose a few more hours running around Rome before I'm finished with it.", "hours": 38.9, "user_id": "76561198077914319", "username": "WantedEye", "products": 112, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 43, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-25", "text": "Best open world experience among AC series epic story, unique Rome experience, cool gadgets and good variations for combat", "hours": 50.7, "username": "Shabbro96", "products": 910, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 43, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-24", "text": "To start, this game is AMAZING!\nI just purchased it on steam after playing through AC2 for the first time in probably 5 years.  Now I've already played this game on console, but didn't have the Leonardo DLC.\nThis game is hands down a must have.  It expands on what AC2 does, story-wise and gameplay.  You have an expanded shop/ownership system, while in AC2 all you have is one city.\nPros:\nSingle city: Rome\nGreat storyline, both inside and outside the Animus\nMore weapons that past games.\nGreat animations and graphics for it's time\nCons:\nThere are a few glitches with AI that can affect the gameplay\nFinal present day timeline that will allow exploration.  Present storyline starts to head down the drain after this game.", "hours": 27.8, "username": "Venocide", "products": 301, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 44, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-24", "text": "Brotherhood is Carvan. Brother is Bassio.\nOh!  It's Assasin. \u300cAssassin\u2019s Creed Rogue\u300dis Right!\nRogue is Assasin's Coatclothe.\nEzio go to Edinbara in Itaria.\nOh! He is Mascot of Mafia.\nHe is Seed-horse of Italy.\nI was in ELsalem-Kingdom. I'm Assasin-Surif.\nWhere is Trueth?", "hours": 3.1, "username": "RyuzenTennoh", "products": 25, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 44, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-22", "text": "Pros:\n+Enormous\n+landmark-filled world to explore\n+Leonardo's machines are a fun change of pace\n+Uniquely fun multiplayer action\nCons:\n-Story's kind of flat compared to ACII\n-Visual glitches\n-Occasionally infuriating controls\nSome could say this was the last good AC game.\nDefinitely worth a buy for AC fans, or even parkour game like Prince of Persia fans.", "hours": 6.3, "username": "f\u044f0z\u0454\u0418^G", "products": 425, "early_access": false}
