{"product_id": "48190", "page": 45, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-01-10", "text": "So this crap is where the 100% sync \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665t started. Crammed with pointless collectibles and unskippable cutscenes, you're gonna waste a hell lot of time trying to \"get the most out of this game\". And seriously, the whole \"investments\" thing is just silly.\nThe only reason I played this thrash is because I played AC2, I loved it and I wanted to know Ezio's fate.", "hours": 15.1, "user_id": "76561198322262818", "username": "LarryPinhead", "products": 270, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 46, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-10", "text": "The great story of Ezio continues.\nHe is now a Master Assassin, and the game sure makes you feel like one.\nMany additions to AC II that enhance the gameplay, and this is, for me, the best gameplay in any Assassin's Creed.\nGameplay is better, but the story is ok, not even close to the story of AC II.\nSoundtrack is also, in my opinion, not so good as that of AC II.\nOverall, great game...", "hours": 48.1, "username": "ACCURD", "products": 105, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
