{"product_id": "48190", "page": 49, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-25", "text": "I was already in love with it's predecssor, Assassin's creed 2, only to find out that brotherhood is an awesome upgrade. Guess relocating to the italian capital is exactly what they needed to take the game to the next step. Anyway's this game is definetly in my top 3 for Assassin's creed games. I would recommend playing AC2 first to get the whole backstory otherwise you'll feel a bit lost.", "hours": 119.6, "username": "Ball_Fondlers", "products": 36, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 49, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-23", "text": "I love this game and its very adictive", "hours": 10.3, "user_id": "76561198267927707", "username": "Rudski", "products": 19, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 49, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-23", "text": "Now, I never played Assassin's creed 1, and my memories of the second are blurry at best, but while all the ones I've played since certainly has their own pros and cons, Brotherhood is my favourite. Revelations had (in my opinion) the best parcour curtesy of the hook, 3 has one of the best story climaxes I've ever seen in my game, 4 certainly is a great pirate game (but being in it for the stabbing in bathrobes, I find it a touch lacking) and Unity certainly is the one where the city feels like a living, breathing city. But Brotherhood is the only Assy-Creedy where I genuinly lost myself in the simple act of playing the game, from running around to stabbing to fighting to football team management. So I like itI guess the reviewer term would be it's the most immersive one.\ufeff", "hours": 36.1, "user_id": "76561198081374993", "username": "Catasros", "products": 260, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 50, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-22", "text": "Good Assassins Creed game if you like the type. Story continues well and ends suprisingly. Some small annoyances like some parts of the game bugging out if you don't have VSync on which is... confusing.\nAnd at the end of the game, be prepared to go for a coffee, walk or watch a movie since you can't skip the 36mins long credits.", "hours": 60.2, "user_id": "76561198267653815", "username": "Aziret", "products": 62, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 50, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-22", "text": "As good as ever and much better than the remaster (which is frankly just a lick of pain), shame no-one is on the multiplayer  anymore, as it was the best part of the game for me.", "hours": 23.7, "username": "kaney1008", "products": 61, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 50, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-22", "text": "Pros: Awesome Game, awesome game play, awesome story, having your own assassin recruits is cool.\nCons: It randomly freezes when your riding a horse, cut scean audio some times gets cut out but you can fix this by pressing esc, it glitches cut sceans not making them pop up  atall, to avoid this put it on v-sync the game doesn't seem to like high fps and make sure your resolution is at 60hz, if you only play the main story once you will only get around 14 hours out of this game, side quests are kinda boring just my opinion.\nConclusion: Its still awesome get it.", "hours": 14.1, "username": "Sund\ud83c\udd70y Roast", "products": 129, "early_access": false}
