{"product_id": "48190", "page": 52, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-02", "text": "This game is and has been my favorite Assassin's Creed game yet, I own all the games and so far this stands on top. Ezio is an amazing character and my favorite assassin of all time. 9.5/10 Play this!", "hours": 49.6, "username": "Sapling", "products": 347, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 52, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-01", "text": "I changed my view on Assassin's Creed: Brotherhood. The game itself actually make me remember Italian landmarks easily such as Castel Sant'Angelo, The Pantheon, Colosseum and many more! I can learn something about this game and try to relate it with my history class especially The Renaissance. Quite a keen game to educate about The Renaissance. However, do not believe 100% of it as it is edited version. Only some or certain parts of it.", "hours": 23.7, "username": "ReconSixth", "products": 100, "early_access": false}
