{"product_id": "48190", "page": 60, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-30", "text": "A good continuation of the Ezio's story. Roma is magnificent. Gameplay is fun and polished, but as any AC game it has many repetitive aspects, one of the reasons I decided to mostly focus on the story to not get bored. Multiplayer's hide and seek can be fun, though I hate players that hide within a crowd of NPCs that have identical character models. I always kill the wrong one :P Anyways, if you like the previous AC games you will this one too. Do not play this one if you didn't play AC2.", "hours": 23.1, "username": "Zeus_CM", "products": 432, "early_access": false}
