{"product_id": "48190", "page": 63, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-15", "text": "I liked everything about this game.\nThe world has improved so much since the first AC. There's side quests and I don't want to spoil too much but there's just a lot of amazing aspects to this game. The storyline is great, and the graphics aspect is really well done in my opinion. Beautiful scenery.\nThere is a fast travel system in this game, which is pretty good. I don't find myself using it much, however. I find it more fun to run or ride a horse across Rome.\nLots of different weapons to choose from in this game, and of course you get more of a variety as it goes on. Leonardo Da Vinci appears in this game, which is GREAT.\nThis game is hands down my favorite AC game so far. I'm trying to give a balanced review of this game but honestly the only thing I can complain about is the unskippable credits at the end. That's tolerable though \u00af\\_(\u30c4)_/\u00af not so much for AC Revelations", "hours": 82.9, "username": "heartofscylla", "products": 37, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 63, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-14", "text": "A solid AC game. I did find the story rather repetitive, not some of the same variety of the newer AC games.\nHowever, this game has excellent mechanics, and a very big city with enough to do, even for this older AC game.\nWorth a solid 40 hours of gameplay.\nWould rate 87/100", "hours": 37.1, "user_id": "76561198225039728", "username": "Spyral", "products": 35, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 63, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-13", "text": "I would recommend this installment even if you were able to FINALLY get through AC2.  This one is much better managed as far as the length of the storyline goes.\nRome is one of the greatest cities to be mapped out for a game and they did a spectacular job.  The plot up to this point has been great.  AC2 was too long in my opinion but AC Brotherhood is nicely balanced.  You also get some long awaited closure as far as the Borgias are concerned.\nAs with AC2, the ending seem grafted on, but not as bad this time.  So I am still enjoying the plot for both Desmond and Ezio.  At the end of the day, having Rome as your personal playground makes this a great game.", "hours": 61.2, "username": "BadHello", "products": 75, "early_access": false}
