{"product_id": "48190", "page": 65, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-14", "text": "^^ I rate this game . ^^\n^^ Story : 4/10 ^^\n^^ Presentation : 6/10 ^^\n^^ GamePlay : 7.6/10 ^^\n^^ Performance : 8/10 ^^", "hours": 62.2, "username": "Walker #12697", "products": 140, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 65, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-13", "text": "This is such a fun game. I've played through the main story, but still have more to do. I don't tend to think about reviewing games, but this is the game I've played the most, and enjoyed virtually every second of it. Some of the basic assassin's creed mechanics don't quite work, such as sneaking through open fields, but that really doesn't detract from gameplay. I love this game, and I'm just now realizing it's hard to write a good long review. Well, I suggest you play this game if you enjoy the franchise, and even if you don't, you'll probably enjoy it.", "hours": 74.1, "username": "Gryph", "products": 120, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 65, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-12", "text": "Gonna keep this simple with no spoilers. I have a $300 laptop I was able to play this on, no graphics card, decent cpu. And running it wasn't real smooth, 12-26 fps at 800X600 but I loved the game so much I finished it with it set so small with bad graphics. Which even with low and off graphics it still looked great. Wish I could actually make it look worse. Recomend 100%.", "hours": 26.7, "username": "TheBlueCrafter", "products": 47, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 65, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-09", "text": "One of the best AC sandbox ever!\nJust a one large city (Rome), own assassin guild, tons of sidequests and a lot of good stuff from all previous games.\nVery good thing is also that from \"present times\" you have just a few minutes.\nBut the top in this game are missions for Leonardo da Vinci. Try the tank, airglider, flamethrower ship... cool!\nAlso, missions with Lukrecia  Borgia are also pretty good!\n...\nNow... CONs. !SPOILER WARNING!\nYes. There is 1 major \"minus\". Ending. End of the main story. Its \"UFO-deus-ex-wtf-moment\".\nBut, all around, this game is really excellent!", "hours": 39.3, "user_id": "76561198008580123", "username": "PRAVEMI", "products": 240, "early_access": false}
