{"product_id": "48190", "page": 66, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-07-05", "text": "This game is heavily overrated by critics, I only praise it as a pack (continuity of AC II)...     6.0/10.0\n- Early Reinassance Rome is still great to visit\n- The ACII Ezio's storyline has an epic conclusion here\nCriticism:\n- Just one city (no matter how big) and a few localized areas versus the north of Italy feelsbadman\n- The story is significantly short, evidently, as a conclusion of ACII plot\n- Features on the game were copy-paste from ACII, no innovation at all", "hours": 15.6, "user_id": "76561198109858979", "username": "Kalimonde", "products": 145, "early_access": false}
