{"product_id": "48190", "page": 67, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-27", "text": "Out of all the ACs I enjoyed this one most!\nIt's been a while since I've played it though so I'll sum it up: nice graphics. great sounds, great story - I loved roaming around Rome! Great characters, a lot of exploring and a bunch of collectibles for the \"extra challenge\".\nThe only negative that you might see others mention: Uplay.... *sighs*\nBut get it and enjoy it! :) Overall very smooth!", "hours": 76.5, "username": "not_imposter_lynx", "products": 374, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 67, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-26", "text": "If you liked AC2, you'll love ACB. If you didn't like AC2, you'll love ACB.\nIt's similar to AC2, but now with optional objectives it makes it more challenging. I've found myself thinking how to get the perfect assassinations, restarting memory sequences, and failing optional objectives so often. But that's what's fun about it.\nI think my favorite is Ezio out of all the AC protaganists, not because of the trilogy, but because of his epicness.\nI recommend playing with a controller, but it's not required.", "hours": 32.9, "username": "FireIceBlade", "products": 90, "early_access": false}
