{"product_id": "48190", "page": 71, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-05-26", "text": "Assassin's Creed Brotherhood follows much of the principles of Assassin's Creed 2.\nThe game is enjoyable and has a captivating storyline that, similar to it's predecessor, does not contain arduous repetitve tasks.\nThe game does not change play style a great deal but includes several mechanics like the parachute, ability to ride horses through the city, and improves on the fighting engine/animations.\nI would recommend this game for at least a single playthrough.\nAlthough there is not much of a replay value for singleplayer, multiplayer is somewhat enjoyable and can fetch an extra couple of hours here and there.", "hours": 17.6, "username": "Psychowire", "products": 267, "early_access": false}
