{"product_id": "48190", "page": 72, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-05-15", "text": "... Eh. Only if you've already beaten ACII and are hungry for more.\nDon't get me wrong- there's nothing much wrong with it. It's solid, it's just more of the same. There are changes here and there that make it more polished, but at the end of the day, ACII had a solid and interesting, if not terribly inspired, story backing up its gameplay and exploration every step of the way, supporting its flaws. Brotherhood... kinda doesn't. It's fine, it's just less engaging than its predecessor, and while some of the new gameplay tools are quite fun, it's hard to justify buying a whole game for \"more of the last one\" without having a story of some sort worth carrying it.", "hours": 27.0, "username": "Toastasaurus Rex", "products": 84, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
