{"product_id": "48190", "page": 73, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-05-05", "text": "The continuation of the story line is great, but I'm disappointed that the gameplay is very similar to the previous two - fights can essentially be won by mashing your attack button and finding objectives is super straightforward.  However, the graphics and scenery are still wonderful, and the open-world exploration is thrilling.\nI would definitely recommend the game if you don't mind a lot more repetition, but I just can't get myself past that part to continue the story line.  In this rare case, I'm fine just looking up the plot on Wikipedia.", "hours": 36.7, "user_id": "76561198025073584", "username": "Barium", "products": 29, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 73, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-05-03", "text": "Much like II, one of the only games I've not stopped playing until I got 100%. Overall a good continuation of the series, with an ever so slightly worse story than the previous ACII, it more than makes up for it by having more improved gameplay and fluidity, especially in combat.\nIf you were into the story of ACII, about becoming a master assassin from a youthful noble, theres not much development here. If you were into the gameplay of ACII, much has been improved, from the addition of the crossbow (allowing for more stealthy approaches), cinematic executions from your bare hands to two handed swords, and everything inbetween, and being able to use your pistol in a combo with the tap of a button, its much less of a chore to fight than it was in the previous games.", "hours": 33.6, "username": "\u2660 Shas'O Bongosun Mont'yr", "products": 623, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
