{"product_id": "48190", "page": 76, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-04-04", "text": "Finally closing the Italian story of Ezio being set in a smaller environment.\nYou can only walk around (or run or whatever strikes your fancy) in one City (Rome, if you hadn't guessed) instead of multiple ones, which isn't a realy problem because of the amount of detail that has been put into the city.\nThe fact that you can train assassins and renovate certain parts (mostly stores) in the city was something else from having an upgradeable homebase but not a bad thing in my opinion.", "hours": 94.8, "username": "Seerk", "products": 263, "early_access": false}
