{"product_id": "48190", "page": 77, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-25", "text": "This game is really fun even though the wrist blade is unrealastic. I can't write much of a review because i am on a mac book air which doesn't run this type of game well. From my experience with this game i rate it a 7.5/10 I rate it this low just because I find that the future part and you are using a machine to go into the past is kind of stupid it should just be you are playing a character in the past. This is probably the theme throughout all assassins creed but i don't know so I can't talk about other Assassins Creed Brotherhood.", "hours": 2.7, "user_id": "76561198208784836", "username": "Wooglet", "products": 134, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 77, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-25", "text": "First of all,  this game is good,  It doesn't lag at all,  FPS satys at a range from 50-60,  but the storyline.  The storyline is terrible with one of the worst endings i've seen in a game EVER.  Yet the free roam is awesome. And the Da Vinci machine missions in my opinion are the greatest part of the game.", "hours": 53.3, "username": "gnome person", "products": 84, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 77, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-23", "text": "Excellent game. Great plot for the continuation of Ezio's storyline. But I still find the fighting mechanis very easy and needed to be stepped up.\n9/10", "hours": 4.3, "username": "Decr0zeath", "products": 53, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 77, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-20", "text": "I\u2019ll make this easy.\nEnjoy Assassin\u2019s Creed II? Buy this game. Didn\u2019t like AC II? Don\u2019t buy this game. Didn\u2019t play AC II? Buy and play AC II first.", "hours": 35.2, "user_id": "76561198007197608", "username": "[S]almon", "products": 274, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 77, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-20", "text": "Sadly this is the final decent game in my opinion from the Assasins Creed Francise- Not only did it carry with it everything that was great from the previous 2 games but it added more game machanics and improved on what AC 1 and 2 brought to the table. I felt this was outstanding and an original masterpiece in it's own right - a game that stood on it's own completly. This is an all time classic and deserves to get a 9.5 out of 10. Sadly after playing all AC titles after this, they all suffered greatly from the cash grab syndrome, being released with numorous bugs glitches and sound desync bugs otherwise known as rush jobs.", "hours": 5.9, "user_id": "76561198036004266", "username": "Acid-Man", "products": 159, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 77, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-20", "text": "Now we are in Rome, which is little bigger than Florence or Venice, but only Rome. The best thing in this game is that you can recruit assassins and use them during missions to help, which is really big help and makes the game smooth. Nice little mechanic that makes the game more enjoyable.", "hours": 32.2, "user_id": "76561198012833532", "username": "Awesomo 2000", "products": 435, "early_access": false}
