{"product_id": "48190", "page": 85, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-18", "text": "Assassin's Creed: Brotherhood is an excellent game. It offers plenty of playtime and a great city to explore. While it isn't much different from the gameplay in AC2, it does change and add a few new things. It does only offer 1 city (Rome) to explore while AC2 offers 4 cities (Venice, Florence, Forli, and Tuscany). For that reason and a few others, AC2 is the better game in my opinion. Nonetheless, Brotherhood is a worthy sequel to an amazing franchise.\n9/10\nGreat Game :)", "hours": 42.2, "username": "MJmoneybagsHD", "products": 41, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 85, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-17", "text": "If you're really not into games like Assassin's Creed, then I'll tell you, even though you don't like it, this game is \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing amazing! It's the best game in the entire Assassin's Creed series, if you ask me. The quality is even really good for when it came out, although I don't really care about graphics. I recommend playing 2 before you start playing this one, but if you don't care about storyline, than go on son, by yourself a little gift! It starts off in the year 1499 at your uncle Mario's Villa, where you start where you have ended in 2. After doing some small missions the Villa immediately gets attacked by a guy called Cesare and his army. It's totally recommended!", "hours": 38.8, "username": "Green Cunt", "products": 159, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
