{"product_id": "48190", "page": 85, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-01-16", "text": "-Some of the missions were buggy, I had to reload the last chapter several times,\n-The AI is pos, the soldiers were glitchy a lot of times,\n-I synched one of the viewpoints several times, still didn't gave me the synchronization for that tower and it was still on my map,\n-IMO, AC2 was better.\nI regreted buying the Deluxe Edition, I'm disappointed.", "hours": 14.9, "username": "Niko Bellic", "products": 497, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 85, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-15", "text": "A great game that extends the story of Ezio Auditore from Assassin's Creed 2, as this game starts off exactly where AC2 ended. I really enjoyed the upgrades they made for this game which made the gameplay more enjoyable, which includes the recruitment of assassin's to help you fight along the rest of the game, very useful. This game also has a great setting of Rome which you can explore. However, one of the things which I hate about this game are they included the 100% sync requirements in every mission. It's satisfying once you have completed it but some of missions are impossibly hard. The worse thing is that you can't revert to the last checkpoint if you failed the 100% sync. Apart from the cons, this game is still a must play for any AC fans out there, I give it a 8/10 overall.", "hours": 56.7, "username": "Natlam-ini", "products": 35, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 86, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-15", "text": "A great game that extends the story of Ezio Auditore from Assassin's Creed 2, as this game starts off exactly where AC2 ended. I really enjoyed the upgrades they made for this game which made the gameplay more enjoyable, which includes the recruitment of assassin's to help you fight along the rest of the game, very useful. This game also has a great setting of Rome which you can explore. However, one of the things which I hate about this game are they included the 100% sync requirements in every mission. It's satisfying once you have completed it but some of missions are impossibly hard. The worse thing is that you can't revert to the last checkpoint if you failed the 100% sync. Apart from the cons, this game is still a must play for any AC fans out there, I give it a 8/10 overall.", "hours": 56.7, "username": "Natlam-ini", "products": 35, "early_access": false}
