{"product_id": "48190", "page": 97, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-11-05", "text": "6/10\nFairly dissappointed. The story campaign was not as expected. Controls are obviously not optimized for PC gameplay, although still playable. Combat system improved since previous titles but not as good as the new ones. Parkour system is awful. Missions (including side missions) are too repetetive. Story length is equivalent to other AC games. It's honestly not as \"epic\" as the trailer makes it seem like it is.", "hours": 24.3, "username": "bignut", "products": 26, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 97, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-05", "text": "Beat this on 360 back in the day.\nMore Ezio? Yes plz.\nRoma? Yes plz.\nFurthers the AC plot and is a fun game. There are better AC games if this is your first step into the franchise, but if you're a completionist getting the franchise and/or beating it in the order they came out then it's an obvious buy.", "hours": 1.6, "user_id": "76561198004230891", "username": "Smug Pug", "products": 200, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 97, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-11-04", "text": "Unfortunately I don't get to rate the game as the designers intended because stupid Ubisoft didn't include controller support for the Mac version. Be aware, after much searching online, I have not been able to find a solution to this. How dumb a problem is this ot be having? It's 20-****ing-15. If I could control the game, it'd probably be super fun.\nPlease also know my review only pertains to the OS X version of the game.", "hours": 0.2, "user_id": "76561198056555165", "username": "lehestro", "products": 227, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 97, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-04", "text": "This was a great game. One of the best I've played in the AC series. As a bit of a Roman history junkie I enjoyed getting to run around a medieval Rome where things weren't as destroyed yet as they are today. You can run up to the top of the Pantheon. Do you need more?", "hours": 35.5, "username": "NZRevan", "products": 138, "early_access": false}
