{"product_id": "48190", "page": 97, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-01", "text": "Good continuation of 2, if you liked that one you will probably like this one.", "hours": 37.4, "username": "Halen5", "products": 951, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 98, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-10-31", "text": "I really wanted to like this game, I came from playing Black Flag where the controls are smooth and well setup and this was a clear downgrade.\nReally liked the story and the main character as far as I got, but the controls totally ruined the gameplay for me.\nAfter seeing how much easier it was to control your character in Black Flag, Rogue and even Unity I couldn't find the motivation to keep playing.\nIf you can ignore the controls or get used to them, this seems like a good game. If you can't, I'd recommend Black Flag instead (unless you hate pirates ofc).", "hours": 2.9, "user_id": "76561197970778363", "username": "Mini Me", "products": 193, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 98, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-10-30", "text": "Cesare is hot.\nNearly forgot to mention: last hour of gameplay is hysterically awful. Just stop before the last infiltration and watch a 60 second version on youtube. It's ok though I think Ubisoft will do the right thing with this series from here on in... right...", "hours": 33.2, "user_id": "76561198141424386", "username": "Saulty", "products": 160, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 98, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-10-30", "text": "Continuing with Ezio's storyline and adding in new elements of combat, Assassin's Creed Brotherhood is a good experience overall. Though the fact that there is only one city to explore, Rome, can be a little limiting compared to the various setting of Assassin's Creed 2, there is still plenty to do. The combat has become quicker and better with sequenced executions and  you get a ton of opportunities to fully exercise these new skills throughout the game. Added on is the fact that you can recruit other assassins and manage a guild, which I found an interesting element of gameplay. The storyline is somewhat more predictable than in Assassin's Creed 2, but it nonetheless carries through just fine. Aside from that, multiplayer is good, but rather basic. Nonetheless, is this game a good sell.", "hours": 81.2, "user_id": "76561198008155152", "username": "Dr. VonDerButch", "products": 19, "early_access": false}
