{"product_id": "48190", "page": 102, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-10-13", "text": "Let me start off by saying that I love the Assassin's Creed game franchise, but this game is literally unplayable on windows 10. First, you have to download the crappy Uplay DRM launcher. It barely works and I had to reinstall it several times. Once opening the game, it lags and stutters at horrible speeds. I can barely get through th game menu at 5 fps. I am running dual GTX 970's.... my hardware is not the problem, the software is. Do not get this game if you have windows 10, I recommend reading the online forums about this game.", "hours": 0.3, "username": "Letsgetlostatsea", "products": 22, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 102, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-10-13", "text": "Considerig how this game just came out for mac, I figured I'd inform my fellow mac users on how it performs. Short answer: great.\nLong answer:\nI am playing this game with my 2015 macbook pro 15\". This game has been incredibly optimised for this system, for I can run the game at 60 fps and maximum settings. However, since the game is so well ported, it works much better than most other ports. I'm sure it can be run on any mac at various settings. As someone frequently concerned with port quality, I can confirm that this one is beautiful.\nOne more thing: There is a new problem where on some systems where the game crashes on launch.\n. There you go :).", "hours": 2.1, "username": "gayred", "products": 56, "early_access": false}
