{"product_id": "48190", "page": 102, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-10-13", "text": "If AC II defined this series then Brotherhood truly perfected it! Syndicate my\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665", "hours": 17.8, "user_id": "76561198123258008", "username": "marijan773", "products": 83, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 102, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-10-12", "text": "Little has changed between AC: Brotherhood and its predecessor Assassin's Creed II. Nonetheless it's a decent game, and its recreation of Rome is gorgeous.", "hours": 19.5, "username": "Dan Bull", "products": 3619, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 103, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-10-12", "text": "The best game in the series.  A well-polished adventure experience set in the Rennaisance Rome without the usual AC bugs and camera issues that were present in the previous games. Fascinating & engaging story, various side missions, smooth combat mechanics and fantastic graphics that hold great against time.\nMy overall rating 9/10\np.s. And, contrary to what others say, it does work on Windows 10", "hours": 53.0, "username": "Dimitri Cosmos \u2705", "products": 291, "found_funny": 5, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 103, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-10-12", "text": "A piece of art.  Many games recieve hype and praise but end up as a lukewarm pot of old stew. This game and the series it is apart of are masterful in both the gameplay and story. Investment and Intrigue mark some of the utmost feelings when playing this handcrafted masterpiece.", "hours": 44.0, "username": "Johntheblack99", "products": 477, "early_access": false}
