{"product_id": "48190", "page": 112, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-07-19", "text": "Soooo.... I didn't enjoy AC II but I thought what the hell since Ubisoft keeps releasing this series that I should continue with this\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 So about 7 to 8 hours into the game (close to the end) it descided to \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 with me. It keeps glitching. ALL OF THE \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ING TIME. Ohh... and the last Ezio chapter or sequence or how ever the \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 you want to call it... I couldn't start the last part, the game didn't load the cinematic. I did a quick google search and it turns out I'm not the only one who had this problem. So I eventually found a solution - turn on Vsync. Like seriously? I MEAN LIKE WHAT THE ACTUAL \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665. \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665. This. Game. Don't buy it. Ubisoft, you're the reason I drink.", "hours": 15.6, "username": "Coke", "products": 131, "early_access": false}
