{"product_id": "48190", "page": 120, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-27", "text": "The Best Assassin's Creed Game in my Opinion. Definitely worth the price!", "hours": 3.2, "username": "Nutty Granny168", "products": 130, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 121, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-26", "text": "Awesome game; stunning graphics; Ancient Rome comes to life again; as an Assassin & his compatriots work to wrestle the evil Borgia family from power; befriend Leonardo for access to cutting edge (for ancient Rome, that is) technology to help you accomplish your quests.....\nIf you are a lover of history; you will fall in love with this game; while a fictionalized story; the history is that Rome has been brought back to life to live via the game....\nThe game is somewhat a shooter; but your stealth, & hand to hand fighting abilities are a big part of what makes it interesting; the lush map of famous landmarks & archetecture of Rome gives the game soul....", "hours": 131.4, "user_id": "76561198024848318", "username": "VanSchaick", "products": 54, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 121, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-26", "text": "Without a doubt the best Assassin's creed game out there, being the second game featuring Ezio, this game is one to buy and never forget. 10/10 story line and beautiful gameplay.  Playing Assassin's creed II I just had to buy this game just to see what would happen to Ezio, then following this game: Assassin's Creed Revelations Ezio's story just gets even better. anyone who has enjoyed Assassin's creed games in the past will definitely want to play this game, just be sure to play Assassin's Creed II before playing this one to understand the story line. Overall 10/10 would bang.", "hours": 36.9, "username": "megamutt216", "products": 28, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 121, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-26", "text": "PROS:\n-you can throw axes and swords, extremly satisfying\n-economy\n-shops\n-buying landmarks\n-training recruits\n-lot of bussiness outside of story\nCONS:\n-terrible controls (slightly better with gamepad)\n-boring story, nothing happened at all\n-prone to crashes\n-apple of eden is useless, I kill faster with my axe\nThe game was good when I was buying out landmarks and shops, renovating stuff and training recruits. When there wasn't anything else left to do, I completed the plot which was pretty bad.\nTL;DR:\nLots of sideactivities, including interesting economy and recruit training. You can throw axes. Plot is boring. Controls are extremly annoying.\n6/10\n(would be 9/10 if I ignored the story and stopped playing after finishing all bussiness in the economy and recruit training).", "hours": 45.9, "username": "Earth Ultimatum IV.", "products": 137, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 121, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-26", "text": "I know \u0131 am following the series from behind,but my hardware needs to be upgraded.Anyway, ths game is one of the few games that really captivated me. Even though \u0131 finishd the game before, \u0131 just want to play it again, and again :)", "hours": 115.8, "username": "Darth-Talis", "products": 30, "early_access": false}
