{"product_id": "48190", "page": 121, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-25", "text": "This time you can murder people with you fellow justice-league friends.", "hours": 11.5, "user_id": "76561198109589421", "username": "Waffle Wizard", "products": 266, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 121, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-05-24", "text": "Doesn't work on mac and is a rehash", "hours": 1.6, "user_id": "76561198055866254", "username": "Shmoney", "products": 83, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 121, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-24", "text": "It isn't Assassin\u2019s Creed Brotherhood, it's more Assassin\u2019s Creed 2, and that is not a bad thing. The main problem is that the story is perhaps not as enthralling as its predecessor, but if you've played through Assassin\u2019s Creed 2, the entire situation is given a little more context. If you found some annoying problems with the movement or combat in Assassin\u2019s Creed 2, they will probably still be present, so be warned. The resource management minigame is an interesting distraction, and there is some satisfaction to be had in seeing your hired assassins become more skillful.", "hours": 42.6, "username": "Rice", "products": 319, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 121, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-23", "text": "Do you like doing the same frustrating thing over and over again, and looking at the same flashing red FAIL screen everytime when you do not play the game exactly  the way the game wants you to play it?  Well this is the game for you!  This game is such a mix-up of playing styles, some really fun and some really frustrating and totally not fun.  It really seems like a frankenstein game made up of different parts by different programming teams - as the INCREDIBLY long credits proves!  Just too much design by committee here instead of a single vision.  Yes, I did finish the game but it was such a chore to do so, I couldn't wait for it to be over.  I guess I do recommend it as I did finish the game, but it's really not as much fun as the first 2 games in the series in my opinion.  And that ended - wtf!  Really a total letdown to end the game like that especially after the previous game ended so well.", "hours": 36.5, "user_id": "76561198024922437", "username": "Santa", "products": 440, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 121, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-23", "text": "Wow, this game is only that tiny bit different to Assassin's Creed II and maybe it is only the fully clothed sexscene that got me into buying this one... nah, just kidding. It was the Return of Ezio Auditore aka manlyman who came to rescue the day and place some punchlines (with blades I mean).\nThis game seems to go out to the unreachable guys and gamers that like to play other games like GTA San Andreas or True Crimes: Streets of LA. I can not think of any other reason why they should name this one Brotherhood, x-capt for your crip in which you be hustling together with the girls of the streets and 5-fingers of the subs when you are going to kick some dog's who go by their crip of the Wolfpack - Yo (Sorry, I got no idea where this is going)\n9/10 Assassin attack! Good boy.", "hours": 36.2, "user_id": "76561198036498823", "username": "Solanum nigrum", "products": 1136, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 122, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-22", "text": "While the Assassin's Creed series isn't exactly shining at the time that I write this, this game is, and likely always will be, my favorite Assassin's Creed game and one of my favorite games of all time. It has a vast and realistic depiction of Rome, with details so accurate you can find some of the small alleys that really exist there in-game. It has complex characters and a charismatic lead who is questionable but sympathetic. It has side missions that actually engross you. It is essentially everything that AC2 was, but with a little more gameplay variety, and in Rome to boot. I strongly recommend this game.", "hours": 29.9, "username": "AshleyTrash", "products": 132, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 122, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-05-21", "text": "CANT FREAKIN PLAY ON MAC KEEPS CRASHING\nCANT EVEN START THE GAME", "hours": 0.1, "username": "tragic", "products": 6, "early_access": false}
