{"product_id": "48190", "page": 122, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-10", "text": "Hi again, last time I was reviewing Rogue (AC) and now time for Brotherhood!!!\nSo, Assassin's Creed Brotherhood have epic and intresting story of Ezio Auditore. It takes place in Monteriggioni, small, peaceful city, but peaceful for not so long.\nGame itself have great graphic and clear details. Characters there are awsome (as in every AC series). But Now, let's see + and - :\nGood:\n+Great Graphic\n+Superb story\n+Amazing Fights\n+Epic Brotherhood\n+City is a great parkour place\n+Multiplayer\nNow, Bad stuff:\n-Extra short story\n-Some missions are boring or easy\n-Memes\nSo Buy this awsome game if you wish to join Ezio brotherhood!!!!", "hours": 12.2, "username": "BountyHunterV.5 hellcase.com", "products": 149, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 123, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-04", "text": "It is great it took the good things that ac2 had,and even improved the bad ones,the story was great,gameplay was improved and much more. 9/10", "hours": 24.5, "username": "StahlGrim", "products": 177, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 123, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-02", "text": "This is one if not the best assassins creed! Playing as Ezio again is super fun ( and sad ). The only problem I had was playing as Desmond. Its difficult for me to play as him, but otherwise this game is GREAT!", "hours": 3.9, "username": "R3", "products": 10, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 123, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-02", "text": "is a parkour beat'em up adventure game. On the run from Abstergo, Desmond further explores his ancestor Ezio's memory to find where he had hidden the Apple of Eden, bringing him to the Papal Wars when he settled in Rome to rebuild the Assassin Brotherhood and oppose the Templars that controlled the Vatican.\n: Once again improves on the previous one, introducing new mechanics early and giving a coherent reason for starting from scratch. Replaced multiple medium maps by one large open world: Rome and the surrounding countryside and villages, which you assist in rebuilding by investing in it. Looting enemies now gets you ammunition, more money, and actual loot which can be sold or traded to unlock equipment. The near-future is also more relevant, as Desmond can log out of the Animus and interact more with Lucy and the others. Oh, and another WTF ending!\n: Rome is a clusterfrak to parkour in: streets zigzag incoherently while rooftops are so uneven it's faster to just run on the floor than climb up and down all the time. The loot you get is mostly clutter you'll sell, only a few of which you'll use to unlock stuff. Graphics didn't see much change at all. The last Ezio chapters are rushed.\n: \u2605\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2606 - Next on your list!\nGreat sequel to\n, but it's basically \"more of the same\" with some light improvement and more story. Don't play without playing the previous one first, and if you did like the previous one, you'll love this one, too!\n\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014", "hours": 44.8, "user_id": "76561198030788488", "username": "Cracktus Jack", "products": 327, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 123, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-02", "text": "The story of Ezio Auditore continues on with Brotherhood that brings new gameplay elements and multiplayer.\nThe story is on par with the last game and brings plenty of hours of fun. However the multiplayer is awful and unbalanced. Even if you would try to play the multiplayer you would probably never be able too because it's long dead.", "hours": 73.5, "username": "J.Jensen", "products": 756, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 123, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-02", "text": "If you like Assassin's Creed 2, then you will surely like the Brotherhood. It's not just a continuation of the story, but it also the extension of your abilities to influence the environment: rebuilding Rome, collecting stuff, completing the guild challenges. To do everything this game has to offer, it will take you quite a lot of time, so be prepared and... enjoy the ride!", "hours": 58.9, "username": "Nocturnal Stalker", "products": 761, "early_access": false}
