{"product_id": "48190", "page": 123, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-04-27", "text": "Great game! Good successor after Assassin's Creed II. Rome has been made well and after the initial confusion it turns out to be very huge and explorable. There are lot's to do for everyone, who has even bit of an adventurious nature and even though combat is way too easy and crossbow is significantly overpowered, one can easily overcome these by trying pacifistic (hurt minimal amount) or ghostlike (not been seen or vanquish right away when seen), or what ever the player feels like. Little problems setting up ubisoft user but game made it all quickly up. Also I was suprised that the online player vs player was still plentifully occupied with fellow assassins.", "hours": 46.2, "user_id": "76561198131403511", "username": "thotyyh", "products": 67, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 124, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-04-27", "text": "Great game! Good successor after Assassin's Creed II. Rome has been made well and after the initial confusion it turns out to be very huge and explorable. There are lot's to do for everyone, who has even bit of an adventurious nature and even though combat is way too easy and crossbow is significantly overpowered, one can easily overcome these by trying pacifistic (hurt minimal amount) or ghostlike (not been seen or vanquish right away when seen), or what ever the player feels like. Little problems setting up ubisoft user but game made it all quickly up. Also I was suprised that the online player vs player was still plentifully occupied with fellow assassins.", "hours": 46.2, "user_id": "76561198131403511", "username": "thotyyh", "products": 67, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 124, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-04-26", "text": "great story, good graphics, no bugs no problems smooth gameplay. only problem with multiplayer not alot of players online so dont trust it to be online.", "hours": 50.1, "username": "idan", "products": 200, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 124, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-04-26", "text": "While the story is more grounded then AC II this game is far from disappointing with all your fellow assasins by your side as you begin to develop the reach and influence of your brotherhood. The gameplay is smooth and their is plenty to do on the side to get more florins for your coin purse. The story is incredibly well done and has been done so that even in short play sessions you can make enough progress to leave you wanting more . Overall, assasins creed brotherhood is a perfect 10/10 and remember nothing is true , everything is permitted!", "hours": 26.9, "user_id": "76561198056310151", "username": "TJ", "products": 24, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 124, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-04-25", "text": "WAS a fun game for me, until I forgot what my Uplay Account password was.\nSo from now until the end of time I cant play this game because of Uplay.", "hours": 96.7, "username": "Steelmeat Fistdick", "products": 164, "early_access": false}
