{"product_id": "48190", "page": 130, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-02-28", "text": "Ubisoft games are absurd. I need to input a cd-key, i have to login to ubisoft after that and associate my email, I need to be loged in to the internet, and I need to remember my damn username and password and input it every time I want to play my OFFLINE game.\nBesides that the controller support is absolute crap.\nI will never ever buy any other game from ubisoft", "hours": 45.4, "username": "skzo", "products": 32, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 130, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-27", "text": "Assassin's Creed 2.5, as I would call it. Ezio is back in an extension to his storyline, and even more great features are added such as training assassins. Another fantastic storyline is introduced, and while it is not as long and there are not as many contracts to kill, the enjoyment as playing as Ezio still remains in this inbetweener game. While there were some plots in the game that I wish I would have been able to do (which will not be mentioned for sake of spoilers) I still thoroughly enjoyed the game. The rebuilding aspect is brought back as you try to rebuild Roma and eradicate every Borgia influence in the town (which I did not do and struggled with getting money to buy extra armor to raise my health.) I give this game a 9.1/10", "hours": 11.6, "username": "[PG] Lildog", "products": 375, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 130, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-02-27", "text": "Dont mind the 2 hours, ive played this on other systems and its the same ol assassins creed. nothing spectacular from the others. not sure how it got in my library must have been drunk or stoned when i got it. go with black flag and forward those are the good ones. and the first one. i do not recommend due to repetitiveness and the fact it took 4 years to make the first one and now they come out with one or two every year. they just use the same interface guys but with a different time era and story. i feel they re becoming a major rip off like call of duty franchise. what i see. sorry", "hours": 2.7, "user_id": "76561198087141532", "username": "ColumbianCokaCola", "products": 76, "early_access": false}
