{"product_id": "48190", "page": 131, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-21", "text": "AC: B...\nWhat can I say?\nIt's the second chapter in the Ezio-trilogy. Moving around the Rome is actually pretty fun, and if you feel like learning something, the Animus Database has some interesting facts and knowledge of history.\nThe new Assassin Recruiting -mechanic was really fun, and it helps in some situations a lot.\nThe game itself plays just like AC2, but the plot isn't actually as compelling, although still pretty good.\nThe end of the game was hectic as \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 and I loved it the most in the game.\nThere's not enough Da Vinci, though. That's a minus, but otherwise the game was very fun!", "hours": 53.0, "user_id": "76561198046741114", "username": "Glass Half-Spilled", "products": 247, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 131, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-21", "text": "One of the best assassin creed games. This is pretty much assassins creed 2 but with the added ability of gaining more members for your brotherhood by saving them from templars.\nAlso there is multiplayer but noone plays it anymore so dont bother.\nAnd i dont know why everyone's complaning about uplay, I just put in the code and its done. The added ability to get outfits and weapons in the game for uplay points is cool as well.\nI should also mention that you should not get the dulexe edition unless you want 2 admittedly cool characters for multiplayer but noone plays it so theirs no point, you get a outfit for singleplayer, and also the songtrack of the game,and some more singleplayer maps.\n8/10 Get it on sale", "hours": 10.9, "username": "Copyright", "products": 206, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 131, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-02-19", "text": "Assassin's creed broterhood is a good game with a wonderful graphic and with a faithful reproduction of the Rome in the 15th century.\nUnfortunately I  have not felt the same empaty like in the previous chapters of Asssassin's creed,maybe because also if the story by itself is not bad at all,it is not the main part of the game ,It is more a killing  a captain to free a zone by the Borgia influence,without any strategy or story and so far for the major part of the game, not involving a real sense in your action!\nSo...you can buy it and have hours of fun,considering the presence of a nice multiplayer too,but about me is a little step down in confront the other 2 previous Assassin's creed games!\nMy vote 7/10!", "hours": 40.5, "user_id": "76561198001884138", "username": "Arafenix", "products": 428, "early_access": false}
