{"product_id": "48190", "page": 144, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-26", "text": "+ Classic stabby-climby gameplay still not getting old.\n+ Improves a lot of little things from ACII (everything is more expensive so money has more meaning, ability to buy maps to find all those damn flags & feathers)\n+ Challenge modes in crazy virtual-land are actually quite fun.\n+ Rome setting pretty awesome - climbing all over the Colosseum is cool.\n+ Ordering instant assassinations from the Brotherhood: OP or hilarious every time?\n- Story is confusing for the first few hours unless you've just played ACII.\n- Is there any practical difference between the crossbow, throwing knives and pistol?\n- Played 40 hours, still don't understand investment system.", "hours": 40.6, "user_id": "76561198021885112", "username": "scoredog", "products": 107, "early_access": false}
