{"product_id": "48190", "page": 147, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-20", "text": "Assassin`s Creed Brotherhood is a direct sequel to Assassin`s Creed 2.\n- You can enter into cities with your horse.\n- You can whistle for call to a horse, when you click the key \"E\".\n- You can do assassination from a horse.\n- You can combine a kill with the main weapon and pistol.\n- Blood added to.\n- You can recruit people to the brotherhood from the city, and call them for help when you click the key \"T\".\n* You can send them to assassinations around the worldwide.\n* You can improve there skills, change there color suit.\n- New guns are added to the game.\n- New Combo kills.\n- The combat system become easier and it`s not good at all, because\nit`s make the batlles more EZ to win.\n- There are some problems with the \"Artificial Intelligence' of the game.\n* Good graphics for 2011.\n* The Sound effects and background music are ok.\n* Nice story.\n* A lot of \"side missions\" that you can do.\n* A huge open world map.\n* Nice parkour animation.\n9/10\nI liked more the \"gameplay\" of AC 2 but... in general \"Assassin`s Creed Brotherhood\" is\na good continue to Assassin`s Creed 2.\nI'm recommend this game.", "hours": 32.9, "username": "lofty", "products": 38, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 147, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-19", "text": "Continuing the trilogy of semi-young assassin, Ezio. Struggling with fighting templars and securing the Apple of Eden. Not quite as long and complex as second Assassin's Creed II, although it is still great. Controls did not come through a lot of changes from previous Assassin's Creed games. Nice graphic style, and Roma looks so good on high details. 'We work in the dark to serve the light, we are Assassins.'", "hours": 62.9, "username": "Silencer", "products": 161, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 147, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-18", "text": "I actually prefer AC Brotherhood to AC II, though that's not to say I didn't like AC II. I really liked the story line in AC II so the continuation of that story in this episode kept me engaged throughout. Some missions do get repetative but there were some additions made to Brotherhood that helped seperate it from AC II.\nIf you've never played an Assassin's Creed game I would highly recommend this one, after you finish AC II. If you just play the main story missions you will still get a solid experience from this series but if you're someone who likes to complete all of the side quests and collect all items you will spend a lot of time enjoying this game.", "hours": 61.4, "username": "HomeBrewDude", "products": 77, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 147, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-18", "text": "Absolutely love the game, brilliant gameplay, thoughtful quests, realistic (Apart from the Parkour, which is still realy cool) And all historically correct!", "hours": 141.3, "user_id": "76561198127381150", "username": "Smoke Trees", "products": 83, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
