{"product_id": "48190", "page": 148, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-13", "text": "Great follow up for the best game in the series, and in my opinion the last Assassin's Creed game that doesn't suck. Reasonable story, beautiful city, great design overall.\nWhat makes it actually great is the multiplayer mode. In console version, I spend over 80 hours back in the day, just playing the multiplayer. It's appearently not everyone's cup of tea but if you like it, you will be spending lots of hours. It is better than AC: Revelations Multiplayer because Ubisoft watered down the damn game, in order to make it more accessible. Multiplayer mode in PC still has player base, which makes it a worthwhile buy for me. If you like stealthy, sneaky-stabby action, then this is for you.", "hours": 0.3, "user_id": "76561198020486150", "username": "malachai", "products": 427, "early_access": false}
