{"product_id": "48190", "page": 149, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-08", "text": "I love assasin's creed with a passion but brotherhood isn't the best of the series, I played it until i found almost all of the easter eggs and did all of the quests and now it is just boring. All I can do is just freeroam, kill people, kill more people, or have my assasins kill people.\nIn the end, this game gets old too fast", "hours": 72.5, "user_id": "76561198116268887", "username": "Major Boom", "products": 92, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 149, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-07", "text": "The first two hours are an interactive slideshow, then half of the rest of the game are cinematics and half are easy missions. There are multiple sidequests and missions besides the mainline, but once you finish the main one, you can not go back and finish the others. Overall the experience leaves a bad taste.", "hours": 27.2, "username": "Julio Nobrega", "products": 414, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 149, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-07", "text": "+ nice place (Rome)\n+ assassin recruits\n+ worth to collect optionals\n+ good story\n- still poor fighting mechanism\n- camera views can be annoying sometimes (it's true for the all II too)", "hours": 66.2, "user_id": "76561198069358881", "username": "juhasz.roland.istvan", "products": 224, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 149, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-07", "text": "Assassin's Creed Brotherhood it's fine game.\nSingle-player:\nYou got new location - it's Rome, weps from Assassin's Creed II and few new: instant poison and arbalest (same time here we are can select battle tactics), long story and big open world, good graphic (for me graphic from Assassin's Creed II was looks to much better). Much cute girls like at Assassin's Creed II (\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ls <3 which can fallow you :3).\nHere we are got again Leonardo da Vinci. Will got much interesting quest from him.\nI Love Italy <3 But location at Rome for me is bored.\nMultiplayer:\nAssassin's Creed Brotherhood it's first game of Assassin's Creed which got multiplayer. Much chars for select and much maps. Not bad gameplay.\nGraphic at multiplayer looks to much better then at single-player (for me).", "hours": 33.1, "username": "\u01b8\u04c1\u01b7 Bunny Girl \u01b8\u04c1\u01b7", "products": 573, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 149, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-06", "text": "Yes, this is an old out-dated, no longer next-generation game. Yes, AC III, and AC IV have better grahpics, but Assassin's Creed Brotherhood triumps all other Assassin's Creed games, because if you play AC II, you will be both emotionally invested and a understanding of all Ezio's actions. This game was the basis for the current recruiting system Assassin's creed has.\nI would buy this game, and you should too. Because some games are worth keeping.", "hours": 0.4, "username": "Drakyl Yukishiro", "products": 84, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 149, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-05", "text": "Have you ever dreamed to visit renasiance Italy? Want to be an assassin and control your assassin budies? Yes? Then this is your game! Although this game can be a bit easy sometimes, it will challenge you enough.\nDon't wait any longer and buy this awesome assassin's creed game! (Just do it, it is only \u20ac15 ;)", "hours": 20.9, "user_id": "76561198068030515", "username": "Gaius Marius Cesar\u00e9", "products": 43, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 149, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-04", "text": "It took some time to get UPLAY to work correctly but it was worth it for the game. I would say I have basic competence at using forums to fix my problems so it really isn't to hard to get it to work.\nI only played the first two games and decided to buy this one because people said it was one of the best ones. I was not really to big of a fan of the first two, I just really liked the concept. However this one is so dope! There is so much to do in the game that I was not expecting. I have a hard time playing a game for more than a few days unless it is really good (Skyrim, Rust, Cod 4 are just a few games I can find enjoyment after playing for so long). It is a little buggy during the cutscenes but that is probably because I am playing on a laptop. If you like free roam games and a decent storyline I highly reccomend it.", "hours": 25.5, "username": "ScoobeeDoobie", "products": 72, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 150, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-04", "text": "It took some time to get UPLAY to work correctly but it was worth it for the game. I would say I have basic competence at using forums to fix my problems so it really isn't to hard to get it to work.\nI only played the first two games and decided to buy this one because people said it was one of the best ones. I was not really to big of a fan of the first two, I just really liked the concept. However this one is so dope! There is so much to do in the game that I was not expecting. I have a hard time playing a game for more than a few days unless it is really good (Skyrim, Rust, Cod 4 are just a few games I can find enjoyment after playing for so long). It is a little buggy during the cutscenes but that is probably because I am playing on a laptop. If you like free roam games and a decent storyline I highly reccomend it.", "hours": 25.5, "username": "ScoobeeDoobie", "products": 72, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 150, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-03", "text": "By far the best game in the series, but I recommend not finishing it too fast. Just enjoy what Ubisoft will never accomplish again.", "hours": 15.4, "user_id": "76561198089699063", "username": "Doctor Vens", "products": 94, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 150, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-03", "text": "Decent. The other games are better, but then this is better than some. I rate this above AC and AC: Revelations, maybe even Black Flag.\nI like alot of the concepts they introduce, like the assassin helpers. Overall a good game, worth it if you find it cheap", "hours": 70.7, "username": "Isaac", "products": 180, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 150, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-03", "text": "A continuation of the second game's story that doesn't do anything different.\nGameplay - 3\nGraphics - 4\nStory - 4\nUI - 3\nReplay Value - 2\nOverall - 3\nGripes:\nGame felt more like DLC than a sequel, doesn't do much other than continue the story.\nIn Debth:\nAs I stated, the game doesn't do much more than continue the story.  And while I realize it's a sequel, a good sequel should bring something new to the table while preserving the thing that made the original entertaining.  The game basically just continued the story and gave Edzio a few new toys.\nIf you want to play the Assassin Creed games for the storyline (and you should), then you should play this game.  It's still fun, it's just a bit tiring in the gameplay department since we've done all of this already.", "hours": 14.0, "user_id": "76561197969628949", "username": "ImAGodDmnDragn", "products": 296, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 150, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-03", "text": "AC Brotherhood is good game with much more action then AC 2\nIt is very fast as well is improved\nGraphics has remained perfect\nstory also\nhonestly recommend it to everyone !", "hours": 14.5, "username": "KingSin", "products": 195, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 150, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-03", "text": "Okay, all Assassin's Creeds have the same basic idea, but they are different usually. But, AC: Brotherhood and AC II are VERY similar in many respects, and since I haven't played them for awhile, I am literally copy-pasting the same review to both of them because I can't remember all the little things that are different, because really, they are very similar. So here we go:\nI love the Assassin's Creed series. I played the first AC about seven years ago, and I played it nonstop. The basic idea of AC is that you are and assassin, and you have a city as your assassination-playground, usually multiple locations. You start the game as Desmond, a guy who uses a machine called the Animus to shoot back in time to his ancestors' history. This is accomplished from the Animus being able to use his mind as a channel for those ancestors' memories.\nThen, you are his ancestor, an assassin. and you have to kill things. The story is usually deep and intriguing, and it brings you along, and the gameplay of it is awesome too. And then you can just do random things as sidequests, usually pickpocketing, or another assassination target, stuff like that.\nYou have two profiles: Low profile, where you don't draw attention, and just push past people, or walk. Then High profile, by holding right trigger, where then you start running and you can parkour, fight, shove through people, and sprint.\nThe combat is fun, and the sneaky-assassinating is satisfying. There's some flaws, but Brotherhood and AC II are probably the best out of this series. Would recommend anybody to try.", "hours": 0.3, "username": "Splatterman", "products": 184, "early_access": false}
