{"product_id": "48190", "page": 151, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-11-30", "text": "The game that broke Assassin's Creed, both in terms of combat and world design.  It's not completely terrible; it's no III, Revelations, or (god forbid) Unity, but it's not quite as good as 2 either.  If you're okay with pathetically easy combat that basically gives any pretense of this being a stealth game the middle finger and spending large portions of your time trotting slowly around big empty fields on a horse, hey, more power to you.\nI really wish Steam would let me give a 'meh' score; not quite yes, not quite no.  Somewhere in between.  Just... you know... meh.", "hours": 83.1, "username": "Trangx", "products": 287, "early_access": false}
