{"product_id": "48190", "page": 152, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-30", "text": "Brotherhood is perhaps my favorite installment in the AC series. An expansive, open-world enviornment allows the player to prance about and complete various tasks in any order they desire without any linear elements. The default controls are a bit strange, but can be easily binded to a custom configuration.\nA unique quality of this game is the ability to relieve notoriety when being pursuded by enemies. This mechanic is not common in other third-person open-world games and proves to be quite useful.\nAll in all, I'm not crazy about Brotherhood, but it was definitely worth the buy. I would rate it 8/10.", "hours": 29.8, "username": "Raiin", "products": 77, "early_access": false}
