{"product_id": "48190", "page": 157, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-11", "text": "The follow up of AC2. If you liked the way AC2 was build youre gona love this game. It takes the good parts from AC2 and adds even more to it. Like building youre own familiy of assassins to do work for you.\nAnd this is the 2th game of the history of Etzio one of the grates assassins.\nAll in all if you likes AC2 this is a must have game.", "hours": 13.2, "username": "TheDragonFruite", "products": 640, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 157, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-11", "text": "Fantastic addition to Assassin's Creed. Great story and setting revolving around Ezio in Rome, aguably the best character and story in the whole series.\nNot much different from AC2, but for me, that's a good thing. You can ride horses in cities, call them from anywhere, recruit assassins to your brotherhood, carry double-handed weapons, use parachutes, and play with Leonardo's war machines. Also has a few nice flashbacks to Florence and Venice.\nA few glitches and hiccups here and there, but the setting is otherwise stunning. Beautiful graphics and visuals, combined with a killer soundtrack, makes 16th century Rome look very enticing.", "hours": 10.2, "username": "Boristrop", "products": 149, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
