{"product_id": "48190", "page": 167, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-19", "text": "First of all Ubisoft failed at Mac-ing this game, WARNING: Mac Users Do Not Buy This Easily!!! Check System requirements!!\nI have mavericks and it took a long time to fix it, I had to replace several things including the game launcher. After I fixed AC brotherhood, it was quite awesome. A delicate open world stealth game, with graphics better than the games made in 2014, and of course frustrating parkour that makes u look cool.  Brotherhood continues the story of Ezio Auditore Da La La La in Rome, with intense main storyline, and lots and lots of side missions. Once again I have to warn mac users that before you buy this game think twice, or you can add me on steam, i'll tell you how to fix it.", "hours": 10.3, "username": "dLan", "products": 40, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 167, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-09-17", "text": "Brotherhood picks up right where Assassin's Creed 2 leaves off and it's very much more of the same - not that that's a bad thing. The animations and graphics have improved. The game has a much more fluid feel and pushed the AC storyline along nicely. Being able to restore Rome  and expand your faction houses is a nice addition.", "hours": 31.5, "user_id": "76561197972037748", "username": "Scoilt", "products": 472, "early_access": false}
