{"product_id": "48190", "page": 173, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-27", "text": "Heyyo, not as epic of a build upon predecessors like AC2 was, but still a fun AC game. If you want to complete the series? You won't go wrong on this one. :)", "hours": 29.7, "username": "ThE_MarD", "products": 802, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 173, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-27", "text": "A good continuation from where it left off. Assasins Creed Brotherhood tells the story of Ezio's journey after his time in Florence. Once again Ubisoft has done wonderfully in terms of graphics and gameplay. The city of Rome is an excellent place to perform parkour and free run. Some new additions were also nice, such as being able to recruit your own assasins to help you on your missions. 9/10", "hours": 35.2, "user_id": "76561198026434128", "username": "DopeInder", "products": 162, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 173, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-25", "text": "The best Assassin's Creed game yet in my opinion, Rome is the best setting for the franchise, it may not be the biggest but it is by far the best to explore, the story is also the best of the series! 10/10", "hours": 12.7, "user_id": "76561198102063800", "username": "InFamous-X22", "products": 73, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 173, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-07-25", "text": "So this is where my enjoyment of the AC Series tapered right off and I just decided I CBA with it anymore. More of the same  (admittedly cool) running, the same bloat collect-em-all subgames, the substandard AI and lack of fulfilment of the original AC concept...the watered-down casualisation (yes I just invented a word) of the GTA open-roamer. Inevitably, a typical all-you-can-eat Ubisoft game.\nPersonally I had my fill with AC1 and AC2. Observing the annualisation of the series and general direction probably had more of an influence on my decision not to continue with this game, and series. As a AAA stalwart, AC has always been very polished and maintained high standards, but it is just not the game for me.", "hours": 6.4, "user_id": "76561197980307847", "username": "Masaai_Warrior", "products": 84, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 173, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-25", "text": "+ Fast travel tunnels\n+ Hours upon hours of content\n+ Towers have a unique 'climb pattern', no two are the same\n- Recruits & new combat system make fights too easy", "hours": 46.4, "username": "XYZ", "products": 869, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 173, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-24", "text": "Can't stress it enough. This seems far superior to the previous games in this series. A more open word environment and a higher amount of things to do, this has turned out to be one of my favourite games in the Action/Adventure genre.", "hours": 89.3, "username": "Nurse Mathye", "products": 670, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 174, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-24", "text": "Continuing from Assassin's Creed II this game is fantastic. Now you can recruit assassin's to help you fight your enemies, which is an interesting addition to the series. A fan of Assassin's Creed should definetly buy this.", "hours": 22.6, "username": "MythrilMagician", "products": 94, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 174, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-24", "text": "Hours and hours of awesome and very different play. 9/11, would crash", "hours": 97.4, "username": "doctorwhovian", "products": 856, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 174, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-23", "text": "Gameplay 10/10\nGraphics 9/10\nControls 8/10\nStoryline 9/10\nBug-Free 9/10\nReplayability 9/10\nLevel of Challenge 10/10", "hours": 50.5, "username": "Gettys63", "products": 252, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 174, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-22", "text": "I like new system that allowed you to form your assassins team on your own.\nOf course, when it comes to recruit citizen, I just left male died but if it's female then it's rescue time. So my team is full of girls. lol lol", "hours": 43.3, "user_id": "76561198086061585", "username": "gaia.razus", "products": 1863, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 174, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-21", "text": "Probably the best one out of all of them in my opinion. the rest of the AC series above these are way to easy.", "hours": 66.6, "username": "TheDirtyCubeMan", "products": 136, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 174, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-20", "text": "This title expands to what Assassin's Creed II so great, but also takes a small step back. And that step back is for the better. ACII wanted to make everything bigger and better. They made a lot of things better as opposed to AC1, but some of the cities and locations felt very empty. In this title (which in my opinion should be could Assassin's Creed III: Brotherhood) the entire adventure takes place in Rome. It is gigantic and very well detailed. It looks way better then Assassin's Creed II and there are some subtle improvements to the gameplay of ACII.\nThe Story is not as good as the last two games in the series. The ending is great and leaves you guessing. Ezio is now becoming a Master Assassin and thus recruits new Assassin's. You can call these brothers in arms into battle whenever you wish. Yes, it's a cheap and overpowered way to get yourself out of a tough fight, but I love the way these Assassin's come out of hiding places just like Alta\u00efr or Ezio would. You bond with a lot of characters and I love that.\nIn other words, did you play the wonderful Assassin's Creed II and you want to know the next chapter in the story? Brotherhood is a very safe purchase. Fun, beautiful and exciting! Love it.", "hours": 42.6, "username": "PodjeGamen", "products": 578, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 174, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-20", "text": "whole series is excellent", "hours": 155.1, "user_id": "76561198069466833", "username": "sreeves77", "products": 219, "early_access": false}
