{"product_id": "48190", "page": 175, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-11", "text": "Definitly a step up from AC2, combat, weaponry and customization are way better than its predecesser. The mission are tough and can be very annoying. Out of all the AC games I own (basically all except one) it has the most bugs e.g. versing Cesare Borgia, for some reason Caesare decides o fall down and not get up. Ten minutes later and I have to start the memory again, sucky. But this is a worthwhile game. 8/10.", "hours": 57.9, "username": "Tmart", "products": 15, "early_access": false}
