{"product_id": "48190", "page": 176, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-11", "text": "An awesome game", "hours": 13.0, "user_id": "76561198059181279", "username": "Peerasak.S", "products": 17, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 176, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-10", "text": "Personally, I enjoyed AC2 way more than Brotherhood. I think that Brotherhood was good, but some of the missions felt tacted on to remind you of the new features added on to the series. I think the story progressed nicely, but I felt some of the side missions were too much. Capturing the towers and paying to open up the stores had me hesitant to stay away from those areas until I needed them. Overall the game was good, but not great like AC2 for me.", "hours": 15.7, "username": "dzinction", "products": 360, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 176, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-10", "text": "Great game.", "hours": 165.4, "user_id": "76561198074816301", "username": "Partisan", "products": 29, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 176, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-08", "text": "To be honest, I wasn't expecting much out of this game. Killing, parkour, constant missions. After the tutorial mission, I realized it was more than that. There's missions scattered around the map, you have free play, and you get to strategize your killing. I like how you always need to stay aware of your surroundings, inventory, and resources. The free play allows you to pay attention to Ezio's needs, like allowing more ground to explore by eliminating the Borgia infulence, getting medicine, making sure you always have income room, keeping your armor repaired, and buying new weapons. There's a wide varity of content in the missions, you're not always saving the damsel in distress. Also there's ponies. PONIES. You can ride the ponies!\nPros:\nFantastic graphics, even the hugging of characters is realistic.\nFreedom between missions.\nKeeping up with the character's needs.\nAdventure\nPlot\nVariety of mission content\nMain character development\nPONIES.\nCons:\nAuto-parkour button set (space, w, mouse 2)\nAnnoying background voice tracks\nMap concept is really confusing at first\nBasically any character except Ezio's development\nOf course I reccommend this game to any person that likes the adventure genre, has played previous games in the series, and enjoys having the freedom between missions. 8.5/10", "hours": 20.3, "username": "inferior potassium", "products": 97, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 176, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-07", "text": "By and far one of my personal favorite iterations of the AC series! Brotherhood felt like the peak of the series (at least until the release of Black Flag) especially after the poor showings of Revelations and AC3. In my opinion Brotherhood's expansive content trumps even AC 2, and the story is top notch as well. Recommend purchasing on sale given the long shelf life.", "hours": 22.0, "user_id": "76561198040714246", "username": "Mustangcase", "products": 343, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 176, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-07", "text": "If you havent bought or played this game yet you must have been living under a rock.\nOne of the best Assasins creed games and a must play.", "hours": 9.4, "username": "Rayge", "products": 256, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 176, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-07", "text": "Its a awesome game,it has mutiplayer fun and more! stealth open world action and some serious sword fighting!", "hours": 12.3, "user_id": "76561198098468585", "username": "purrpreme", "products": 94, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 176, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-07-07", "text": "I am rather upset at Uplay and my inability to play the Assassin's Creed series I purchased during the steam summer sale. Had I been aware that I need another third party login that has shoddy uptime at best I would not have purchased this product. I am a fan of this series and would have loved to have played the PC port but alas Uplay denies me access. I wish I could refund this product. :(", "hours": 37.9, "user_id": "76561198052359216", "username": "Big Daddy Crawfish", "products": 94, "early_access": false}
