{"product_id": "48190", "page": 177, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-06", "text": "Best game in the History !.......u get it? ....... in the History :D ................................", "hours": 30.0, "user_id": "76561198071766225", "username": "[TBW] HDgamesinHD", "products": 155, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 177, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-06", "text": "Never been a hardcore fan of Assassins Creed but have played the first two games. Great characters, great story, amazing concept (I'm surprised a $200 million film has been released yet) and a very fun game.\nDefinetly more of a sequel of AC:2 rather than a standalone game however it does catch you up at the begining.\nLoved playing the game, classic AC gameplay however surprised at how short the main story was.", "hours": 17.0, "username": "Banana", "products": 65, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 177, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-06", "text": "Best game in the series", "hours": 71.4, "username": "TheACguy", "products": 64, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 177, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-06", "text": "One the Best games ever in my opinion, Can play this following story or free-play for hours.", "hours": 60.0, "username": "Elrond969", "products": 146, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 177, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-05", "text": "It is ok.", "hours": 1.6, "user_id": "76561198021994352", "username": "Toxic Rick", "products": 200, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 177, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-04", "text": "Assassins Creed Brotherhood expands once again in every aspect of the game. Combat is even more fluid, story is even more engaging, and adds many new features to the Assassins Creed Genre. Oh and there is multiplayer as well. So it adds endless replay ability to the game. If you loved the previous games, you will love this one. They have done away with exploring countless viewpoints to view your map and have minimized the amount of points to explore the map. Though you are on one map of Rome rather than multiple environments, you are still thrown to various areas to spice up the scenery from time to time.\nHaven\u2019t had any problems other than the rare ninja spot where the AI just immediately spot you, even though you are not notorious but it isn\u2019t game breaking. Definitely a must buy, if you loved the previous games.", "hours": 25.8, "user_id": "76561198008241330", "username": "Petroph", "products": 251, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 177, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-04", "text": "Awesome, hilarious, fascinating, unforgettable.", "hours": 43.1, "username": "exclusive-tr", "products": 954, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 177, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-02", "text": "Having previously played AC 1, 2 and this game on console, I wasn't really sure what to expect when I bought this during the Steam Summer Sale 2014..... but it delivered and rekindled my gamer crush on Ezio. Gameplay is immersive. There's your main quest line, side quests, Cluster puzzles, plus a bunch of other tasks you can do within the single player game. There's also multiplayer, which if I can remember my console days clearly, isn't too bad either. Controls take a little while to get used to, especially with the move from console to PC for me, but they are displayed on screen and once you get the hang of what all the buttons to do, the combat is so much more enjoyable. I find this game quite challenging. While completing the quests aren't too difficult, the extra requirements needed for 100% sync makes it a little harder for those who are into full completion. I think this game is so much fun to play and I have yet to tire of the whole franchise.\nI highly reccommend this game and give it an 8 out of 10..... points lost because..... well running away and hiding can get a little annoying when sometimes I just want to kill em all.", "hours": 5.1, "user_id": "76561198071114267", "username": "Neon", "products": 75, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 177, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-02", "text": "achivka", "hours": 6.8, "user_id": "76561198042616990", "username": "LEGIJA", "products": 16, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 177, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-01", "text": "The multiplayer is super intriguing and enjoyable but is sadly devoid of most players in it nowadays.  Rome is a beautiful locale and the attention to historical detail (with a few liberties taken) is quite impressive.  The assassination targets are fun, the new abilities and such are fun, but the one thing that sorta makes things frustarting is the addition of buying property and shops for income, which just becomes a bit of a chore to do and doesn't offer a substantial reward.\nAll in all the game is wonderful to play but is slightly hampered by some \"collect-em-up\" side objectives.", "hours": 38.0, "username": "Wisehowl", "products": 306, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 178, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-01", "text": "Great Game!!!!!!!", "hours": 13.8, "username": "\u0192inal\u0192ear\u0192i\u0192ty\u0192ive", "products": 111, "early_access": false}
