{"product_id": "48190", "page": 179, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-06-29", "text": "Boring, I had to force my self to finish this game to see what happens with the story, but this is by far the worse Assassins Creed game I played, its just so boring.", "hours": 43.1, "username": "Viking2121", "products": 185, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 179, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-29", "text": "Assassin's Creed Brotherhood is what you come to expect from an AAA product. Granted it would be a daunting task to do a reasonable follow up to the ever-so-popular Assassin's Creed 2 however considering it's very slow and somewhat confusing start, stay with it as from sequence four onwards catapults this game into a newer dimension \u2013 not as much as from Assassins Creed 1 to 2 however it's a total blast to play. For a newcomer for the series, if you can handle the spoilers, this game is a wonderful entry point as it has a lot to offer. Overall I felt Brotherhood is a better game than AC2 however without AC2, there's no Brotherhood.\nFull review here:\n9 / 10", "hours": 96.2, "username": "Azghouls", "products": 2058, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 179, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-28", "text": "Ok, where to start.\nAC> Great game\nAC II>  Epic game\nAC brotherhood> Ok game\nThe story is nice overall stuff is nice, its AC nothing more has to be said.\nThings i didint like:  Borgia Towers> Imo this is only a way from ubisoft to make the game longer nothing more- no challange boring as hell\nRebuilding Rome: No way dude, No way Total \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665t, you get money thats nice yes i admit but it takes ages to rebuild everything-The new idea failed in my opinion. If we would have>lets say 3 citys or so like in AC 2 it maybe would adapt into the game but here one city pressing one button to rebuild.... meh\nWhat i loved: You have your own assassins-God mode literally\nOverall: Fun game\n6/10", "hours": 18.6, "user_id": "76561198072305672", "username": "Gr33nViper", "products": 45, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 179, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-06-28", "text": "I can't recommend this game, I bought it because I was interested in the back story as I played black flag, but the control scehem makes no sense and is completely distracting from the game and the game is a direct continuation of the story from the previous game, meaning if you didn't play it, you have no clue what is going on anywhere, and the game does an incredibly bad job of telling you what's what and who's who, I still don't have much of a clue what's going on, and I suspect it will stay that way.\nIf you haven't played the previous game, you probably shouldn't play this.", "hours": 43.0, "username": "Viruzzz", "products": 292, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 179, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-06-28", "text": "If you want to play some MP assassin's creed, keep moving. This assassin's creed is dead. Took 30 mins to find a match", "hours": 2.4, "username": "Flubberson", "products": 161, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 179, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-28", "text": "Great story that is unforgettable", "hours": 19.9, "username": "Question Mark", "products": 156, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 180, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-06-27", "text": "I'm going to keep this review as straight forward as possible:\nIs ACB good? On a techincal level, if not mediocre.\nWill you enjoy it? If you can be ok with a ton of repitition, other wise avoid or take caution.\nBrotherhood is probably one of the more boring games i've played, which is dissapointing considering I thought Assassin's Creed 2 was quite good. All the story missions are the same thing over and over game, kill that thing, go here, don't get caught, and of course FOLLOW MISSIONS, which are one of the worst mission types for any sandbox game ever considering the stealth in this game is shoddy.\nIn comparison to Assassin's Creed 2 it is staggering how much quality has been lost.\nOptimization: Assassin's Creed 2 was nicely optomized for pc, it ran well and I don't recall many issues. For ACB the game is laggy, it looks kinda bleh at times, and the video settings keep going to their defaults every single time you re-enter the game, and I found no way to fix this.\nGameplay: Already covered above; story mission too repetitive, and not really varied. Nothing memorable here.\nSetting: Rome is dull. The landscape is bland and honestly uninteresting. We wen't from the streets of Venice to the open grass lands of...Well Rome. I don't know if it might suit someone else's tastes, but I find it uninteresting.\nThis is honestly a pretty weak game in my opinion, not bad persay, but following Assassin's Creed 2 it just doesn't hold up as well, considering its more of the same plus it being incredibly boring and repetative at times. I wouldn't really recommend it that much, not even if you are trying to follow the story because the two timeline plots have simple start and end points, no real inner 'meat' to add anything signifigant or worth noting or caring about.\nWorth a skip.", "hours": 17.7, "username": "Salmon, Lord of Sinder", "products": 628, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 180, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-26", "text": "A lot longer than I thought it was going to be for an expansion but a great addition to the Assassin's Creed story! Although not much has changed gameplay-wise, the beautiful environment, overall smoothness, and intriguing story are more than enough to want to pick this game up!\n8/10", "hours": 36.7, "username": "HisEvenSeven", "products": 565, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 180, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-26", "text": "Awesome as Hell!", "hours": 28.4, "user_id": "76561198058693471", "username": "TheSupremeQueso", "products": 131, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 180, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-26", "text": "The 2nd of the Ezio trilogy. And if you are new to the games, I would reccomend starting with AC2 first justto understand the story. A definite sequel. Improves upon nearly every single game mechanic of Assassin's Creed 2, and is personally my favorite in the series. The combat is more fluid. The guilds make sense and are utilized in the story. Even capturing areas and exploring the world are tied into the 'story' of the game. I only wish the other games in the series took more notes from this one.", "hours": 27.4, "username": "BristolBonsai", "products": 102, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 180, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-26", "text": "In my humble opinion, this is the best episode of this franchise. It's a shame, that the Coppernicus conspiracy DLC is not available for PC. Anyway, I've played this through multiple times, and still love the gameplay, the story and the locations it takes place in.\nI can recommend it to anyone, but before you start it, first play through ACII, so you develop an attachment to the character and understand the story.", "hours": 113.8, "user_id": "76561198084048180", "username": "cainet", "products": 232, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 180, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-26", "text": "Brotherhood is Assassin's Creed at its best. It takes what's best from AC2 and makes it even better, while changing the mission structure to be more open-world than previous games. I love the ability to call assassins at any time during the game. There's only one city to explore, but Rome is absolutely big and varied, and full of things to do. It's a great and geographically varied setting, ranging from rural areas to densely populated city areas. There's also some additional levels outside the city (Leonardo's war machines missions) and some nice surprises along the way. The secret locations from AC2 also make a return as fantastically designed Lairs of Romulus - these are some great platforming levels and completing them is a real pleasure.\nBrotherhood has a great cast of characters and the overall story is interesting. My only gripe is lack of character development for side characters later in the game - Claudia, Maria and Leonardo all suffer from this, leaving their stories a bit incomplete. What's great about Brotherhood is also the modern day bit of the story. It's fantastic - and you actually get to do things as Desmond.\nThis Assassin's Creed outing has also introduced multiplayer for the first time in the series. Keep in mind that unfortunately multiplayer is mostly dead, as the player base moved to newer games in the series.\nOne last thing: you can also unofficially unlock a free Copernicus DLC that was previously PS3 exclusive. Check out this guide for more information:", "hours": 46.5, "username": "W\u0142odi", "products": 1032, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 180, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-26", "text": "Being a fan of the Assassin's Creed series, this is the game to which I compare any of the following storylines, by far. With simple, yet elegant physics and a storyline which actually made me cry in a side-mission (no spoilers), this game first drew my attention just to edge closer to fulfilling the story of Assasin's Creed 2. Which it does with perfection (by my standards, of course).\nNever before or since this game have I felt so truly free to roam a map and to choose my battles by myself.", "hours": 67.8, "username": "ole.noerby", "products": 647, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 180, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-25", "text": "One of the best of the series if not the best in the series, this is an amazing game with tons to do, and lots of tools to help you do them with. The gameplay is rewarding, and the story is nice. This is an awesome must-have for just about anybody.", "hours": 56.2, "user_id": "76561198084392831", "username": "BigAssWindow", "products": 61, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 180, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-25", "text": "I'm finally catching up on the AC series.  I've played AC I & II and enjoyed them very much.  But they pale in comparison to the 3rd installment, Brotherhood.  I think I could get lost in Rome forever - there is simply so much to do.  Where the previous games had a small set of assignments you could do, this game includes a ridiculous amount.   I'm really enjoying recruiting townsfolk as Assassins, buildling my own Assassin's guild. Sending them out on various missions and upgrading their armor and weapons is quite fun.  Sure, it lacks any real depth - you can't play as the other assassins and you don't have a lot of options to upgrade their skills/weapons/armor, but it is a really nice change of pace to the game.\nSo, between rebuilding Rome, building an army, reclaiming Ezio's lost memories, obtaining art for my hideout, amassing wealth, taking assassination assignments, uniting thieves, \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665s and mercanaries, I'm swamped!\nI haven't even touched up on the story arc, which, of course, is epic.  Between discovering \"the truth\" of Subject 16 ( similar to AC II) and discovering what happened to Ezio's love, Christina, not to mention, taking down the Borgia's - yes, even Lucretia makes an appearance here, the scope of this game is LEGEN....wait for it....DARY!\nI realize this game is a number of years old, but for those who haven't gotten into the Assassin's Creed games, this is a great one to jump into and get aquainted with the series.  I highly recommend this installment and look forward to continuing on to AC:Revelations.", "hours": 49.1, "user_id": "76561198012222464", "username": "mfortunato", "products": 316, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 180, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-25", "text": "First actually immersive Assassins Creed title. Playable for hours on end.", "hours": 12.1, "username": "Milky Beans", "products": 657, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 181, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-25", "text": "First actually immersive Assassins Creed title. Playable for hours on end.", "hours": 12.1, "username": "Milky Beans", "products": 657, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 181, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-25", "text": "Good continuation of the story line, and lots of extras to do outside of the main story line.  I would recommend this game to anyone fan of the series or not. I'm excited to play the next game to see what happens next.", "hours": 74.0, "username": "mochong", "products": 102, "early_access": false}
