{"product_id": "48190", "page": 189, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-18", "text": "Great continuation of the series.\nLike any other AC game, some of the missions can get boring, and a bit of the same over and over.\nBut the story, voice acting and non-linear pacing helps for any play style.\nThe ending is a real cliff hanger but really sets you up for the other installment, and continues the tradition of a great storyline.\nIf you're into the AC story, this part is necessary.", "hours": 28.8, "username": "Doomtack", "products": 1640, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 189, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-17", "text": "16th century Rome is beautiful, a great continuation of the Ezio trilogy. Gameplay is identical to ACII with a few new mechanics so you have nothing to get used to. Difficulty feels like it has been increased but nothing too frustrating. The most notable new mechanic is right in the title, being able to recruit assassins and help you out when you call upon them. However the game starts to feels like a grindfest when you want to rebuild Rome, it's the same mechanic on liberating each sector: muder captain, climb tower, set fire. Rennovating the shops is also just as tedious.\nBut if you a fan of the Assassin's Creed series or open world gamplay, this is something you will enjoy.", "hours": 19.9, "username": "sen", "products": 207, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 189, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-17", "text": "Expanded Assassin\u2019s Creed 2. Using practically everything from the previous game, and just updating/upgrading some stuff to make it feel like \u201cnew\u201d. Is not a bad game, actually is very good, and  you surely will enjoy wasting hours and hours exploring the old Rome and giving back the city most of its former beauty, but think of it as an expansion.", "hours": 27.7, "username": "Celebrimnar", "products": 4591, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 189, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-04-16", "text": "Let me just say that this is my favorite assassins creed followed by two, three and four. I just love how the city feels alive, the combat system is better than ever and even the modern day charachters are actually fleshed out well. The brotherhood mecanich is fun to use. Give this one a try but play one and two first.", "hours": 112.1, "user_id": "76561198019597035", "username": "Kurama (Sean)", "products": 463, "early_access": false}
