{"product_id": "48190", "page": 190, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-03-27", "text": "For OSX i would definitely NOT recommend this game. Crashes on launch again and again until you reinstall the ubisoft game launcher (and even then good luck with it! Fixing it seems totally random) And then IF you do get it started you cant use a gamepad with it. Total waste of time and money that did nothing but make me angry, ubisoft are the worst", "hours": 8.5, "user_id": "76561198054784601", "username": "Trouble On Triton", "products": 26, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 190, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-26", "text": "Assassin's Creed Brotherhood is by far my absolute favorite game in the Assassin's Creed series. From a story standpoint, the game absolutely delivers. The story of Ezio and his revival of the Assassin order is well crafted and well executed, and any hardcore fan of the Assassin's Creed series will appreciate it. Now, from a gameplay standpoint, Brotherhood does an amazing job as well. The returning old techniques are as solid as ever, and Brotherhood's host of new mechanics and items integrate with the already amzing title flawlessly. Whether you are a casual gamer or a hardcore fan of the series, Brotherhood absolutely delivers, and is well worth the $20 price tag. All in all, I would rate Assassin's Creed Brotherhooda 9/10.", "hours": 4.5, "user_id": "76561198121639176", "username": "Reclaimer", "products": 81, "early_access": false}
