{"product_id": "48190", "page": 193, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-01", "text": "Yes, I would reccomend you DO play this game. I love the gameplay, graphics, animation (major advantage for the game), and a lot more. Assassin's Creed: Brotherhood has its evens and odds (like Uplay), but the odds can be reasoned with. I like most of the game, but what bugs kme the most is that when you want to play it, you MUST go through Uplay: meaning that you MUST have or create a(n) account in order to play the game you just (bought and) want to play. But other than Uplay, I would reccomend this game, it goes for the win, so you should buy it! And if you're feeling nastolgic, then you might want to play this.", "hours": 3.9, "username": "Alex Mason", "products": 49, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 193, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-28", "text": "'Assassin's Creed Brotherhood' improves on its predecessor, 'Assassin's Creed II' in almost every way. The graphics are more detailed and combat systems are even more finely tuned. The commerce system is a bit distracting at first, but proves invaluable if you wish to rebuild Rome as a side mission. Give the game some time to gain its momentum because it gets more fun once you start recruiting people to join your brotherhood.", "hours": 34.7, "username": "CharlieLima79", "products": 169, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 193, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-28", "text": "The games ran well on an intel dual core, but on an amd quad core it is completely unplayabe. Terrible optimization isn't going to push me to upgrade for one over hyped game series.", "hours": 7.5, "username": "AnimAspect", "products": 142, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 194, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-28", "text": "Great game. You start the game up and it keeps you on it for ages, you just can't stop. Totally recommending this to anybody whos looking to play a single-player game with a good story-line.", "hours": 15.6, "user_id": "76561198119249767", "username": "El Patr\u00f3n", "products": 114, "early_access": false}
