{"product_id": "48190", "page": 196, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-17", "text": "Off all the games in this series this one is my favorite.  The open world combined with the beautiful architecture of Rome makes for hours of exploration.  The plot is great and has some fun twists which make playing it over and over easy to do.  Like in most game series it is best to play the games in order but if you really don't want to get them all and just want to try one I would recommend starting with this one.  You will not be sorry.", "hours": 106.7, "user_id": "76561198022855721", "username": "jaddis777", "products": 99, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 197, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-16", "text": "Good way to continue from where AC2 has ended. If you want to play a good Assassin's Creed game, here's more of it where AC2 left off. Combat is still lawful, and I was in no hurry trying to get the best armour of the game. I finished the story mode without it.\nI haven't really played the multiplayer. I'm not the one to judge it. I tried the tutorial & it required a re-bind to the controller, but I haven't really done much in that.\nI recomend it for the story mode.\nUpdate after 102 hours of playing: If you're a fan of the series & you have a SSD, go on and have a go, but if you don't you can't 100% the singleplayer. Ubisoft back in 2010 decided to make galloping a SSD only feature in freeroam mode. My second playthrough was not as enjoyable as the first. Also to note some the Da-Vinci machines are awkward to control and completing the no hit requirement in the memory just makes it infuriating.", "hours": 153.6, "user_id": "76561198073927253", "username": "von Sanneck", "products": 174, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 197, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-14", "text": "Best game but not best to none than AC 2,it has Multiplayer though,which actually integrated nicel with the aspect of the game which was stealth,and Multiplayer is fresh as ever.", "hours": 46.3, "username": "JustKoAix", "products": 57, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 197, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-13", "text": "Solid game, huge improvement over the other two on the free run system, decent story.", "hours": 22.6, "username": "White", "products": 279, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 197, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-12", "text": "Assassin's Creed Brotherhood is an excellent continuization of the Assassin's Creed series. It brings a smoother game play and action while not sacfrificing on story. Also, commanding your Assassin brothers to kill your targets, when possible, is MOST enjoyable.", "hours": 53.3, "user_id": "76561198034029365", "username": "indestructable", "products": 79, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 197, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-12", "text": "This game has the best of AC II with several cool additions, and better graphics too.\nIn my opinion, it's the best of the Ezio's Assassin's Creed's game!", "hours": 67.9, "username": "Milton", "products": 92, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 197, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-12", "text": "This is going to be a weird review...\nOk first the game is a great game. I have played it on console and love it.\nthe problem is that the whole uplay thing screws up the game so bad u litterally cannot play it. I cant even open the game to play. It just crashes at the uplay thing which annoys the heck out of me. Until its fixed, I am going to feel like I just wasted 20$....\nHowever the game is a great game. Best in the series next to AC4.", "hours": 2.7, "user_id": "76561198084626242", "username": "TheFratagonia", "products": 39, "early_access": false}
