{"product_id": "48190", "page": 199, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-29", "text": "The third game of the franchise was the most enjoyable for me. Improved mechanics over the previous games, much less repetitive and an intriguing story as well!", "hours": 29.5, "user_id": "76561198040221705", "username": "bumph18", "products": 464, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 199, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-29", "text": "a game that will continue the previous one from the moment you left off will start out as a blast first 3 secuences were a whole lot of fun i cant say that there is anything bad about the game until that point but ofcourse since this is a negetave comment i will say them:\n1. a game with so little story (the story is good but it feels too short) that ubisoft just sqeezed in so many side challanges i spent over half my game time on these side challanges that the story was not fun.\n2. the game contains a DLC \"The Da Vinchi Disapearnce\" which for some reason feels longer than the main game and has a more solid story\n3. assassins - nice touch but overuse of the same npc face (i went to reqruit my last assassin and 4 of the first faces i saw were exactually the same\nSPOILER\n4. the game is too easy going at first but on the last misson it jumps you 9 years forward with no explanation of to how the bad guy is leader of a different army unless you read it in TAB\nmaybe i didnt play it right though....", "hours": 225.9, "username": "Longshot", "products": 129, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 199, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-27", "text": "Do you love Assassin's Creeed? You'll probably love this.\nDo you want to try out Assassin's Creed? I recommend you try Assassin's Creed 1, and 2 before this. Without the first (and especially 2nd), games under your belt, this story will make no sense, you won't care about the characters, and you probably won't enjoy this at all.\nThis is a filler sequel.\nThe gameplay is extremely similar to Assasin's Creed 2. It is hard for me to identify too many new elements. I don't know if any of the weapons were actually new, of if the ammo for them was just more plentiful, but I definitely used the gun, poison darts, and crossbow a lot in this game. I also found myself playing a lot less stealthily, possibly because the crossbow was so much fun to use, and I could loot ammo from any dead body.\nThe one new element is that towards the midgame, you start an Assassin's Guild, sending assasins out on missions throughout Europe. They reward you with money, and some rare \"shop quests\" (i.e - crafting) items. You can also summon them during any battle and they will fight well. It almost feels like cheating compared to previous games, but it is kind of fun to say, \"screw this stealth crap, everyone dies now.\"", "hours": 45.8, "username": "Krabs", "products": 290, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 199, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-27", "text": "Multiplayer is fun, Campaign is fun. everything about this game is fun. I reccomend this to fans of ezio and assasins creed!!!", "hours": 28.2, "username": "le furry lamb girl", "products": 69, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 200, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-21", "text": "This game was even better than AC2. The gun controls have improved, it also has more weapons along with better combat mechanics. Amazing start to the game and amazing ending along with an overall great story which continues almost right after 2 ends for Ezio.", "hours": 16.8, "username": "Calbars1995", "products": 106, "early_access": false}
