{"product_id": "48190", "page": 203, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-04", "text": "One of my favourite Assassin's Creed parts , I must say I enjoyed every second playing it , and I recommend it to everyone , I don't think there's a person who would hate this game, sure it has a few bugs and glitches but the game is good , the grahpics are amazing aswell !", "hours": 73.5, "user_id": "76561198058892418", "username": "WAR", "products": 34, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 203, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-04", "text": "Very much an iteration on Assassin's Creed II, but not necessarily in a bad way. The combat and movement of Ezio feels more fluid and refined, and so does everything else in this sequel.\nRome is a fantastic location with tons of unique scenery and history. The missions are varied and fun and the game is about the right length. A bit shorter than Assassin's Creed 2 which was a bit too long in my opinion.\nMake sure you activate the free Leonardo Da'Vinci expansion in UPlay, it contains a couple of great missions.\nThe biggest difference from the last game is that you're not on your own as much anymore. You get to recruit and train followers that can earn you money and aid you in combat.\nLastly it's great to see proper controller bindings now, bindings that actually makes sense. Assassin's Creed II controller binds were just all over the place but now it works like it should.\nOverall a great, refined game!", "hours": 29.4, "user_id": "76561198018960615", "username": "Spaceship", "products": 85, "early_access": false}
