{"product_id": "48190", "page": 207, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-23", "text": "Amazing game ! a bit shorter than the one before, but worth every minute. It has an ending that makes you must purchase the next one, the plot on Ezio is just the thing that makes AC series amazing !", "hours": 19.1, "username": "SaiyanGod", "products": 393, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 207, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-23", "text": "The jumping puzzles were more obnoxious than what was in AC2, but the story was all around stronger to me, in that I actually understood who I was fighting and why, which is more than I could say about AC2. All in all, a good game for me. I enjoyed the city-rebuilding aspects and the crit-path chain isn't obnoxiously long like it felt in AC2. I did skip some of the side content, like the tomb explorations, since I hated those in AC2 and they're not critical anyway. Storywise, it ends on a definite cliffhanger, so there's definitely an impetus to head into AC: Revelations right afterward.", "hours": 23.0, "user_id": "76561197970549991", "username": "RedFox", "products": 461, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 207, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-22", "text": "One of the better games of the series, Brotherhood continues with Ezio Auditore and adds in several fantastic elements to gameplay. One the whole, the game is smoother for low end computers than ACII. The character interaction is fantastic, and the addition of killstreaks completes the improved combat, allowing it to flow more smoothly.  The addition of the Borgia towers, as well as the improved economy, add a whole new level of detail to the game and a second alternate goal, the rebirth of Rome's economy. Many of the additions are continued in Revelations, although the combat is not as fine tuned. Overall, Brotherhood is a wonderful game and a must play for anyone interested in the series. But play ACII first. Seriously.", "hours": 91.7, "user_id": "76561198054472491", "username": "Frogs On The Brain", "products": 155, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 207, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-22", "text": "Major fun in a sprawling city, builds on the success of its predecessors and does most things pretty well, still the best Assassin's Creed game in my eyes, although Black Flag may change that!", "hours": 46.1, "username": "Piqasso93", "early_access": false}
