{"product_id": "48190", "page": 209, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-10", "text": "While the changes are not as drastic as the ones from the first Assassin's Creed to the second,\nBrotherhood goes a nice way to improve upon the already extremely solid formula cemented by its predecessor.\nCombat is made quicker and flashier through the ability to use both meele and long-range weapons together and the introduction of a chain-kill mechanic. The Assassin recruits create a simple, yet surprisingly engaging past time that pays off big in the long run and for those who enjoyed renovating Ezio's villa in the last game, there is now the entirity of Rome to do as you please with. Even with all this, there is no doubt that this does feel like \"Assassin's Creed 2: 2\", but when the changes that are there build so well upon the last game all the same, one can't really complain.", "hours": 25.2, "username": "ANDY", "products": 225, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 209, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-09", "text": "For anyone thinking of playing Assassins Creed, but do not want to feel that they missed a chunk of plot I recommend playing this game. It is the best Assassins Creed game for the Mac on Steam. I recommend playing this after Assassins Creed III due to the fact that 3 has the tutorial to many of the game mechanics used in Brotherhood. Overall, it is an awesome game and you should not hesitate to play it if you are thinking of playing Assassins Creed.", "hours": 29.0, "user_id": "76561198063195414", "username": "Mo", "products": 111, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
