{"product_id": "48190", "page": 215, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-27", "text": "This game fell behind it's predecessor, ACII. Sometimes the game mechanics get in your way, and doing something as simple as climbing a wall can be a \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665.\n7/10", "hours": 19.1, "user_id": "76561197999507602", "username": "|\u00a2\u043a| d0gecoins", "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 216, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-26", "text": "Rome is awesome.\nIn AC: Brotherhood, Ezio travels to Rome to confront the younger Cesare Borgia for being an evil twit. The plot revolves around the Assassin brotherhood, and gaining ground in society. That was my favorite aspect of the game, the recruiting and training of the assassins.\nThe actual plot involves Cesare Borgia, the son of the Rodrigo Borgia, or Pope Alexander VI. Cesare is a psychopath in the truest standards. He's relentless and lusts for blood.\nAs you can imagine, the gameplay is much like the previous game, but with some fixes to the parkour. Also, the graphics look a little bit better. Not much else changed in technical terms though.\nIt's a great game regardless, and the vast openness of Rome was epic, yet a little boring in the area south of the Coliseum.\n9.2/10", "hours": 43.2, "user_id": "76561198009430218", "username": "JacoRay", "products": 774, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 216, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-26", "text": "Great continuation to AC2. Not quite as good as the previous game, but still a solid 9/10. Has the positives of AC2 with some new things, as well as multiplayer (which is pretty good but close to being dead)", "hours": 15.6, "username": "rush b blyat", "products": 153, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 216, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-24", "text": "Assassin's Creed Brotherhood Review\n------------------------------------------------------\nStory- 10\nGameplay- 10\nGraphics - 10\nNote- Best Game & Series Ever.\nWorth buying - Yes.", "hours": 12.5, "username": "Goku", "products": 307, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 216, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-22", "text": "The best of the saga. One of the best game ever. I've played twice because it's so good.\nTo fully enjoy this game, you need to play to all the preceding ones.", "hours": 92.1, "user_id": "76561198001584035", "username": "BobMammoth", "products": 314, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 216, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-15", "text": "Best AC yet.", "hours": 23.3, "username": "Spicer Jones\u2122", "products": 365, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 216, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-11", "text": "Definitely my favorite Assassin's Creed game.  It has a great story and the setting is just terrific.  My favorite part of all the Assassin's Creed games is the free-running puzzles, and this game had a ton of them!  Combat was also improved, allowing you to chain executes, so that you don't need to wait to counterattack, making a really smooth and flowing gameplay.  My only real critique for this game is that the crossbow makes some parts of the game too easy.  A ranged silent execute is just really overpowered.  However, even though the crossbow may make some missions speed by, this game still offers many hours of fun, so buy it and play it.", "hours": 53.7, "username": "[\u2665] OMFGeoff", "products": 505, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 216, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-10", "text": "It is a really good game.. I just don't like the main charactor that much..\nStill if you dont have any assassin creed games allready I reacon grab it next time its on sale for 75% off..\nOf course if   Assassin\u2019s Creed 3 or 4 is the same price or just a little bit more you might be better grabbing that..   All the Assassin\u2019s Creed games are pretty much the same really just new items.. But everyone should have at least 1 in their libary", "hours": 58.9, "user_id": "76561197965262160", "username": "deathrow_nzl", "products": 431, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 216, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-06", "text": "Still the best AC game to date, highly recommend it.", "hours": 28.2, "username": "Catoose", "products": 233, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 216, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-04", "text": "An RPG disguised as an open world game. For some reason, I thought the AC games would suck when I first played them, but the story is really good, of epic proportions like RPGs. It might not have stats, but it does have dang near every other thing RPGs have, especially RPG-lite type games like Dark Souls. You change your fighting style based on weapons and the weapons have stats like Action-RPGs like Torchlight/Diablo. It \"lacks\" moral choices, but that only makes it a bit more like a JRPG like Final Fantasy than it does a Western moral RPG.", "hours": 27.6, "username": "Krypto", "products": 479, "early_access": false}
