{"product_id": "48190", "page": 218, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-07-18", "text": "up a wall\nwhere this control scheme\ndriveth me\n---\nSo I skipped the first one and played II, Brotherhood, and Revelations back-to-back. I'd have to agree with the consensus that this is the Ezio game you want to play if you're new to Assassin's Creed.\nStill, what blows my mind isn't the silly animus framing narrative--but that to run in this game, you have to push the left analog stick while holding a trigger and a face button. The genius who came up with this control scheme must wear the label ironically.", "hours": 32.9, "username": "ReticentEvil", "products": 330, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 218, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-07-16", "text": "The 2nd best in a great series. If you haven't already, pick up the whole series. It's worth it.", "hours": 52.4, "username": "WhyySoup", "products": 207, "early_access": false}
