{"product_id": "48190", "page": 219, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-06-14", "text": "ACII ended fine, but I suppose the series had to go on.  Its a great game.  The camera angles seem to have gotten a slight fix, they still go all wonky when you don't want them to, but not as common as they did before.  Two questions linger in my mind though.  How were players supposed to figure out some of these button combos for required puzzles?  Also, how did Ezio age so many years in the couple weeks that pass between ACII and this game?", "hours": 54.2, "user_id": "76561198015664912", "username": "Silent Sniper", "products": 87, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 219, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-06-12", "text": "Average sequel to II but a great game, almost everything is the same now, multiplayer aspect is fun but should not be looked at as the main feature of the game, the continuation of the desmond-ezio storyline is the main thing to look for here. Still worth it, but it's not called 3 for a reason.", "hours": 21.7, "username": "Lynk", "products": 1203, "early_access": false}
