{"product_id": "48190", "page": 220, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-04-23", "text": "If you like the AC series then by all means play AssBro!  It does tend to get long in the tooth though if you try to 100% too many things.  It's like AC2 + some new things to add some diversions.  But Ezio still likes to Randomly tackle people when I'm running through streets, or better yet, randomly assassinate a random peasant instead of that guard that I was fighting!  EZIO!!!", "hours": 69.7, "username": "Banzai5150", "products": 463, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 220, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-04-20", "text": "Probably the best installment of the Assassin's Creed series. What really attracted me was that the game was set in renaissance Rome. Any history geek would salivate at the thought!", "hours": 130.6, "username": "Doraemond", "products": 358, "early_access": false}
