{"product_id": "48190", "page": 228, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-16", "text": "8.5/10 - A backstabbing adventure\nThe parkouring in this adventure is smooth yet can be a little inacurate once in a while. It is cool how you can combo the parkour moves and climb around wooden beams like stairs. There is a little bit of upgrades with the knifes and weapons. The story is good and engaging. The missions vary quite a bit with some sub-missions that are the same. The enviroments are pretty different.", "hours": 5.1, "username": "Joey Salads", "products": 596, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 228, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-14", "text": "Brotherhood adds some new gameplay elements to the base ACII format that adds some new variety to the AC format. Some additions make up for some of the more impercise moments when free-running, especially when you accidentally leap from a very tall structure. Addition of you very own brotherhood to control adds some fun elements that can help you when you are trying to remain undetected but need to do some killing, but the system is shallow, as sending your assassins out on missions is less favorable than keeping them around to help you in combat.\nStory progresses right from the end of ACII, but really doesn't add much to the overall plot, but inside and outside of the animus. In all, it felt more like an extended expansion than it did a new title, and might have been better as such, in a trimmed down version.\nIf you like ACII, than you probably won't be disapointed in Brotherhood. It can drag on at moments, but it comes with another 15-19 hours of gameplay in the Assassin's Creed world.", "hours": 19.7, "username": "Bloodstorm", "products": 522, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 228, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-13", "text": "Liked AC2? Good, because that game is \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing awesome. This.. Well... It's AC2 with a little bit more stuff, so that means it's good.", "hours": 38.6, "username": "Ensi", "products": 136, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 228, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-11", "text": "Great game and plenty of side stuff to do. Unlike the other games you don't travel in this. You stay in Rome pretty much the whole game. But staying in one spot kind of makes you feel more like you are a part of the world. The game is a lot of fun and I reccomend it.", "hours": 30.3, "username": "Shayneros", "products": 91, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 228, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-09", "text": "What the \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 did you just \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing say about me, you little \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665? I'll have you know I graduated top of my class in the Navy Seals, and I've been involved in numerous secret raids on Al-Quaeda, and I have over 300 confirmed kills. I am trained in gorilla warfare and I'm the top sniper in the entire US armed forces. You are nothing to me but just another target. I will wipe you the \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 out with precision the likes of which has never been seen before on this Earth, mark my \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing words. You think you can get away with saying that\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665to me over the Internet? Think again, \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665er. As we speak I am contacting my secret network of spies across the USA and your IP is being traced right now so you better prepare for the storm, maggot. The storm that wipes out the pathetic little thing you call your life. You're \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing dead, kid. I can be anywhere, anytime, and I can kill you in over seven hundred ways, and that's just with my bare hands. Not only am I extensively trained in unarmed combat, but I have access to the entire arsenal of the United States Marine Corps and I will use it to its full extent to wipe your miserable\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665off the face of the continent, you little\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 If only you could have known what unholy retribution your little \"clever\" comment was about to bring down upon you, maybe you would have held your \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing tongue. But you couldn't, you didn't, and now you're paying the price, you goddamn idiot. I will\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665fury all over you and you will drown in it. You're \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing dead, kiddo.", "hours": 37.9, "username": "Sleepy Cactus", "products": 133, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 228, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-08", "text": "Pretty awesome game. Enjoy being able to call fellow assasins. Not quite as good as Assassin's Creed II though, but still awesome ;D", "hours": 19.9, "username": "Mr.Niceguy", "products": 137, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 229, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-08", "text": "Wonderful game. Beautiful graphics (with improved faces) and long lasting, open world gameplay. The game has some great new additions as well, in comparison to ACII. Running around also feels more natural this time.\nI continued playing this even after I finished it, and I don't do that very often.\nThe multiplayer is great as well, very tense. Loved it.\n[Rating: 91/100]", "hours": 24.7, "username": "mark | dj.", "products": 3577, "early_access": false}
