{"product_id": "48190", "page": 230, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-23", "text": "5 dollars...!!!", "hours": 34.6, "user_id": "76561197984737819", "username": "No_SuRReNDeR", "products": 179, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 230, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-23", "text": "It's a pretty good game. Story was amazing as usual, but gameplay remained unaltered. Graphics were a step down from ACII (even though this came out a year later). There were a few problems, and it felt like a poor console port. The entire game lasted one-third of the time that ACII did, which was a little bit of a surprise. Also, the whole Assassin's Guild system was pretty easy to master; however, recruiting new people felt repetitive. There were a lot a structures that were clipping through each other, but most of the Assassin's Creed games have had lots of errors like this (flying lamps, lots of clipping, etc).\nOverall, it was a nice edition to the franchise; but they could have done better.", "hours": 11.7, "username": "MacroPower", "products": 1351, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 231, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-11", "text": "Same game as Assassin's Creed 2. Slightly streamlined, but lots more sandbox stuff if you really want to get into it. That content is entirely skippable, luckily.\nUbisoft \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ed up the UI controls in this one, however, by separating them from the character controls. So annoying now to switch back and forth on the keyboard just to buy a goddamn potion. Too bad the humour in the game dies after the first fifteen minutes, too. I liked Ezio getting made fun of.\nIf you liked 2, play Brotherhood. Just be prepared for the longest, worst credit roll in history.", "hours": 32.5, "username": "Daassie", "products": 166, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 231, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-07", "text": "Don't write this off because it seems like Assassin's Creed 2.5 - it's actually the best in the series to date.", "hours": 43.2, "username": "Trevor", "products": 448, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 231, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-06", "text": "Really Nice Game Good Story Line", "hours": 9.2, "username": "[TS3H-ML]King2203\u2122", "products": 196, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 231, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-10-03", "text": "The Assassin's Creed series just keeps getting better and better. The first game was a solid start, but the missions got repetitive after a while. AC II blew me away with the number of things they added; a compelling plot and characters that felt authentic, interesting platforming sequences, and a real sense of humor!\nI just finished the story campaign of Assassin's Creed Brotherhood, and I can't decide whether I liked it better than Assassin's Creed II or not.\nGraphically Brotherhood is obviously better, but it is not as big a difference as the change from AC to AC II. Also, 3D gaming is really useful while freerunning around Renaissance Italy because depth perception helps me to know whether I can make a jump or not.\nI think I preferred the story of AC II because it was an epic narrative of Ezio's journey over several decades to train and grow from a rather self-centered lady-killer young adult to a mature assassin (still a lady-killer). AC Brotherhood was much more limited in scope, as it takes place over the course of a few years in the city of Rome. Don't get me wrong, it was epic, but I liked the tangible progression that Ezio went through in AC II.\nHowever, I definitely preferred the gameplay of Brotherhood. They improved on a few of the things that had been iffy in the previous games (like horses!) and they added some really great things as well. The big one of course is recruiting assassins to help you out. I felt like a total badass whenever I walked by a group of guards, raised my hand and whistled, and a moment later they were dead. I also became rather attached to the recruits, and it made me very proud when they gained enough experience to become full-fledged assassins. Losing recruits didn't have quite as big an emotional impact as losing people in The Walking Dead did, but when I accidentally killed one it came pretty close.\nThe endings of these games keep getting more and more mind-blowing; I have heard that Revelations raises the bar once again, and I can't wait to get there. One thing that definitely gave me the chills was the date that the finale takes place on. Ubisoft has intentionally been converging all events on December 21, 2012 and the final scenes of Brotherhood take place 72 days before that.\nSo if you were to ask me which Assassin's Creed games you should play, I would say all of them. If you are short on time/money skipping the first one is excusable. AC II, Brotherhood, and Revelations make a nice little trilogy, so don't start after AC II.", "hours": 36.1, "username": "Wolf Revo", "products": 439, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 231, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-10-03", "text": "23 hours or so long, I did lots of sidequest things.\nGame runs fine and looks prettier than AC2.  Controls are a bit righter, but there are a lot less rooftops to run around in and a lot more open fields.\nCompared to AC2, this game streamlines the combat without improving it at all.  Bosses are as dissapointing as they ever were, but now there are less of them.  There is not much innovation in mechanics or content, but zones are much more well designed and fleshed out.  Storyline is fine, but there's a lot of pointless sidequest and a few plot points just left unadressed.  There's a 'trade good' and shop quest system that is not at all developed or fun.  There's a few new tools for the player to use but not necessarily in interesting ways.\nOverall the game is basically AC2 with more spitshine but, as will come with the curse of sequels, they dont do anything unsafe with it.", "hours": 23.8, "username": "I'm Not Sue", "products": 603, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 231, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-28", "text": "If you liked AC2, you will definitely enjoy the continuation of the story in AssBro.\nFocused on one big area with only a few side quests away from Rome, but with new weapons and a paradise for achievement hunters.\nRemember to get the Deluxe version if you want the extra SP missions and MP items, as you can't buy them if you only have the regular edition!", "hours": 68.7, "username": "Fart of Presto", "products": 4802, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 231, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-26", "text": "Assassin's Creed Brotherhood is a great game. I liked the story and enjoyed exploring Rom. I remember that I often lost track of time while playing, wanted to finish just this one quest and ended up spending another hour. Some of the quests are very challenging and others are very easy, but almost all of them are fun. There were a few quests I needed more time to figure out how to solve them.\nI also tried the Multiplayer Part, but had a similar problem like I had with Splinter Cell. Other than with Splinter Cell I at least found a friend online, but couldn't make it work. I do play a lot of other Multiplayer games and had only problems with Ubisoft games so far. I know that I am not the only one, found many posts in forums and on blogs about that subject and think Ubisoft needs to make it easier for players to enjoy the Multiplayer portion of their games.\nBut I still can recommend this game, because the single player is fun and will keep you occupied for some time.", "hours": 10.8, "username": "Simok33", "products": 75, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 231, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-25", "text": "Awesome as hell. Arguably the best in the series.", "hours": 56.2, "username": "shovelface", "products": 306, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 231, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-09-08", "text": "Another year, another turgid crapfest from the AssCreed series. Unskippable cutscenes (really, we're still doing these in 2010?), sticky cameras, lousy storytelling, etc. To be fair, though, this isn't QUITE the same sweaty nutsack that AssCreed II was; the combat is vaguely improved, and the scenery looks as nice as ever. Eventually, Ubisoft might make a worthwhile entry in the AssCreed series that's actually worth the 10 bucks I pay for them during Steam sales, but I doubt it. In the meantime, I'll keep slogging through the pigshit that the AssCreed series leaves in its wake, all the while posting whiny non-recommendations on Steam.", "hours": 35.5, "username": "Ham", "products": 304, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 231, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-08", "text": "Very fun and addicting :D", "hours": 35.8, "username": "Strawhatz", "products": 97, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 232, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-05", "text": "After five years on the east coast, Carl Johnson returns to the city of Los Santos, San Andreas to find numerous fellow gang-members dead and enemy gangs having dominance of the city. Carl must take over the city and get his old gang back on top before the city destroys itself", "hours": 46.6, "username": "Malcolm XCOM", "products": 516, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 232, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-01", "text": "Fantastic 3rd game in the series filled with rich 15th century history (loved the twised and sordid history of the Borgias), great characters (more Ezio is a good thing), combat and gameplay. One of the best storylines in a game series to date. The downsides are that the Assassin's Brotherhood gameplay addition is more of a gimmick than anything else which is a damn shame as it could have been awesome to train up your fellow assassins by being able to engage with them more directly instead of just sending them on pre-scripted text based missions. Also, being able to call them to help you in a fight is cool and all but can be used to easily cheese your way through the tougher encounters in the game.\n8.5-9/10", "hours": 57.5, "username": "Valassi", "products": 211, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 232, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-01", "text": "The Good :\n+ Best Looking game than other AC games\n+ Biggest Game in AC series\n+ Varied Missions\n+ Da Vinci's Disappearance is awesome\n+ Brother hood is awesome\n+ Beautiful Killstreaks\nThe Bad :\n- Confused ending\n- Sometime's character does'nt listen to our commands\n- No gallop button for horses\n- Average and frustrating Multi-player", "hours": 13.6, "username": "Watch_Doge", "products": 143, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 232, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-27", "text": "It was exactly what I expected it to be: a continuation of the second one. Again, fantastic story, amazing music, good graphics, it keeps the same style of the second one. The gameplay is pretty much exactly the same. The real kicker for this one is the actual brotherhood system; being able to pick and choose your allies and stuff, it's really neat and engaging. Also this game had a totally kickass ending. All in all, 9.5/10. On to Revalations! :D", "hours": 10.6, "username": "-=TheDoctor=-", "products": 494, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 232, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-26", "text": "I love Assassin's Creed, and this is one of the best in the series. I think Assassin's Creed Revelations is the best out of all the games so far though. But this is definately a great play! This series is just amazing, also very pretty. It is just breath taking. This game and the Assassin's Creed series is Highly recommended.", "hours": 16.3, "username": "Imaginesque", "products": 37, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 232, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-24", "text": "good game, good story and good world with lots to do", "hours": 30.9, "username": "Friedrich Engels", "products": 136, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 232, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-21", "text": "Continues straight from where AC II left off, Brotherhood has even more varied missions mainly in Rome. Even though there are a lot of simultaneous missions and lots of areas open at the same time, which might cause a headache to some, it also gives the opportunity to choose what you want to do instead of following the plot all the time. Also features tradable items and maps that help you find feathers and flags.", "hours": 70.3, "username": "salriella", "products": 195, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 232, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-19", "text": "Love this game and evolution of Ezio. Pretty much the same as the other newer games.", "hours": 15.0, "username": "BLATSPLAT", "products": 917, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 232, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-17", "text": "Epic fight moves, better graphics and a multiplayer !!! The multiplayer is simply the best. I do recommend this game for everyone ! (P.S.: The ending ot the story shocked me. :s)", "hours": 19.4, "username": "\u272a wild", "products": 140, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 232, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-15", "text": "Expands upon the already great Assassin's Creed 2, new items, characters and multiplayer make this a must-own", "hours": 18.1, "username": "Trevor the Burninator", "products": 107, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 233, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-12", "text": "What can I say!? The Assassin's Creed series deserves the attention of EVERY gamer!", "hours": 31.1, "username": "Tabulation", "products": 467, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 233, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-06", "text": "Assassin's Creed: Brotherhood suffers from a so-called 'intermediate chapter syndrome'. It's just as good as Assassin's Creed II with improvements in some areas. What it lacks though is surprise. Brotherhood continues the story of Ezio, becoming the second chapter in a sub-trilogy within Assassin's Creed tetralogy. As a result, few new characters are introduced, and the story progresses at a slow and steady pace. It's not any less interesting than in previous games, and its ending, again, is cool and unexpected, but while the second game was a major step forward compared to the first one, Brotherhood feels more like an expansion pack for the second game.\nIt introduces multiplayer which is surprisingly fun for something that shouldn't have existed in the first place. It has integration with Assassin's Creed: Project Legacy, a Facebook game that sheds some light on the series' mysteries.\nThat being said, AC: Brotherhood is still a must-play for everyone who enjoyed the first two games.", "hours": 7.2, "username": "Toff", "products": 3154, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 233, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-04", "text": "This is my favorite part of the Ezio Auditore de Firenze triology of Games (II, Brotherhood, and Revelations).  AC2 was the longest of the three and the most justifiable for the price but Brotherhood's ability to better integrate Claudia (Ezio's Sister), horses, and the Poison weaponry makes Brotherhood somehow my favorite.  Rome is a far larger town than anything from AC2, and the updates to the HUD and controls are much needed from AC2.\nShort Version: Get AC2 for the Story, Brotherhood for the Gameplay, and Revelations for the history of the Assassin Order.", "hours": 36.6, "username": "L \u03a8 Kongroo", "products": 350, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 233, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-31", "text": "BEST ASSASSINS CREED GAME SO FAR CANT WAIT FOR AC3", "hours": 18.9, "username": "SPONGE_4k", "products": 9, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 233, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-30", "text": "its fun as heck", "hours": 22.2, "username": "dannyboy", "products": 72, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 233, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-25", "text": "This game REALLY took a *leap of faith* in giving us a whole new story and gameplay to associate Desmond Miles and Ezio Auditore with. (Leap of faith-- yeah, I've been waiting to use that one.) Honestly, though, it isn't the story that takes frontrunner here, as it seems that with each entry the story gets more and more confusing (not that that is necessarily a bad thing in this case), but the thrills that come with being able to call forth allies on a moments notice to help you take out your enemies. Leveling up your Brotherhood and becoming more engrossed in the brilliant side tasks gives players more reason to come back than any other entry in the AC series, and that is saying a lot. Of course, however, those who would try to play this without playing at least AC2 will be making a gross mistake. Fair warning to any who haven't touched upon this fantastic series.", "hours": 63.7, "username": "Silshryk", "products": 179, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 233, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-22", "text": "I think of it as \"Assassin's Creed Auto.\" You get to run around Rome being a total\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 and having fun.", "hours": 44.8, "username": "One Man Riot", "products": 284, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 233, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-22", "text": "1 word - Awesome.\nGreat graphics, long and cool storyline.\nBut multiplayer could be better.", "hours": 22.5, "username": "cara made me do it", "products": 81, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 233, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-21", "text": "Oh man is this game awesome. Take the aciton and setting that have made Assassin's Creed unavoidable and great, and then add the best storyline and general content of the whole series and I'd say it's worth the $50.", "hours": 37.3, "username": "MagikalKraker", "products": 169, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 233, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-21", "text": "Perfect! :)", "hours": 32.0, "username": "Alex Fox", "products": 140, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 234, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-20", "text": "25 horas y contando. Creo que es un buen juego. Jejejeje.", "hours": 38.7, "user_id": "76561198002789672", "username": "Albinon05", "products": 7501, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 234, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-20", "text": "Better than AC2, the mission synchronization challenges make stealth and speed actually a thing in this addition to the franchise. Totally worth it if it's on sale.", "hours": 9.6, "username": "Smooth Billy N-Style", "products": 653, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 234, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-19", "text": "Didn't buy this originally because I thought it would play like a DLC money grab but I couldn't have been any more wrong. Sure it's still the same game I know and love but there's a good 20 hours plus of single player content set in Rome and they've introduced the most original multiplayer mode there has been for decades based around blending in with the AI civilians. They've also added challenges and some hard time trial stages which are very much welcome. Ended up getting 100% as usual too because I'm so fond of the free running and climbing.", "hours": 35.2, "username": "Rivent", "products": 804, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 234, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-19", "text": "Muito massa principalmente o MultiPlayer xD", "hours": 19.9, "username": "DarthNapa", "products": 194, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 234, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-19", "text": "Best game ever!", "hours": 26.5, "user_id": "76561198022103376", "username": "LORD", "products": 47, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 234, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-18", "text": "Umm...You are an assassin. You can call down your assassin buddies to kill people for you. Umm...stop reading this and buy it, now.\nBut yeah, awesome game, great story + you're a complete badass. 10/10", "hours": 25.5, "username": "Vbdude", "products": 119, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 234, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-17", "text": "Awesome gameplay with very impressive visuals. The story is also very compelling.", "user_id": "76561198014114782", "username": "JohnyTea", "products": 94, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 234, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-16", "text": "Having only played a chunk of the first Assassin's Creed and a few hours of AC2, AssBro is like some sort of beautiful work of art. From what I hear Revalations is like this but less impressive, so If you choose to play an Assassin's Creed, make it this one.", "hours": 39.2, "username": "Wudz", "products": 212, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 234, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-16", "text": "While the story is perhaps a bit weaker than AC2, there are some improvements. Gameplay is about the same, though there are more things to collect and unlock. Renovating the city adds a bit to the game, and the music is as good as the first. Overall a good buy.", "hours": 56.4, "username": "Resplendent", "products": 285, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 234, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-16", "text": "Another great entry in the Assassin's Creed Franchise. The story was cool, the scenery was great, and the setting was awesome(its Rome). This game brought one of the biggest changes to the Assassin's Creed games, htis change is the Multiplayer. Which has a really cool concept. The only bad thing about the multiplayer is that people rarely play it (ive only tried to play online once, so it may have been just that one time.) I would highly reccommend this game, it is on par with the first game. And far better than Revelations(which isnt a bad game, its just really short... like i beat it in 8 hours including sidequests, and someone i know beat it in 4 hours while just doing the story.)\n9/10", "hours": 6.6, "username": "Kealmcking", "products": 610, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 235, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-16", "text": "What a game !", "hours": 33.0, "user_id": "76561198027157334", "username": "AlpoTheWhite", "products": 35, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 235, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-16", "text": "I have played nearly all of AC games released till now (July 2017), but AC Brotherhood is a game that i will come back to from time to time just to ejoy Ezio and the world around him. New AC games have allot of inovation, but they just miss that something that Brotherhood had.", "hours": 9.4, "username": "Mr.Jaffa-Cake", "products": 216, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 235, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-15", "text": "Assassin's Creed: Brotherhood is a good game, no arguments, you can't debate it, AC:B is a good game.\nIt would be a great game, if you didn't feel like you were being milked while playing it.\nGood gameplay, good story, good pacing, that is hooked onto the AC formula seen in the first and second games.\nAnd that's it.\nYou know that Ubisoft is going to milk you for every penny, making you pay full price for the work that is essentially DLC extra's and fancy modding padding extra layers onto bloated thing they have already.\nThis is more blatant with the new \"innovative\" feature of Assassin's Recruits that really is a tack-on, and the game would survive fine without it.\nBut if you've already played the first two Assassin's Creed games, you'll definitely play AC:B, so go ahead buy it, it's still a good game.\nJust dont' think about how badly your being played.\n8/10", "hours": 29.6, "user_id": "76561198000382639", "username": "zombies", "products": 357, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 235, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-14", "text": "AC FTW", "hours": 28.3, "username": "Zlacko", "products": 111, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 235, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-14", "text": "Kiling guards cant get better than this :)", "hours": 70.7, "user_id": "76561198031879393", "username": "Cyberrat", "products": 122, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 235, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-14", "text": "One of the best games that i have ever played with.", "hours": 68.7, "username": "in[s]anity", "products": 148, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 235, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-14", "text": "I have just spent a week of evenings in this game. I loved every minute of it.", "hours": 79.9, "username": "Xillix_404", "products": 1568, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 235, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-13", "text": "You can tell your assassin minions to kill anyone you want them to kill, and they do it! It's awesome!", "hours": 47.5, "username": "Professor of Rageology at Hate U", "products": 375, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 235, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-13", "text": "An excelente sequence of a great game.", "hours": 13.0, "username": "Hwarang", "products": 815, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 235, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-13", "text": "Para mi gusto, el mejor de la saga, hasta la fecha", "hours": 2.4, "user_id": "76561198034360887", "username": "Alvaro S", "products": 163, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 236, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-13", "text": "Para mi gusto, el mejor de la saga, hasta la fecha", "hours": 2.4, "user_id": "76561198034360887", "username": "Alvaro S", "products": 163, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 236, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-13", "text": "One of the best AC games", "hours": 33.6, "username": "LethaL", "products": 276, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 236, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-13", "text": "Me encanta sobre todo el mapa de la Alhambra de Granada donde vivo =) 9/10", "hours": 32.1, "user_id": "76561198021985196", "username": "Wampa", "products": 74, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 236, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-13", "text": "i love this game javonni was right its amazing :)", "hours": 18.7, "username": "Dark the Great", "products": 311, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 236, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-12", "text": "Incredible series, probably my favorite of this \"generation\".  Brotherhood is a brilliant way to continue Ezio's story.  I can't believe I sunk 40+ hours into this one game.", "hours": 47.4, "username": "Winterblink", "products": 341, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 236, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-12", "text": "Used to be such a fun game to play with friends , still able to find a match in multiplayer but takes long enough to find one but still worth the wait.", "hours": 169.1, "username": "Nati", "products": 428, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 236, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-12", "text": "Freeroam and stuff bla bla bla bla awesome!", "hours": 119.0, "username": "SUICIDEX", "products": 331, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 236, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-12", "text": "Game is worth its price, nice and cool story. Assasinating people, what else?", "hours": 42.5, "username": "Mr.Gabber", "products": 238, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 236, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-12", "text": "The jump of quality from Assassin's Creed to Assassin's Creed 2 was as big as the Grand Canyon. The leap to Brotherhood is not as big, but the game brings quite a few improvements. Now you manage a brotherhood of assassin's while trying to take down the Borgia. It has a lot of side missions, which do not get repetitive and the city of Rome is really fun to explore. I highly recommend this game to any fan of action-adventure games.", "hours": 64.4, "username": "JediEagle", "products": 1123, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 236, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-12", "text": "\u0421\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0441 ^_^", "hours": 27.1, "username": "Dr.SmiLe", "products": 67, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 237, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-07", "text": "Assassin's Creed: Brotherhood (AC:B) should be considered a worthy expansion of Assassin's Creed II, but it serves as a standalone game that continues where AC2 left off. The game continues the narrative saga, but quickly becomes tedious in its constant parkour maneuvers and climbing. However, AC:B is the first of the series to offer a multiplayer mode which in itself becomes just as tedious. Still, AC:B provides a crucial extension to the AC2's story line that again leaves fan hanging on for more. Essentially, AC:B feels like a paid expansion to properly conclude AC2 and begins to really show the repetitive nature of the series.", "hours": 22.7, "username": "Hairbautt", "products": 674, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 237, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-30", "text": "Continuing the saga of roof-running stabby goodness we have AC:Brotherhood.\nThe game continues to grow in interesting ways with much more diversity in how you deal with missions courtesy of your new group of \"mini-me\" assassins able to do your job for you. Got a guy on the rooftops in your path and no time to sneak up on him? Let your peeps handle it. Need a distraction? No problem, they're good. Need every guard in sight to take a \"nap\"? They've got you covered.\nAgain Ubisoft manages to expand the mission options and gameplay filling another game chock full of interesting characters and new gameplay. It's not just another expansion, it truly is a continuation and evolution of the series.\nThe now mandatory multiplayer is also quite intriguing but let's face it, that's not what you buy an AC game for, that's just a bonus.", "hours": 31.7, "username": "Mokubai", "products": 307, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 237, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-26", "text": "A very good game for the series but I wouldn't go out of my way to pay alot of money for it. Its pretty much just an expansion to creed 2. The storyline is meh but the game pay is fantastic! The city of rome is beauiful and there is so many wonderful things that you can do. I just wish the story had been btr and longer. Still, you should play it but don't pay too much for it.", "hours": 44.5, "user_id": "76561198002986817", "username": "Phantom Virus", "products": 356, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 237, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-25", "text": "Out of the series, this is my favourite so far. Familiarity of AC 2's HUD system and combat mechanics with additional in-game features such as building up your very own troupe of Assassins and sending them on missions to gain levels and become more powerful. One of my favourite features was having the Assassin's at my beck and call to terminate any tricky targets or just to troll the guards for a bit of fun. Great continuation of the story so far with even more intrigue thrown in and questions raised. Definitely a worthy addition to your AC collection, or just a fun game all around. *****", "hours": 17.6, "username": "Adeptus Ineptus", "products": 644, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 237, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-23", "text": "*-*  100%Sync + All Achievements", "hours": 26.5, "username": "XeLaphim", "products": 480, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 237, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-22", "text": "More stuff for Ezio to do and new equipment to do it with. The camera control issue is still there. I haven't tried the multiplayer aspect, but it has received decent reviews from those who have. The game gets a bit repetitive in places and a few side missions are quite frustrating (mainly due to camera control). The good folks at Ubisoft might have tried to bring in more than was really good for the game, but it's well worth the time to play with enough variety to keep it from becoming a complete disappointment. Get it if you can catch it on sale.", "hours": 162.7, "user_id": "76561198032084191", "username": "marstinson", "products": 157, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 237, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-10", "text": "A fantastic game with a lot of content, it's basically more of the same we saw in AC2, which is a good thing as that game was great. The main storyline undergoes little evolution, as has become common in AC games, but all is forgiven since reliving Ezio's memories in Rome during the Renaissance is a great experience.", "hours": 44.0, "username": "GamingAsArt", "products": 296, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 237, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-09", "text": "You don't buy this game for the gameplay. It plays almost exactly the same as the previous games. You should only get this game if you are interested in the story. It is a bit of a filler but it builds on Ezio's and Desmond's characters quite well. I think it's worth the money (during a sale though) if you're into the Assassin's Creed story.\n----[Rating weighted based on the genre]----\nI'm basing my rating on the game being part of a larger whole of the series. I do not recommend playing this game on it's own.\nStory: 5/5\nGameplay: 4/5\nChallenge: 2.5/5\nDiscovery: 3/5\nReplayability: 3/5\nAesthetics: 3.5/5\nVisuals: 5/5\nAtmosphere: 2.5/5\nMusic: 4/5", "hours": 38.2, "username": "Demian", "products": 229, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 237, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-08", "text": "Just when I thought Assassin's Creed couldn't get any more awesome... then came Brotherhood", "hours": 27.9, "username": "4cylinder", "products": 407, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 237, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-08", "text": "A good AC game.", "hours": 23.2, "username": "\u041c\u043e\u0438\u0441\u0435\u0439", "products": 271, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 238, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-06", "text": "The multiplayer is pretty fu\u2014 EXPANDING SEARCH CRITERIA", "hours": 1.8, "username": "HoboMan", "products": 524, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 238, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-01", "text": "Maybe the best game I've ever played, totally awesome sequel to this great series.", "hours": 57.0, "username": "_jackknife", "products": 474, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 238, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-28", "text": "A refinement of part 2, which I liked more but which I also did not play on Steam, so you're getting a recommendation of this and not that. The gameplay is standard Assassin's Creed stuff with a few additions that make it much easier, it's up to you whether that's a good or bad thing. I found a lot of the upgrade systems to be largely unecessary and mostly just busywork. If you play it stealthy like you're supposed to you won't need more powerful weapons and armor. And as long as you learn the combat you can get by with anything. The dialogue is not always great but at least the overall story is not insufferably bad. Requiescat in pace, videogioch.", "hours": 22.1, "username": "Borgnine", "products": 228, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 238, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-27", "text": "Great multiplayer :)\nI bet that Revelations has even better multi, but... Brotherhood is cheaper :)", "hours": 2.8, "username": "Elf", "products": 364, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 238, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-23", "text": "In spite of the hours I've logged on AC:B and ACII, don't be fooled: only about half of those hours are worth the playing. Most of all the AC games involves running around and trying to avoid being attacked by guards, who seem to spawn just in time to complicate your escape. The storyline and actual missions are great, but they tend to be variations on the same basic types: tail someone. Assassinate someone without being detected. Hold down W + RMB + SHFT indefnitely (what the game calls \"freerunning\"). AC:B seems to be particularly annoying with regards to how the controls and freerunning works: sometimes Ezio will leap off a tall building even though you told him to walk cautiously in the opposite direction, and sometimes he will lock on to something you didn't even know was there and save your hide before you even realized it was in danger. There are also several annoying features of the game, like the camera switching perspective, which throws off the direction Ezio moves in.", "hours": 18.2, "user_id": "76561197989581647", "username": "Fat-Bellied Graug", "products": 163, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 238, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-20", "text": "most definitely one of the best games ive played. Great story, great graphics, great multiplayer... Great gaming experience.", "hours": 78.0, "username": "Kruno", "products": 91, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 238, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-20", "text": "AWESOME GAME !!!", "hours": 7.0, "user_id": "76561198031147097", "username": "LozZou", "products": 102, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 238, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-20", "text": "More of an expansion to AC II but still fun. The selling point is the multiplayer and it is worth the hype.", "hours": 41.1, "username": "DroppinLoot (DavyDave)", "products": 125, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 238, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-17", "text": "Terrible game, multiplayer m\u00e1s terrible a\u00fan. Recomendadis\u00edmo.", "hours": 65.3, "username": "checho.-", "products": 158, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 238, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-15", "text": "Assassins creed brotherhood - \u044d\u0442\u043e \u0442\u0440\u0435\u0442\u044c\u044f \u0447\u0430\u0441\u0442\u044c \u043f\u043e\u043f\u0443\u043b\u044f\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e \u0444\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0447\u0430\u0439\u0437\u0430 assassins creed \u043e\u0442 \u043a\u043e\u043c\u043f\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0438 Ubisoft. \u0412 \u044d\u0442\u043e\u0439 \u0447\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0431\u044b\u043b\u0430 \u0438\u0437\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0430 \u0441\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0435\u043c\u0430 \u0431\u043e\u044f, \u0447\u0442\u043e \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u0433\u0447\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u0441\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f. \u0412\u0430\u043c \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0438\u0442 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u044c \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0435\u043c \u0433\u0438\u043b\u044c\u0434\u0438\u0438 \u0430\u0441\u0441\u0430\u0441\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0432, \u043a\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0430\u044f \u0441\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0430\u0435\u0442\u0441\u044f \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0442\u0438\u0432 \u0442\u0430\u043c\u043f\u043b\u0438\u0435\u0440\u043e\u0432. \u0412\u044b \u0432 \u043b\u044e\u0431\u043e\u0439 \u043c\u043e\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442 \u043c\u043e\u0436\u0435\u0442\u0435 \u0432\u044b\u0437\u0432\u0430\u0442\u044c \u0438\u0445 \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0449\u044c \u0447\u0442\u043e \u0442\u043e\u0436\u0435 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u0433\u0447\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u0441\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f. \u0413\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u043d\u0435 \u0438\u0437\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0438\u043b\u0430\u0441\u044c, \u0430\u043a\u0440\u043e\u0431\u0430\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u0442\u043e\u0436\u0435. \u041d\u0430 \u043b\u043e\u0448\u0430\u0434\u0438 \u0442\u0435\u043f\u0435\u0440\u044c \u043c\u043e\u0436\u043d\u043e \u0435\u0437\u0434\u0438\u0442\u044c \u043f\u0440\u044f\u043c\u043e \u0432 \u0433\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0435. \u0421\u044e\u0436\u0435\u0442 \u0442\u0430\u043a \u0436\u0435 \u043a\u0430\u043a \u0438 \u0432 \u0434\u0440\u0443\u0433\u0438\u0445 \u0447\u0430\u0441\u0442\u044f\u0445 \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0432\u044b\u0441\u043e\u0442\u0435 . \u0421\u0430\u0443\u043d\u0434\u0442\u0440\u0435\u043a \u0441\u0430\u043c\u044b\u0439 \u043b\u0443\u0447\u0448\u0438\u0439 \u0432 \u0438\u0433\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0439 \u0438\u043d\u0434\u0443\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0438.\u0412 \u0438\u0433\u0440\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u044f\u0432\u0438\u043b\u0441\u044f \u043c\u0443\u043b\u044c\u0442\u0438\u043f\u043b\u0435\u0435\u0440. \u0412 \u0446\u0435\u043b\u043e\u043c  \u043f\u043e\u0445\u0443\u0436\u0435 2 \u0447\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438.", "hours": 56.8, "username": "St_Flash \u2764 Mass Effect", "products": 703, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 239, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-10", "text": "It took the Assassins Creed series to a new level of game play. This game continues the amazing story it wove back in 2009 with AC2. I would say the only thing that AC2 could rival in this game is the story telling element. Other than that, very immersive and exteremly fun characters.", "hours": 60.7, "user_id": "76561198042108807", "username": "Loy Donarillo", "products": 226, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 239, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-07", "text": "For only one area you deal in (Rome) it's so in detail it's almost amazing. The characters look wonderful and I have to say, Ezio, Desmon and even the Altair outfit for Ezio looks great. They really should have used the models for Revelations. At times it does almost feel like a DLC for AC2, but I feel that it holds up on its own as a separate game. I only wished I had known my username for UBIsoft UPlay would be the username I used to sign up, meaning I'm stuck with a name I would rather not have causing me to really be unable to enjoy the Multiplayer aspect. All in all, definitely a game I would reccomend along with all the others in the series.", "hours": 8.9, "username": "Aracnel", "products": 412, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 239, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-05-06", "text": "Buy this game for $5 or \"borrow\" it. It was bad.\n2/10", "hours": 17.8, "username": "`v3nture", "products": 376, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 239, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-04", "text": "What a tragedy! Why, Ubi? Why did you let this game die and give it no love? AC:B won several GOTY awards, and frankly if I could give one, it'd win one from me, too. The atmospere is immersive, the voice acting is spectacular, and the music gives it a soul. With the exception of the controls often being the most epic boss in the game and the plot never going anywhere, story mode is worth the trip! But the MP flattens the SP by far! Vibrant, colorful, well-voiced, well MO-CAP player models and genius design, the MP is arguably the best gaming has ever seen. Unfortuantely, Ubi decided to go all COD on it, releasing another AC every year. The legendary MP that they did so well to make is now dead forever. What a shame. This game deserved to live forever like QUAKE or CS. Still recommended, just don't expect to get a MP game.", "hours": 54.8, "username": "Upsilon", "products": 137, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 239, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-24", "text": "This game is pretty sweet, actually. The city is pretty immersive and fun to explore, the story missions flow pretty well, and the mechanics are improved from the previous games. I just hate the sequences as Desmond!", "hours": 71.6, "username": "Badger M.D.", "products": 594, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 239, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-19", "text": "\u0418\u0433\u0440\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0438\u0432\u0430\u044e\u0449\u0430\u044f \u0443\u0432\u0430\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f!!! \u0420\u0435\u0441\u043f\u0435\u043a\u0442 \u0441\u043e\u0437\u0434\u0430\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044f\u043c. \u041e\u0436\u0438\u0434\u0430\u044e Assassin\u2019s Creed 3.", "hours": 17.9, "username": "FROZTi", "products": 166, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 239, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-13", "text": "Continues the great plot of AC games. With plot set in Rome in early 15 century, it is as beautiful as its predecessors. There are also some new elements of gameplay. And amazing multiplayer. Totally worth its price.", "hours": 25.9, "username": "Von the Wat?", "products": 1177, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 239, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-11", "text": "This game is awesome and the mechanics are great. It introduces new features and surpasses its predecessor. A must-have for every lover of the AC Games.", "hours": 40.5, "user_id": "76561198001496551", "username": "PrydeRage", "products": 180, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 239, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-09", "text": "The third game in a great series of games, they just keep getting better, even after completing the main story line there seems to be so much more this game has to offer. If you haven't tried it already it is definitely worth a try.", "hours": 53.5, "username": "KeyboardDemon", "products": 194, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 239, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-04", "text": "Mechanically the best AC game but it's more than a little padded with filler. If you're a completionist, know what you're getting into.", "hours": 107.2, "username": "CarlCX", "products": 2372, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 240, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-09", "text": "The third game in a great series of games, they just keep getting better, even after completing the main story line there seems to be so much more this game has to offer. If you haven't tried it already it is definitely worth a try.", "hours": 53.5, "username": "KeyboardDemon", "products": 194, "early_access": false}
