{"product_id": "48190", "page": 240, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-04", "text": "Even better than AC2!! ZOMG!! And there is a multiplayer. It's fun but sometimes so unfair D:\nAmazing game! Can't wait to play Revelations zomg! YEYEYE yfaklf aklhklf jahl", "hours": 33.3, "username": "bashscrazy", "products": 378, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 240, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-01", "text": "Really fun, the controls on PC are difficult are first but you get used to them fairly quick.", "hours": 17.9, "username": "Esudesu-senpaiu", "products": 309, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 241, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-02-27", "text": "One city? Really?!\nAfter being spoiled with AssCreed2 and the multiple locations rome just becomes mundane and lifeless.\nThere is no drive to continue to find out where you will end up next and what the next place will look like.\nThe story is ok, but starting to get borning.\nGraphics are poorly optimized, with random white fog at the top of the screen...", "hours": 49.2, "username": "Tularis", "products": 480, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 241, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-24", "text": "excelente jogo, muito longo, porem recomendo zerar o 2 primeiro!\ntow com+ de 20 horas de jogo e s\u00f3 fiz 70% do modo historia! at\u00e9 agora\"!\njog\u00e3o j\u00e1 em portugu\u00eas! RECOMENDO", "hours": 45.5, "user_id": "76561198035351056", "username": "PernambucanO*", "products": 96, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 241, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-23", "text": "If you liked previous AC games, you'll love this one. They finally got the kinks out of the combat system, making multi-kills and fluid takedowns easier and enhancing gameplay in many other areas. Good story too.", "hours": 50.1, "username": "cdrummer85", "products": 156, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 241, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-19", "text": "A worthy follow up to Assassin's Creed II. It advances the plot further and gameplay mechanics are much improved upon. I love this game and have spent alot of time on the whole series. Graphics aren't improved that much from the other games in the series, but the changes in weapons, cities, and missions make it new and exciting.", "hours": 71.9, "username": "Vern", "products": 254, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 241, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-08", "text": "If you are looking to buy one of the AC games, get Brotherhood, none of the others compare.", "hours": 77.5, "user_id": "76561198046090105", "username": "Brain Anus Rhythm", "products": 71, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 241, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-30", "text": "AC Brotherhood may not be as fresh as AC2, but it's an excellent example of improving what was already good, and implementing good new things. Besides, if you played the second game, you owe it to yourself to play this one. 4/5*", "hours": 65.9, "username": "Riquerico", "products": 308, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 241, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-29", "text": "Just another soap opera again. I expected much more. Bright side is the multiplayer as it looks pretty innovating and fun.", "hours": 77.6, "username": "(GoR)Andrew.zhd", "products": 353, "early_access": false}
