{"product_id": "48190", "page": 242, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-06", "text": "10/10 I loved it.", "hours": 71.5, "username": "418", "products": 321, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 242, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-04", "text": "Mesmo mantendo praticamente a mesma mec\u00e2nica e o mesmo visual, Assassin's Creed Brotherhood consegue ser levemente superior ao seu antecessor. As poucas, mas not\u00e1veis adi\u00e7\u00f5es ajudaram a deixar o jogo mais din\u00e2mico (como os assassinos da Brotherhood e o sistema financeiro). As miss\u00f5es, especialmente as side quests, ficaram um pouco mais diversificadas e n\u00e3o est\u00e3o t\u00e3o cansativas. \u00danico problema \u00e9 que a hist\u00f3ria demora demais pra sair do lugar e quando come\u00e7a a ficar legal, o jogo termina. Isso \u00e9 realmente frustrante. Recomendado pra quem jogou e TERMINOU o AC II.", "hours": 39.8, "username": "tiotuli", "products": 262, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 242, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-04", "text": "This is a fun game if you like to parkour around, beat up random fat chicks, pickpocket people, kill and loot gaurds, and throw their dead bodies into a body of water or off of a bridge.", "hours": 0.0, "user_id": "76561198041115941", "username": "The Bad Elf", "products": 18, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 242, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-31", "text": "This is one of the best games I've played.", "hours": 2.8, "username": "LoGa", "products": 468, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 242, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-30", "text": "xD", "hours": 9.3, "username": "Naid", "products": 152, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 242, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-30", "text": "If you get past the hang up with Ubisoft's system, this is such an engaging, ramped up version of Assassin's Creed II.", "hours": 35.5, "username": "Perp", "products": 133, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 242, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-29", "text": "Best assassins creed game yet released", "hours": 48.5, "username": "RyderLT", "products": 90, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 242, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-29", "text": "Great game, you'll be playing it for hours and wont get bored!", "hours": 94.7, "user_id": "76561197971342328", "username": "Johny", "products": 217, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 242, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-29", "text": "Awesome game and is a great step up from Assassin's Creed II!", "hours": 65.0, "username": "Saftle", "products": 1931, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 242, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-29", "text": "The Single Player is not much more than Assassin's Creed 2, just one or two new ways to kill people or get around the city, which isn't necessarily a bad thing, but any gripes with the series so far probably haven't been addressed with this installment, and what people have liked about the series is still in the game.  My favorite aspect of Brotherhood was the multiplayer.  I personally haven't played any game that had this style of gameplay, so it was \"fresh\" so to say, something new to learn, new mechanics to wrap my head around and master, a different way to use the mechanics we were given in single player.  I greatly enjoyed the way the multiplayer emulated the feeling that the original assassin's creed created when it first released, which was the feeling of being an assassin, which I personally haven't felt since AC 1 was released.", "hours": 26.1, "username": "grimlock", "products": 283, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 243, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-29", "text": "The Single Player is not much more than Assassin's Creed 2, just one or two new ways to kill people or get around the city, which isn't necessarily a bad thing, but any gripes with the series so far probably haven't been addressed with this installment, and what people have liked about the series is still in the game.  My favorite aspect of Brotherhood was the multiplayer.  I personally haven't played any game that had this style of gameplay, so it was \"fresh\" so to say, something new to learn, new mechanics to wrap my head around and master, a different way to use the mechanics we were given in single player.  I greatly enjoyed the way the multiplayer emulated the feeling that the original assassin's creed created when it first released, which was the feeling of being an assassin, which I personally haven't felt since AC 1 was released.", "hours": 26.1, "username": "grimlock", "products": 283, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 243, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-28", "text": "Really amazing multi player and really cool everything.", "hours": 67.9, "user_id": "76561198020789201", "username": "Zeta", "products": 144, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 243, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-28", "text": "There's just something about having an elite band of underlings to unleash upon the city.", "hours": 122.8, "user_id": "76561198034230631", "username": "Anaze", "products": 123, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 243, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-28", "text": "This is probably the best AC game.", "hours": 92.2, "user_id": "76561198038360600", "username": "ThermoNuc", "products": 143, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 243, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-28", "text": "amazing game, freaken nice!  you must have tried this", "hours": 28.8, "username": "IamKZ", "products": 222, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 243, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-28", "text": "beautiful graphics, real locations of venice florence italy... good story line, LOVE IT!", "hours": 9.6, "user_id": "76561198017033087", "username": "easy peasy", "products": 57, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 243, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-28", "text": "An epic game where you play with history. A great sequel to Assassin's Creed II, which takes Ezio's story farther. A game where you can literally climb anything you see and go anywhere you want, as far as it's not outside the map's limit. And what a beatiful map to.. 1500 Rome, really beatiful setting for the game. And it's even completed by the most unique multiplayer I ever tried. What else would you want?", "hours": 446.1, "username": "ElleCore", "products": 745, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 243, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "\uc815\ub9d0 \uc7ac\ubc0c\uc9c0!", "hours": 36.5, "username": "Purupuru", "products": 183, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 243, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "So many things to do ..... Loving the latest iteration of the combat system -- not to mention virtual environment challenges", "hours": 70.1, "user_id": "76561197980968829", "username": "warDrum", "products": 128, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 243, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "If you haven't played this game yet, you're missing out. What  other AAA title takes place during the Italian Renaissance? This is hands down the best iteration despite being considered a quick \"expansion\". Come for the multiplayer, stay for the time machine simulation. This\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665is like heroine for history buffs!", "hours": 31.5, "username": "Sevirm", "products": 413, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 244, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "SOOO AMAZING", "hours": 73.4, "username": "Carne Esada", "products": 93, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 244, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Assassin's Creed Brotherhood takes what it's predecessor did and moved it further into a commanding role of the assassins. While it does hold it's own missions, there's an interesting meta-layer that is used to improve Rome's economy and business which in turn helps you outfit you and yours.\nThe only downside is that if you invest the time into making sure you have Rome fully supported, you practically end up swimming in money which really damages the balance of the game.\nDespite that flaw, it's more of the same with a bit of new on top that again justifies the asking price over it's predecessor, DRM not withstanding.", "hours": 25.6, "username": "Freyar", "products": 1368, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 244, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "It's like cake, only with assassins.", "hours": 41.7, "username": "Davor", "products": 628, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 244, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "i like this game a lot, but there is no cow level", "hours": 16.7, "user_id": "76561197995526568", "username": "Kaptajn Keglekonge", "products": 243, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 244, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Despite Revelations being the newer title, Brotherhood is what I consider to be the pinnacle of the Assassin's Creed game concept. If you like the pairing of third-person action with RPG elements and free roam, you can easily sink 50 hours into it if you seek out the side quests! Multiplayer is also quite serviceable, though it's probably hard to find a community playing it now - better spent playing with friends.", "hours": 47.0, "username": "Kevlar", "products": 1189, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 244, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Fantastic game, can't wait to play the next installment.", "hours": 71.3, "username": "Erazor", "products": 95, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 244, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "My Fav in the series so far", "hours": 89.6, "username": "DraQion Ocer", "products": 131, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 244, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "AC:B is IMO the peak of ACs storyline. I loved every corner of Rome^^ If you are, like me, more a fan of good storytelling nad want to explore regions you may not be able to see quit soon just do yourself a favor (yeah, I don't like UPlay either..) and buy it. Personally my last recommendation for a AC titel.", "hours": 43.9, "user_id": "76561198015583421", "username": "Nills Knillz", "products": 409, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 244, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Cannot recomend this enough! One of the best games I've played! Intriguing story, the combat and movements are fluid and really engaging. When you start getting apprentices is really fun, you can cooly stand back and watch your apprentices sweep the way before you.", "hours": 82.6, "username": "rage77", "products": 421, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 244, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Some call it an \"Assassin's Creed 2.5\", but that's a heavy understatement. Ezio is back with even more clever and amusing ways to kill Italian (and later, French) guards throughout Rome as you strive to rebuild the city for its people, along with additional character development with Desmond.\nPerhaps the most innovative thing about Brotherhood is its introduction of a multiplayer deathmatch, where the objective is to find and assassinate other chosen target players throughout a town or other similar map.", "hours": 30.3, "username": "beep", "products": 353, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 245, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Some call it an \"Assassin's Creed 2.5\", but that's a heavy understatement. Ezio is back with even more clever and amusing ways to kill Italian (and later, French) guards throughout Rome as you strive to rebuild the city for its people, along with additional character development with Desmond.\nPerhaps the most innovative thing about Brotherhood is its introduction of a multiplayer deathmatch, where the objective is to find and assassinate other chosen target players throughout a town or other similar map.", "hours": 30.3, "username": "beep", "products": 353, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 245, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Twice the disk-space, half the content, and only a third of the story of AC2. Buy it if you like the series and can't live without certain plot information, don't buy it otherwise.", "hours": 11.0, "username": "Ev", "products": 179, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 245, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "The most epic, deep and powerful AC done to date, and last one done by AC creator. It uses a huge sandbox reign over all rome. You get to explore it's fields, its house disctrict, even its anciens.\nEverything feels alive and you feel like a part of it.\nCharacters are further explored and developed, you really see them grow since the last game. I must say that one of the standing points of the game is it's writting.\nThe engine and gameplay feels a lot more polished than the previous one, more soft and confortable, again you feel like you have complete control.", "hours": 49.6, "user_id": "76561198005362575", "username": "Shark Knight", "products": 48, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 245, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Stabby, poisony, shooty, stabby, slashy, bashy, stabby, look at my horse!", "hours": 59.4, "username": "Butterknife", "products": 429, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 245, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Pretty fun game, but I think number 2 was by far better.", "hours": 22.1, "username": "Karth Komputer 2.0", "products": 322, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 245, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "The Assassins Creed series is definiitely one of my favourites. From the story to the gameplay it's just outstanding. I love the freedom of hopping between rooftops and doing quests and assassination missions while at the same time restoring different towns/cities. Brotherhood lets you recruit and manage your own Assassins group allowing you to send them on their own missions to get you money or have to assist you when you're in a tough situation. Brotherhood is definitely a must-buy if you've played the other games and if you haven't, I suggest you play Assassin's Creed 2 first as this is a direct sequel to that. Playing Assassins Creed 1 is not entirely necessary, but it helps.", "hours": 1.8, "user_id": "76561198005615605", "username": "Lethal Games", "products": 151, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 245, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "wassa-natte with you al-tair", "hours": 113.4, "username": "ISR|Glitch", "products": 93, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 245, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Great game. Love the Economy system. Gives the game a rich gameplay. Can't wait to play Revelations.", "hours": 51.1, "username": "Mr. Illya Kuryakin", "products": 227, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 245, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "I love this game. I recommend this game to every gamer. It's a MUST BUY!", "hours": 102.1, "username": "linas.warrior", "products": 723, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 245, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Basically a glorified expansion to the first game, with improved combat and game mechanics but a weaker story. Still fun, but not as compelling as Assassin's Creed 2.", "hours": 59.8, "username": "Jahandar", "products": 1171, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 246, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "best AC yet\n2016 edit: still best AC", "hours": 61.1, "username": "kARDON", "products": 58, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 246, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Good game!!", "hours": 152.0, "username": "Shaked6540", "products": 172, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 246, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "I love this game so much I can't wait to play the new one, it would be great if they made a ninja game as well", "hours": 41.9, "user_id": "76561198034741383", "username": "xeroja", "products": 140, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 246, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "not bad", "hours": 42.0, "username": "\u2655Goose\ud83d\udc51", "products": 400, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 246, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Pretty decent game, a few things to do.", "hours": 1.7, "username": "Vobra", "products": 233, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 246, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-25", "text": "Test your skills and agility while being a one man army", "hours": 35.9, "user_id": "76561197971206509", "username": "Mr Woodchuck", "products": 275, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 246, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-23", "text": "Simplesmente espetacular, a Ubi ta mandando bem com esta s\u00e9rie, me atrevo a dizer que \u00e9 uma das melhores s\u00e9ries j\u00e1 vista. Apesar de ter gostado mais de AC II, esta continua\u00e7\u00e3o n\u00e3o deixou nada a desejar. Recomendo com vontade.", "hours": 96.9, "username": "bubsylopez\u00ae", "products": 786, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 246, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-17", "text": "This is super awesome 5 stars. Though the last one looks way better", "hours": 124.6, "user_id": "76561198019273105", "username": "Dwayne \"The Minion\" Johnson", "products": 101, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 246, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-03", "text": "Couldn't we have just called this Assassin's Creed 3?\nAlthough little more than sequel to the previous game, it still gives you enough new mechanics and locations that it doesn't actually seem like a retread.  Unfortunately, it is much more integrated into Uplay, including a shared-market idea that totally misses the mark and detracts more than it possibly adds.  The excellent story arc continues, with an ending that is spoileriffic -- so don't go searching for it.", "hours": 73.4, "username": "mdwyer", "products": 315, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 246, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-28", "text": "EPIC GAME", "hours": 45.3, "username": "Dank Grimes", "products": 151, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 247, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-26", "text": "Revolutionary Multiplayer. Fantastic sequel. An all around amazing game. This series has much to offer. The quote \"History is our playground. Join us.\" is the all in all sumation of what this SUPREME game series has to offer.", "hours": 67.5, "username": "Chef Curry", "products": 124, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 247, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-11-26", "text": "After AC2 being a much better game than AC1, I had expected to like AC:B equally well. But for some reason I cannot explain this never happened. I really tried to like it but somehow they managed to change the existing game concepts in a way that makes me experience the game as an incredibly slow paced and tedious piece of work. I  never felt fun playing it. Maybe I overplayed on AC2 and need to give it a break. For now I wont finish this.", "hours": 10.5, "username": "go_oh", "products": 103, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 247, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-24", "text": "Game is teh\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665", "hours": 17.0, "user_id": "76561198020926821", "username": "Zenpachi", "products": 74, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 247, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-22", "text": "Auch ein guter Teil, aber nicht so gut wie der 2.te.", "hours": 16.5, "user_id": "76561198018478327", "username": "Skip", "products": 146, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 247, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-20", "text": "Again this was a great incarnation of the assasins creed series. Continuing with ezio where he left off and keeping the great gameplay style of the last game it was a winner for me. I would recommend this if you played assasins creed 2, however if you haven't then i suggest you play that first. I haven't played multiplayer so i can't comment on that i've only ever been interested in the single player.", "hours": 14.5, "username": "Invisible Man", "products": 514, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 247, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-16", "text": "Moreover, it is an expansion to Assassin's Creed 2, but still worth your time and money. Great game.", "hours": 4.7, "user_id": "76561198045872273", "username": "The Cheesinator", "products": 126, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 247, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-11", "text": "The best title in the series yet.", "hours": 23.1, "user_id": "76561197993473943", "username": "broozar", "products": 196, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 247, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-10", "text": "An excellent job of  tricking you into not realizing that you're stuck in one place with largely recycled gameplay. Rome is a thrill. Masterfully done.", "hours": 47.3, "user_id": "76561198031538705", "username": "johntheobscure", "products": 140, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 247, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-10", "text": "It is like Assassin's Creed 2.5, more storyline and further englufs you into the story of Desmond Miles and Ezio Auditore. You learn to appreciate how bad\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665the assassins really are. I didn't expect much from it at first because it wasn't AC3, but really they do an amazing job with this game and I'm VERY MUCH looking forward to the next in the series. The ending was crazy good as well and left you with your jaw on the ground and wanting more.\nOh it has multiplayer as well but I didn't really try it.", "hours": 19.2, "username": "ItadakiTom", "products": 491, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 247, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-02", "text": "jogo legal de ler parkur, vc pratica ler parkur na espanha ou mechico (nao sei, ) mas tem banidos que querem coisa ruim de vc", "hours": 16.0, "username": "Sentafria", "products": 736, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 248, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-02", "text": "jogo legal de ler parkur, vc pratica ler parkur na espanha ou mechico (nao sei, ) mas tem banidos que querem coisa ruim de vc", "hours": 16.0, "username": "Sentafria", "products": 736, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 248, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-01", "text": "Despite a few bugs, the game is excelent. The new Brotherhood system is awesome.", "hours": 52.1, "username": "MiKau", "products": 450, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 248, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-26", "text": "Most awesome AC game so far, now with multiplayer! The story also developes even more, the player once more gets a lot to think about and we learn things about characters we didn't know before. Really great!", "hours": 113.7, "username": "Munchiechu", "products": 207, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 248, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-21", "text": "I am in love with this series and this is by far the best installment so far. Great story, characters, setting and bucket loads of content.", "hours": 20.6, "user_id": "76561197992310231", "username": "HeyOldMate", "products": 218, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 248, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-21", "text": "The second part of the second chapter of an epic novel, this time the story is driven by vengeance.", "hours": 35.7, "username": "Humanista", "products": 104, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 248, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-18", "text": "Pure Pleasure ;) Assassin's Creed is always a fun game to play and in my opinion, Brotherhood is still the best one in the series. Worth the money! No other ACs come close!", "hours": 20.5, "username": "NotMyGopher\u2122", "products": 450, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 248, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-11", "text": "Awesome storyline but  a bit short.However it has multiplayer and its reallyy good to be an assasin against human players", "hours": 58.2, "username": "Tulpar1988", "products": 188, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 248, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-09", "text": "Bene, very bene", "hours": 0.0, "username": "neeyik", "products": 509, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 248, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-06", "text": "Major improvements over the otherwise great Assassin's Creed 2. The missions in this game doesn't feel as much as the same thing over and over again. Great big singleplayer game that continuous the story from AC2 (however, I do think the story in AC2 is better than in Brotherhood).\nI haven't tried the multiplayer, but the single player is really worth the price.", "hours": 57.7, "username": "Skaery", "products": 6723, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 248, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-03", "text": "Brotherhood is the best showcase - yet - for the series' formidable quality and range, with an excellent campaign and an equally intriguing online approach.\nBrotherhood is a must have for all Assassin's Creed fans.", "hours": 31.9, "username": "FranK", "products": 147, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 249, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-02", "text": "The 3rd game in the series; it contains single and multiplayer which are seperate.\nThe multiplayer mode is 'Vs' with you playing as a character that looks like the townsfolk so you can blend in and kill your target which is another player.\nSingleplayer is pretty much let off the last game in terms of story so unless you want spoilers to be given to you in cinematics I suggest completing the previous games or it will ruin it.\nThis game reminds me of Assassin's Creed 2, with a few minor improvements to the options and UI, but nothing major from what I can tell .", "hours": 2.7, "username": "DarkOnistar", "products": 1130, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 249, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-02", "text": "The first Assassin's Creed was clearly a game with great potential and cool ideas, a new approach to the \"sneak and stealh\"-genre. But alas, it turned out weak due mostly to it's highly repetitive missions and completion structure, unintresting plotline and world and it's generally unpolished finish. Cue Brotherhood, the third installment in the franchise. This is Assassin's Creed in it's top form. A beautifully rendered Rome in the Reneissance Era with characters, buildings and events from real-life combined with the fictionous Ezio and his quest, vastly imporved controls that add to the fluidity of the parkour movements and the general feeling that now I, the player, am in control of not only Ezio but also Rome. This is how it should have been from the beginning!", "hours": 31.9, "username": "[LUC] Chride", "products": 113, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 249, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-28", "text": "The only game that can top this one, must be Assassin's Creed 4! Add to cart, buy and purchase, play and love it!", "hours": 38.7, "username": "[+rep] RePLAY [DK]", "products": 215, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 249, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-23", "text": "Great Game", "hours": 15.0, "username": "DongCena", "products": 111, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 249, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-18", "text": "I don't know how to describe these games, they're made of conspiracy theories and win. It's a Sci-fi story of Assassins and Templars that could mean the end of the world as we know it...the story is still unfinished...and you're the key to finding out the secrets of those who came before us.", "hours": 23.8, "user_id": "76561198011581104", "username": "Codename B.T.", "products": 476, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 249, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-18", "text": "Are you all excited for AC: Revelations? Well then You better get this now and get practicing. Oh, If you care about the story, start with AC2, but NOT AC1. AC1 is a waste of your time. AC2 is WAY better and they got everything right. come to think of it, I'd say AC:B had better game play, but AC2 Had the better story and ending. Have fun going around killing people, and hang in there until you can recruit assasin trainees in sequence 4, THATS when the game really shines. Prototype meets GTA in the rennesance, BETTER than both games and you need to play now. BTW the multiplayer is first rate once you get the hang of it. It's less than $30 and there's no excuse not to own and play it. It's just DAMN good and there's nothing else like it.", "hours": 145.1, "username": "AzzKikr143", "products": 215, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 249, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-15", "text": "Brotherhood picks up right where Assassin's Creed 2 leaves off.  Ezio begins gathering and training new assassin recruits for the order, which itself becomes a major new gameplay mechanic allowing you to find and rescue them, get them to join, train them, and call them to aid you in battle. Ezio on his own is a force to be reckoned with for a whole army of renaissance warriors, but with the Brotherhood at his side it becomes a slaughterfest.\nAgain, this game builds upon its predecessors, adding new weapons, mechanics, refinements, options, etc. Better quest system and economy system. You can gain military control of parts of Rome by destorying enemy bases....etc etc etc etc\nThis game is awesome.\nMy only complaint with it might be that between his ranged weapons, and the Brotherhood, Ezio might be TOO powerful.\nAlso, Multiplayer.\nIt's unlike any other Multiplayer out there and, contrary to conventional wisdom, Assassin's Creed translates to be a GREAT multiplayer game.", "username": "Thunderous Clockwork WarMachine", "products": 312, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 249, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-14", "text": "That game really exceeded my expectations!There's a lot of stuff to do and a lot of secondary missions!The graphics and gameplay are perfect in my opinion!", "hours": 88.8, "username": "vicmgrj", "products": 101, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 249, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-08", "text": "Deep storyline, following Ezio Auditor\u00e8 da Firenze on his journey through Rome. Like the previous installments, the gameplay's core mechanics are based on parkour movements, crowd-blending stealth, assassinations and melee fighting system. Recruit and train Assassin's as you're the \"Il Mentore\" head of the Assassin Guild. Bring vengeance upon Cesare Borgia and the Templar Order and build up Rome.", "hours": 27.5, "username": "Solstark", "products": 274, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 249, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-06", "text": "Ezio rocks!", "hours": 92.6, "user_id": "76561197968247577", "username": "Ezekielsims", "products": 165, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 250, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-05", "text": "With it\u00b4s combined free to go where u want to, the good story, graphics and a move/fight system like no others i can say all truly that i cannot see another game like this.", "hours": 75.4, "username": "JFET_Castics", "products": 225, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 250, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-28", "text": "a  perfect  work!", "hours": 67.1, "username": "motherched", "products": 720, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 250, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-23", "text": "Best of the series yet. Play Assassin's Creed 2 first if you haven't. (AC1 doesn't really matter and it sucks anyway.)", "hours": 31.4, "username": "Ultraviper", "products": 875, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 250, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-22", "text": "I never want to stop playing", "hours": 15.3, "username": "Gvaz", "products": 1206, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 250, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-08-21", "text": "+++ multiplayer is fun...\n--- ... when you can wait 5 to 10 minutes for match making and stuff like that\n-+ assassins recruits\n- assassins recruits =) you don't need them. I mean you're the boss in the ring, no enemy matchs you. and now, you can sit on your horse, call your recruits on your enemies and look bored like a boss\n-- to many boring side missions\n-- the main missions are also boring\n--- the whole singleplayer game feels like an add-on for the multiplayer mode\n--- I could'nt follow the story anymore, I don't understand the ending and I don't really care\n---- the glyph riddles are very boring", "hours": 50.2, "username": "kingkrabbe.#bof", "products": 178, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 250, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-20", "text": "AC:Brotherhood added a ton more from AC2, but I'm not too crazy about all of it. I felt overwhelmed in some parts but I got used to it eventually then came to enjoy all the extra stuff they threw in. Also, multiplayer has got to be the most fun I've had online in a long time. Takes some serious skill.", "hours": 63.1, "username": "Mr. Roboto", "products": 2488, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 250, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-18", "text": "The game it self is a masterpice\nthe problem is that the community for multiplayer is very close to nonexistent\na shame since the multiplayer is very simple yet very fun and will make you come back for more.\nyou will need at least 6 players (within stabil ping range) in order to play a game of multiplayer.\nI love the game and i'm sad to see that almost no one plays it ;_;", "hours": 28.6, "user_id": "76561198003396606", "username": "Wanted ZandvicH \u25d5_\u25d5", "products": 72, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 250, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-15", "text": "The continuation of Assassin's Creed II's story in single player, and a mutliplayer mode that seemed pretty sketchy at first but was implemented in a really great way. You should get it so more people are playing it on multiplayer because it is fun and challenging.", "hours": 35.5, "username": "NorskVind", "products": 227, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 250, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-14", "text": "Assassins Creed Brotherhood is what I would consider a very good expansion to AC2. Ubisoft refined the combat system and the storyline is as enticing as ever. Sure, the Desmond parts are just the usual acrobatic feats but it's great. Ezio, now in his 40's and an experienced Assassin heads to Rome, and Rome is huuuuuge! I won't waste time on the SP experience as I loved it. As for the story? It was good but it doesn't top AC2 in terms of the wow-factor.\nThe Mulitplayer is what shocked me. It's so fun. It's really fun! I thought it would fail but it didn't and I can't get enough of it! Sure you have the nooby roof runners which will\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665you off and the MP will get on your nerves and have you raging, but it's great nevertheless. 8/10 from me overall.", "hours": 186.9, "username": "Merchant2006 - Streaming Live!", "products": 477, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 250, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-14", "text": "The Best Assassin's Creed ever!\nIt has an awesome multiplayer, that is just epic!\nAnd story mode is cool too so, this is a must-buy game.", "hours": 0.6, "username": "DevilSP", "products": 225, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 251, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-05", "text": "\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665thought this was GTA 6 nvm", "hours": 6.1, "username": "The Knightofdeath", "products": 485, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 251, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-05", "text": "Excellent GTA style open world with plenty of weapons and upgrades available.  Real fun game, but it's excellent really rests with Multiplayer.  Simple, but beautiful mechanics make all multiplayer games incredibly enjoyable.", "hours": 36.9, "user_id": "76561198006141937", "username": "Black Monday Blues", "products": 429, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 251, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-04", "text": "Assassin's Creed: Brotherhood is the sequel of Assassin's Creed II.\nBest way to describe it is to simply say that this game is even more interesting and awesome from the previous one.\nThe story continues with the same main character from Assassin's Creed II.\nThis time everything is placed around the Rome of ~1500 with a complete design of how all city designes used to be.\nThe game's storyline is as interesting as ever, with more great surprises and revealed infrmation.\nVery well designed graphics with details and great animations.\nA lot more RPG elements and a great quantity of extra features and new weapons.\nJust like Assassin's Creed II,you will not get bored of the game.\nEither by choosing to follow only the main quests or by going freeroam or by doing some of teh many sidequests you can just choose whatever you like.\nThe game is really awesome!\nFound some bugs but this was a minor to what i experienced by playing this.\nCan't wait for Assassin's Creed Revelations.\nRecommended!", "hours": 71.8, "username": "Zweis\u2020ein ( \u0ca0_\u0ca0)", "products": 261, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 251, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-02", "text": "Brotherhood is an amazing game that was extremely hard to put down. There is so much to the game its crazy! The sights in the game are breathtaking, the sounds really draw you into the gameplay. The fighting are totally fun and looked foreword to. The story is in-depth and makes sense. The \"Brotherhood\" itself are great to have with you in battle. The multiplayer is so fun and really unique. The controls are great , I played this with an Xbox 360 Controller. The overall game really is a must play for any lover of the Assassins Creed series. If you have played the previous 2 Assassins Creed then don't hesitate any further. This is a must have! I've loved playing it to the end and I know you will too!", "hours": 35.4, "username": "NorkDorf On Twitch {Live}", "products": 8235, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 251, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-31", "text": "I was drawn into the interesting, continuing story of Ezio and his wall-running war against the Templars", "hours": 18.2, "user_id": "76561197971002914", "username": "The Wah", "products": 157, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 251, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-25", "text": "Great game, alot shorter than the last one but its alot more challenging than the last one, so it balances itself out. Cant wait for the next one to come out, the tralier for it looks awesome.", "hours": 9.8, "user_id": "76561198005894381", "username": "Escurofalcon", "products": 60, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 251, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-22", "text": "Plays a lot like Assassin's Creed 2, but with some cool extra features. Most notably is  the Brotherhood system where you recruit civilians to the Brotherhood to work as assassins. They can either pounce from the shadows to take out tough targets or send them out on missions to earn more money for your cause.\nThe story picks up immediatly after AC2. For this reason, it's hard to recommend ACB over AC2. ACB is pretty much AC2+, so if you can only buy one: buy this one and read up on AC2's story on wikipedia.", "hours": 25.5, "username": "Flea", "products": 465, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 251, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-22", "text": "This series gets better and better.  ACB keeps the core elements of the first two games while adding some depth and leveling elements to recruiting assassins and guilds to help fight the Borgia oppressors.\nMultiplayer is unique and fun as \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665.  If your friends are playing this online, and you don't buy it to join them, then I don't know why they still call you a friend.  You're missing out on a new kind of Multiplayer fun that doesn't try to clone Call of Duty.\nThis game is solid.", "hours": 135.9, "username": "Captain Serious", "products": 344, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 251, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-22", "text": "Hist\u00f3ria muito boa, onde voc\u00ea aprende a hist\u00f3ria de monumentos, cidades, personagens REAIS, convive com personalidades famosas como Maquiavel e Leonardo DaVinci e possui um multiplayer inovador e viciante. Precisa de mais motivos para comprar este jogo?", "hours": 39.7, "username": "Beto", "products": 385, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 251, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-18", "text": "Great single player and multiplayer!", "hours": 28.7, "username": "Oglaf", "products": 80, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 252, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-22", "text": "Hist\u00f3ria muito boa, onde voc\u00ea aprende a hist\u00f3ria de monumentos, cidades, personagens REAIS, convive com personalidades famosas como Maquiavel e Leonardo DaVinci e possui um multiplayer inovador e viciante. Precisa de mais motivos para comprar este jogo?", "hours": 39.7, "username": "Beto", "products": 385, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 252, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-18", "text": "Great single player and multiplayer!", "hours": 28.7, "username": "Oglaf", "products": 80, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 252, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-17", "text": "amazing", "hours": 14.5, "username": "Nauj", "products": 507, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 252, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-17", "text": "Just as much fun content as Assassin's Creed II, and the same basic ideas and gameplay too, but not as well put together. The main story doesn't drive you to the more fun missions in the game. Do run around and find every Leo mission and clear every borgia tower.\nWorth playing if you enjoyed the second game, but if you passed that one up, don't pick this over it.", "hours": 30.1, "username": "VampireStrike!", "products": 365, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 252, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-16", "text": "pedazo juego le doy un 9.5 el modo historia es una joya pero lo del multi mola pero se me queda corto muy recomendable comprarlo", "hours": 1.2, "username": "N3w0ne", "products": 259, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 252, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-13", "text": "Awesome game, pretty damn addicting. I kill people just to see the animations. Killing people has never looked so cool", "hours": 28.3, "username": "POMF =3", "products": 227, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 252, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-13", "text": "One of the most enjoyable games that have been made, the story is in single player is good. There is much side quest to do. But what I appreciate about the game most is actually, multiplayer part, could not stop playing the game for 6 hours. Was really fun, I recommend this game warm.", "hours": 32.4, "user_id": "76561197985108747", "username": "Fortman", "products": 510, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 252, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-12", "text": "Best Assassin's Creed game, hands down. One of the best games I have ever played.", "hours": 33.4, "username": "LtKuba", "products": 181, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 252, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-11", "text": "The multi-player in this game is a surprisingly enjoyable and addictive experience that should not be passed up. Likely the most underrated for the year.", "hours": 52.2, "username": "MyoMoe", "products": 216, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 252, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-11", "text": "Love it", "hours": 38.7, "user_id": "76561197989433116", "username": "Quickhand69er", "products": 339, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 253, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-11", "text": "By far, one of the best games I've played. If you want a different multiplayer experience, get this game.", "hours": 180.0, "username": "Sovereign [CHL]", "products": 152, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 253, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-10", "text": "I never really got into the Assassin's Creed games, but I'm glad I finally did. A vastly enjoyable game, with slick movement and an engrossing plot. Now I just need to play AC1 and 2...", "hours": 11.1, "username": "awmperry", "products": 1339, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 253, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-10", "text": "I only have one thing to say.... (OMG) A MUST PLAY GAME!!!!", "hours": 5.7, "user_id": "76561198036162519", "username": "Miroslav", "products": 46, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 253, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-10", "text": "sick game", "hours": 41.4, "username": "Sinister_S", "products": 45, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 253, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-10", "text": "Super Game =D", "hours": 18.5, "username": "StrikeUnleashed", "products": 460, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 253, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-10", "text": "\uc774\ub984\uc740 \uc5b4\uc314\uc2e0 \ud06c\ub9ac\ub4dc\uc778\ub370 \ud50c\ub808\uc774 \ud574\ubcf4\uba74 \uadf8\ub0e5 \uc6cc\ub9ac\uc5b4\uc784\u314b \uc7ac\ubc0b\uc5b4\uc694", "hours": 4.4, "username": "\ubd80\uc8fc", "products": 61, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 253, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-09", "text": "Assassin's Creed Brotherhood is essentially a large expansion to Assassin's Creed II. However, do not let that determine your impression. Brotherhood is a fantastic game, building upon Assassin's Creed II while resolving issues from the previous title simultaneously. Renaissance Rome is also truly and remarkably beautiful, as is the seamless combat when finally mastered. The multiplayer support is a little shakey, at best, but the single player campaign is worth the purchase on its own.", "hours": 36.1, "username": "J-Bomb", "products": 240, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 253, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-09", "text": "More of the same and that isn't a bad thing.", "hours": 34.0, "username": "Brinkman", "products": 233, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 253, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-09", "text": "If you liked the second you will like this one.  The multiplayer while new and fun it takes forever to get connected to a game.", "hours": 62.7, "user_id": "76561198007980683", "username": "Leon The Monkey", "products": 412, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 253, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-08", "text": "Un gran juego en cuanto a historia, para accesar al multijugador hay que esperar horas literalmente, juego recomendado. 8/10", "hours": 54.3, "username": "jUstiCieR0  \u30c5", "products": 119, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 254, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-07", "text": "The high point of the AC series.", "hours": 40.0, "username": "The Milkman", "products": 689, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 254, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-07", "text": "It was good even though it started right up where it left off, which would have been cool if it had been $29.99 or 39 DLC. I didn't get into the Multiplayer, but the campaign is what matters, if you have played AC2...", "hours": 516.4, "username": "Bandit|MerC|", "products": 205, "early_access": false}
