{"product_id": "48190", "page": 255, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-04", "text": "A great follow up to Assassin's Creed 2. More of everything which is a little to its detriment and the main storyline isn't fantastic but Ezio is enough of an awesome Italian stabbing dude that it doesn't really matter.", "hours": 13.9, "username": "Dan", "products": 517, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 255, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-04", "text": "Its awesome!", "hours": 20.0, "user_id": "76561197964062996", "username": "Gillies", "products": 157, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 255, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-04", "text": "Still the best in the series. Dont be scared if you havent played the others; you will still have a blast.", "hours": 73.0, "username": "FRIENDLYUNIT", "products": 92, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 255, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "worth it for just the multiplayer. campaign is good too!!", "hours": 27.9, "username": "no", "products": 846, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 255, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Good Stuff!", "hours": 9.3, "username": "RAIN", "products": 611, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 255, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "If you like the Assassin's Creed games, you'll want this one.  It's the best.  Ubisoft has backed off the DRM debacle a bit, so feel free to grab this when it goes on sale.  It probably won't sell for less than $20 for a long while, so that's a good buying point.", "username": "Khalaq", "products": 1220, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 255, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Best in the series.", "hours": 3.9, "username": "\u262dCommissar PUSHCART", "products": 581, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 255, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Excellent game, combat is fluid and enjoyable, think batman arkham asylum, yet not overly simple. I love the parkour gameplay and they do an excellent job of making it fluid and easy to master. AC 2's story was more engrossing, but AC:B has more overall, and has more of a sandbox feel to it. I recommend doing the virtual training early on in the game to understand the gameplay mechanics, and I recommend using the dual hidden blades for most combat as it is not only the most effecient at killing but also the most enjoyable to watch.  However it seems that multiplayer is dead for this game now, so that sucks.", "hours": 35.3, "user_id": "76561198003424373", "username": "Adam", "products": 1301, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 255, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Brotherhood's multiplayer is one of the best I've played, it's different from other multiplayer modes and so much fun! :D", "hours": 45.7, "username": "}SoC{GoldFish-Boy {FGL} \u03dfSMG\u03df", "products": 436, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 255, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Excellent addition to the AC series.  The story is really good and the combat is a lot better than ACII.  Pity you can only run around Rome, but the game is still worth it when on sale.", "hours": 19.3, "username": "Vizkos", "products": 254, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 256, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Brotherhood's multiplayer is one of the best I've played, it's different from other multiplayer modes and so much fun! :D", "hours": 45.7, "username": "}SoC{GoldFish-Boy {FGL} \u03dfSMG\u03df", "products": 436, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 256, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Excellent addition to the AC series.  The story is really good and the combat is a lot better than ACII.  Pity you can only run around Rome, but the game is still worth it when on sale.", "hours": 19.3, "username": "Vizkos", "products": 254, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 256, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "If  you want anything (dead)  - Just whistle!", "hours": 154.2, "username": "DuxOmnia", "products": 905, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 256, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Absolutely excellent game, a clear improvement over AC2, and that's before you even get into the multiplayer. Combat has been improved upon, making it more fluid and exciting, and missions have been expanded to provide opportunities to increase syncronisation. Completely new features were introduced as well, such as the Assassin Apprentice system.\nDepending on how much you like Desmond Miles, this could be either good or bad, but there is more opportunity to play and explore as him, developing the story further.\nMultiplayer is great as well. While I found the interface a bit awkward, gameplay was quite smooth (aside from lag) and entertaining.\nOnly real downside to the game is that it took Ubisoft so bloody long to release it on PC. Thankfully they did it without too much DRM garbage - you can barely notice it here, so you don't have the same problems that existed in AC2.", "hours": 13.6, "username": "R", "products": 143, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 256, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "The multiplayer is so different in this game, such a breath of fresh air.  You have one target from 6-8 people and there could be up to about 4 people that have you as a target.  You have to blend in and not give away that you are an assassin - while chasing your target.  Its brilliant!\nAnd thats not even mentioning the single player!", "hours": 0.0, "username": "Wakeem", "products": 1444, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 256, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Love the multiplayer", "hours": 19.9, "username": "hoserama99", "products": 2130, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 256, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "best game in the series", "hours": 26.0, "user_id": "76561197970485996", "username": "{SOAP} DEFE", "products": 383, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 256, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "this game is pretty cool, you get a pistol, dual hidden blades, and can carry heavy weapons (IE: Hammer, Heavy Sword)", "hours": 31.5, "username": "Bloodshed Romance", "products": 362, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 256, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "If you havent played AC1 and 2, you're going to be wondering exactly what is going on. Does that make this a less game? Aahahahaha.. No f'in way. This game is INCREDIBLE. If you liked the first two.. then why the hell dont you have this one yet? :D", "hours": 91.1, "username": "Speedy", "products": 1708, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 256, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "The game expands on everything Assassins Creed 2 was great at, as well as add in a few minor details such as secondary objectives now. The singleplayer is also longer this time and is in more depth so there aren't as many tutorial sections now. The multiplayer is lovingly excellent, only a few ppl can play it at a time however it is a great cat mouse style of gameplay with unique characters and abliities, seriously buy this as it \u00a315 in the summer sale.", "hours": 47.7, "username": "General Frags", "products": 7807, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 257, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "One good\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665game buy the whole series!", "hours": 53.4, "username": "Roydo", "products": 428, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 257, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Awesome Single Player and Multiplayer! :)", "hours": 154.6, "username": "squidward", "products": 3121, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 257, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Pure awesome.", "hours": 47.3, "username": "Zero82z", "products": 669, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 257, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "One of the best games (game series) I've ever played. And since Half-Life and Max Payne are quite inactive at the moment, I'm willing to pay Ubisoft almost anything for the Collector's edition of every new release from the AC series. Yes, it's THAT good.\nI won't spend precious time writing information you already read in million reviews, I'll put it simply - go buy it. Now. You won't regret it.\nOh, and one more thing - if you haven't played the first two parts before, you should -at least the second one which is equally outstanding (and read the plot of the first one somewhere).", "hours": 192.5, "username": "Tisovcik", "products": 714, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 257, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Exquisite detailed reproduction of Rome, Great voice acting makes you care about the cast , Long adventure stuffed with lots of varied missions and exploration.", "hours": 40.6, "username": "Flame Ifrit", "products": 824, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 257, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Speak of the Devil~!", "hours": 35.1, "username": "Cheejyg", "products": 651, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 257, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Better than AC2", "hours": 3.0, "username": "Terro", "products": 87, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 257, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-02", "text": "I waited for a sale to buy this game, as I was expecting it to be only focused on multiplayer and having a meager single-player campaign, with not much to add. Boy, was I wrong. Not only it improves on AC:II playability (fixing the combat system), it is as big, if not bigger, than it's predecessor. With better city design, quests and antagonists (cesare borgia's \"if I want to take, I take\" speech is brilliant and beautifuly delivered), this is my favorite Assassin's Creed game.", "hours": 58.5, "username": "Martinator", "products": 173, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 257, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-02", "text": "\u05d4\u05de\u05e9\u05d7\u05e7 \u05d4\u05d6\u05d4 \u05d4\u05d5\u05d0 \u05de\u05e9\u05d7\u05e7 \u05de\u05de\u05e9 \u05e0\u05d4\u05d3\u05e8 \u05db\u05d3\u05d9 \u05dc\u05db\u05dd \u05dc\u05e9\u05d7\u05e7 \u05d1\u05d5 \u05d0\u05e0\u05d9 \u05de\u05de\u05e9 \u05de\u05de\u05dc\u05d9\u05e5 \u05e2\u05dc\u05d9\u05d5\nThis game is really great game so go to play it I  realy recommend it", "hours": 47.7, "user_id": "76561198027069009", "username": "SunKnight", "products": 159, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 257, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-01", "text": "Really enjoying the single player more then I thought I would, the optional 100% sync objectives really bring quite a bit more challenge to the game. The multiplayer is really fun , though essentially a distraction.", "hours": 40.4, "username": "Comrade Rarity", "products": 401, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 258, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-02", "text": "\u05d4\u05de\u05e9\u05d7\u05e7 \u05d4\u05d6\u05d4 \u05d4\u05d5\u05d0 \u05de\u05e9\u05d7\u05e7 \u05de\u05de\u05e9 \u05e0\u05d4\u05d3\u05e8 \u05db\u05d3\u05d9 \u05dc\u05db\u05dd \u05dc\u05e9\u05d7\u05e7 \u05d1\u05d5 \u05d0\u05e0\u05d9 \u05de\u05de\u05e9 \u05de\u05de\u05dc\u05d9\u05e5 \u05e2\u05dc\u05d9\u05d5\nThis game is really great game so go to play it I  realy recommend it", "hours": 47.7, "user_id": "76561198027069009", "username": "SunKnight", "products": 159, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 258, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-01", "text": "Really enjoying the single player more then I thought I would, the optional 100% sync objectives really bring quite a bit more challenge to the game. The multiplayer is really fun , though essentially a distraction.", "hours": 40.4, "username": "Comrade Rarity", "products": 401, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 258, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-27", "text": ":D Love this game", "hours": 41.7, "user_id": "76561198043753683", "username": "FuriousFurSeal", "products": 158, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 258, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-26", "text": "Ezio returns in another plot engaging adventure set in old Rome. The combat is more diverse than AC 2 and despite his age, the assassin is able to kill and unite his brethren against corruption.", "hours": 38.9, "user_id": "76561198000021881", "username": "Silent Knight", "products": 208, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 258, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-25", "text": "This is the first  of the 3  Assassin's Creed's so far that gives some love to the pc version. Way improved graphics, user interface and the like.(the keys map to the pc keys for the first time).  The fiction, gameplay and aesthetic are all there again and I highly recommend Brotherhood if you enjoyed the last 2 at all.", "hours": 53.8, "user_id": "76561197965928460", "username": "starwatcher", "products": 230, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 258, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-25", "text": "AC:BH is a beautiful story, on both sides of the Animus. We get a deeper view of Ezio Auditore da Firenze reconstruction of the Assassin order complete with your own Assassin's to train and summon. I'll personally make claim that if you even slightly enjoy political drama you will love the story, even as cliche as it is and full of conspiracy theory. The combat is definately smoother and more satisfying without removing any of the fun of the PK, although the detection can be a little bit sorry if you don't use a controller, which you should for playing this game. I wasn't a personal fan of the revitize rome system in this game but I can see how one might be. Really the most interesting, not really the most fun for me (I like solo games) is the multiplayer which is created under the guise of a training program for the Templar corperation Abstergo, trying to capitalize on the bleedthrough effect that they are using to train Desmond. ~10/10~", "hours": 56.7, "username": "DarkLilly [twitch.tv/darklilly]", "products": 1160, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 258, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-24", "text": "great game, i could play for hours, but i suggest waiting for Revelations", "hours": 56.6, "username": "Elesine", "products": 399, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 258, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-22", "text": "The sheer amount of talent that goes into these games, is amazing. From the story telling to the beautiful visuals, to the engaging gameplay, there's so much to take in it's almost overwhelming. The development team, which is so large it spans across many countries, takes what you loved from the first games, adds to it and improves it to create a truly unique game. The multiplayer is loads of fun, and it even has it's own leveling up system to improve skills and obtain weapons. Brotherhood is by far the best Assassin's Creed to date. The series gets better with every game, and I can't wait to see what Revelations has in store. Buy it, play it, and requiete in pace.", "hours": 31.0, "username": "ManyNekoZ", "products": 1241, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 258, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-19", "text": "It is a very good game. The addition of assassin followers is the newest and most exciting feature which sets AC: Brotherhood apart from the earlier AC games (and makes it a definite improvement). The only real problem I had with the game was the very ending. It offers no sense of closure and instead of doing something good, you kill a close friend and ally with no explanation. Even aside from the ending, the game still isn't quite perfect, but it is easily worth its current $40.00 price tag. I'd give it a reluctant 9 out of 10.", "hours": 27.7, "username": "SirDeity", "products": 299, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 258, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-19", "text": "Each part of this series is an improvement on the last and the combat in this one is superb. The story continues directly from 2 so you'll be glad if you play that one first.", "hours": 56.4, "username": "Fogg", "products": 459, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 259, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-18", "text": "Una obra de arte, digno de jugarse varias veces.", "hours": 42.9, "username": "Myzter", "products": 707, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 259, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-10", "text": "The best Assassin's Creed game yet, and with multiplayer!\nA must buy, if only because it has multiplayer, so pirating it means no multiplayer!\nAnd the multiplayer is fun!\nOh, and obviously the single player is as awesome as you'd expect from an Assassin's Creed game, and it's still a step forward from previous installments in the series.", "hours": 171.0, "username": "Pakundo", "products": 408, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 259, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-07", "text": "So far, the best entrance in the series. Expanded combat in the likes of Batman: Arkham Asylum, small tweaks to the parkour system and great character development. Story was kind of lacking, though. Would like to see this gameplay with the story of Assassin's Creed 2.", "hours": 59.0, "username": "Roni", "products": 308, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 259, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-06", "text": "It's more of what you saw in Assassin's Creed 2, although slightly ill-paced and reeking of consolitis. Still, a very good game, if only for the detailed environments and atmosphere.", "hours": 19.7, "username": "Forceflow.be", "products": 965, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 259, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-04", "text": "The game with the largest scope yet....a feast for the eyes...not just another fighting game!", "hours": 40.7, "username": "Scooter Cogs", "products": 337, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 259, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-01", "text": "7/10", "hours": 2.6, "username": "kaP", "products": 296, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 259, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-28", "text": "It's a very fun game even if you hated Assassin's Creed 1. All the characters in the game also talk like Super Mario :)", "hours": 22.5, "username": "TURNT UP TO DEATH", "products": 401, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 259, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-28", "text": "jump jump jump stab jump jump run run shoot run run... yup... thats life", "hours": 37.3, "username": "buddah", "products": 236, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 259, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-20", "text": "great storeyline in 1 player mode with a whole world to explore...multi player keeps ya on your toes as well :D\nGraphics are just amazing as well..", "hours": 166.8, "user_id": "76561197985112245", "username": "Tetley tea", "products": 61, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 259, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-18", "text": "great game!!!", "hours": 119.1, "username": "mad_gamer", "products": 353, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 260, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-16", "text": "GooD GamE !", "hours": 28.4, "user_id": "76561198020069303", "username": "Koldek", "products": 84, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 260, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-12", "text": "Single-Player: More of the same from AC2, but nonetheless very enjoyable. Side missions have more variety, and the combat styles are more complex than ever. The sandbox (Rome) itself feels somewhat smaller from the previous games.\nMulti-Player: Very unique concept, completely deviated from other multiplayer games. However it's also a real pain in the\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665to your connection settings; for me, I have to sit for literally hours just to find a session and play for about  2-3 rounds. This issue has not been resolved since its launch on PC.\nOverall: SP is great, MP is great, but the matchmaking downright sucks. Ubisoft has yet to release a patch to fix this, and their support isn't helping at all.", "hours": 195.2, "username": "iSpycheck", "products": 52, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 260, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-09", "text": "The 3rd sequel in the series, and conceptually the same as its predecessors. I guess UBI-Soft is sticking fast to their rise and repeat strategy. (Splinter Cell anyone?). The game isn't terrible, and the graphics are pretty. What really sets it apart from its predecessors is the multiplayer.\nI love it. Basically it's hide-and- go seek, but replace seeking with stabbing. It's fun and challenging.", "hours": 19.6, "user_id": "76561197970387541", "username": "Eudial", "products": 466, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 260, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-01", "text": "The best Assassin's creed entry so far. Its a culmination of everything learnt from AC2 and AC1 with elements incorporated from more open-world games. Ezio is one of the most believable and charming characters of this generation. A must play for any Assassin's creed / stealth action game fan.\n9/10", "hours": 40.3, "username": "VraeV", "products": 118, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 260, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-01", "text": "Slightly better than what was thought to be Assassin's Creed Two-and-a-half. Multiplayer will bring you extra hours of enjoyment, covering for the comparably lackluster singleplayer experience.", "hours": 200.1, "username": "derek328", "products": 44, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 260, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-01", "text": "so much to do in the this world. although for the most part you can only stay in rome italy, its like assassins creed 2 with a big update. but it is worth it in my opinion. also the multiplayer is kinda slow paced but good none the less.", "hours": 79.0, "username": "Triple-TTT", "products": 471, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 260, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-27", "text": "The best Assassin's Creed game to date.", "hours": 24.9, "username": "renzo", "products": 447, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 260, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-27", "text": "This game is the best of the Assassin's Creed series to date, and that is saying something. It took all the awesome of the Assassin's Creed II, added more history, more story, and a couple of new features, all resulting in a game that I personally couldn't put down for more than a week straight. And I already feel like starting a 2nd playthrough!", "hours": 46.5, "username": "Apathy", "products": 595, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 260, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-25", "text": "One word - AWESOME!", "hours": 67.0, "username": "Lost Hashishin", "products": 1552, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 260, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-24", "text": "The AC series keeps getting better. Brotherhood is also much longer.", "hours": 53.9, "username": "facls", "products": 663, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 261, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-20", "text": "Once again a very nice storyline, amazing landscape, fantastic gameplay + plus multiplayer mode, of course. :)", "hours": 36.1, "user_id": "76561197983631245", "username": "Pantek59", "products": 219, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 261, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-18", "text": "The Single player is really well done. This game falls when it comes down to mutliplayer it uses a matchmaking system that at the time of this post was and probably is still very broken. I recommend setting up private matches if you dont want to wait 10mins...", "hours": 56.3, "username": "Theta", "products": 452, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 261, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-18", "text": "Assassin's Creed 2.5!\nThis game is great, you get a lot of content and there's a high replay value. It's visually gorgeous and the combat is very entertaining. The voice acting and the music is also top quality.\nSo if you liked Assassin's Creed 2 and want more, I definitely recommend Brotherhood.", "hours": 34.7, "username": "Frawns", "products": 234, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 261, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-17", "text": "a surprisingly great game, it takes insipration from older games (eg: the ship) for a unique muliplayer experience where you are the hunter AND the hunted. it ticks alot of the boxes, great animation, art style, sound, and great gameplay. only a few issues remain, such as lag. this wouldnt be a problem, but it becomes such because of the lobby system. they did not put a server browser, and instead put an automatic lobby system that will sometimes pair you with people with SUCH bad internet connections that they may be residing in the bahamas.\nOn the camaign side, i cannot really judge, as i have only started. But it does seem to follow to \"press X to win\" theme of previous games, and the story wont make much sense to those unfamiliar with the assassins creed universe.\nPerformance is also a big issue, and you need to be careful of your computers spec's before you consider this game, otherwise the framerate is just PAINFUL.\nA great experience, with a fair bit of replayability. :)", "hours": 21.5, "username": "Zable", "products": 447, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 261, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-17", "text": "Note: This game been tried out and reviewed in Steam offline mode or on Consoles.\nThe game is superb in every aspect and worth your time. Play it if you like Historic Action Adventure.\nUBI-Soft made some great improvements in gameplay story and graphics over the time and AC Brotherhood is best among the series up-till now.\nThe game is so much alive like you are living in real life, Amazing Graphics and details.\nStory is really improved in this part as well as gameplay managing all the other assassins, traveling in the city, helping people, completing the story line(Which keeps getting better and better) all of them really cast a spell on you so that you keep playing it and don't want to leave your PC until you completed everything.\nThis game shows that how hard game developers are working to make perfect/good games for you.", "username": "Nessa", "products": 5000, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 261, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-10", "text": "Amazing storyline, there's a new system where you start an assassin order, you send them on contracts or fight along side you. You have the Rome economy where you build up Roma by buying shops, POI and collections of weapon and armour. It helps to you income. I love the storyline of enzo and the time period in Italy so heritage rich.\nThere is multiplayer but currently not worth it as servers are dead. If you want to play any creed then it black flag", "hours": 284.3, "user_id": "76561198039834562", "username": "Jippie", "products": 219, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 261, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-07", "text": "\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665in Italians and\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665", "hours": 16.1, "user_id": "76561197977328933", "username": "Indoorsman", "products": 151, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 261, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-06", "text": "A killer of a game", "hours": 22.8, "username": "DelacourtBE", "products": 157, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 261, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-05", "text": "Fantastic multiplayer!!! And more of the great campaign tied to AC2 that makes you feel like the coolest dude in the world.  But what's special about Brotherhood is the multiplayer, it provides a much needed break away from all the shooters out there in the industry.  You'll love trying to pick out your targets in the crowd of citizens but also trying to keep a low profile.  If you want a unique and refreshing multiplayer experience, or just plain love Assassin's Creed then you need to get this game!", "hours": 37.4, "username": "Mitch | Rathian Slayer", "products": 638, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 261, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-03", "text": "One of the finest piece of art from Ubisoft, I always tought that Assasins Creed 2 was the very masterpiece and this new version will had to climb hard to get ibto my favorite PC games, but i was wrong, the game is huge, lots of things to do, play on the same city all the time provides a good challenge to maintain a low perfil, the long waiting for PC version worth it.\nMultiplayer games are not the best, but i hope soon  we get better patches and fix the glitches.", "hours": 24.1, "username": "Qbert", "products": 147, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 262, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-03", "text": "One of the finest piece of art from Ubisoft, I always tought that Assasins Creed 2 was the very masterpiece and this new version will had to climb hard to get ibto my favorite PC games, but i was wrong, the game is huge, lots of things to do, play on the same city all the time provides a good challenge to maintain a low perfil, the long waiting for PC version worth it.\nMultiplayer games are not the best, but i hope soon  we get better patches and fix the glitches.", "hours": 24.1, "username": "Qbert", "products": 147, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 262, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-02", "text": "If you love to run around, hop off walls and land on some random guard and stab a knife in his neck, then this game is for you! It has a pretty big world for those who like to explore, and that action story-line that allows you to kill a lot of people! I highly enjoy this game.", "hours": 20.4, "username": "Therlbo", "products": 137, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 262, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-02", "text": "When Ubisoft suggested Assassin's Creed II would take place in Italy, the setting in Assassin's Creed: Brotherhood is what I had hoped it would be.\nNever mind the fact that in terms of single player, Assassin's Creed: Brotherhood doesn't bring anything new to the table - Assassin's Creed II nailed the formula between mission originality, familiarity and sheer repetiveness, so I honestly see no need for this instalment to add much more in that department. Regardless, Assassin's Creed: Brotherhood does add some interesting gameplay mechanics such as assassin recruits and, together with with the impressive new locales becomes what I see as probably the game in the franchise thus far.\nFor those who enjoyed Assassin's Creed II: buy it - you won't be disappointed.", "hours": 62.4, "username": "Ares", "products": 375, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 262, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-02", "text": "Highly addictive game involving parkour and blades.  If you can look past the hilarious italian accents, you'll get hooked and play it WAY too much.  To the point where you actually start to believe you can jump and climb over\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665just as easily as that guy on the screen does.\nSo, old people and small children unable to attempt parkour without dying should not play this game.  Agile and athletic people such as myself, however, are fully aware of what is at stake.  You can totally make that jump.  Do it.", "hours": 38.6, "username": "Zalor", "products": 737, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 262, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-31", "text": "nice finish to the series, multi-play makes it enjoyable for hours and hours after you're done with singleplayer. win / win", "hours": 49.8, "username": "meltdown", "products": 371, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 262, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-28", "text": "Just awesome, you MUST buy it!!! :D", "hours": 51.1, "username": "Teaddy", "products": 333, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 262, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-28", "text": "BUY IT! :D", "hours": 31.1, "username": "Samsa", "products": 280, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 262, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-27", "text": "The best game in the AC series to date. Brotherhood replaces the slow counter-heavy slog that was combat in the previous games with a system kind of reminiscent of Arkham Asylum in which speed, aggression, and precision are privileged.\nIt also gets rid of the worst of the repetitive boring crap from the earlier games and expands on the plot, which is a hell of a lot of conspiracy-laden paranoiac fun.", "hours": 52.4, "username": "it's\ud83d\udc80shoe", "products": 645, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 262, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-26", "text": "Fantastic game that follows on directly from AC2, improved combat and even more side tasks to do if you desire. Ezio is back and this time he has even more help with Assassin recruits. The whole game is brilliant.", "hours": 20.8, "username": "nutcrackr", "products": 462, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 262, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-25", "text": "The best game you will ever play! Best graphics and tons of fun.", "hours": 285.1, "user_id": "76561197995181527", "username": "Revan", "products": 207, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 263, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-24", "text": "I strongly recommend Assassin's Creed Brotherhood to anyone that has tried the past games or wants to try for the first time. It has a amazing storyline, continuing Assassin's Creed Two, and this time, a multiplayer option, wich, is challenging and awesome.", "hours": 99.7, "username": "TwistedRaven", "products": 538, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 263, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-23", "text": "If you aren't poor then buy this game, the multiplayer and single player alone are worth the price.", "hours": 66.3, "username": "Scottie", "products": 290, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 263, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-22", "text": "Amazing Game. Update to the graphics engine improves so much on the look and feel, auditory sounds in the cities make it so much more lifelike than in the past two games, the HUD has been slimmed down and the optimization of the game is just amazing. New interactions, items, weapons, city economies, additional parkour elements and a brand new storyline makes this much less an upgrade with the same characters and different storyline, but a fully new game with four times the facets as the previous one.\nThe multiplayer has been flawless since release day, being able to choose your own character skin and just the simple way to play multiplayer with the quick tutorial is so much fun and before you know it 2 hours have gone by in extreme fun. This was worth my $50 by a long shot.", "hours": 98.6, "username": "Cosmic Gates", "products": 275, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 263, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-22", "text": "Jump, kill, kick, hit, call assassins!\nThese are the very essential things of Assassin's Creed: 'Brohood\nPURE AWESOMENESS!", "hours": 22.9, "username": "subZero", "products": 361, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 263, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-22", "text": "AFTER PLAYING THIS GAME AND ITS MULTIPLAYER MODE I WOULD SHOW MY MIDDEL \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665EN FINGER TO ALL OTHER MULTIPLAYER GAMES IF IT IS COD IF ITS CS IF ITS DOD THIS GAME IS BETTER THEN ALL OF EM AND THIS IS THE REASON WHY ITS GOT 98% AVERAGE OVA NET!!! BUT ITS HARDER THEN ALL OF EM SO IF YOU HAVE BALLS THEN TRY IT!!!!", "hours": 94.8, "username": "Ninja \u2122", "products": 548, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 263, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-22", "text": "You thought the crazy Adventures of Dezmond and Ezio are over? Think again. In this third and most likely last installment for a while, you are thrown right back to where AS:2 finished.\nAnyway, the graphics engine has been completly overhauled to provide an even more interesting immersive experience over the previous two games. Its hungry for hardware so perhaps make sure you can play AS and AS:2 at least on medium to ensure you can play this much detailed sequal.\nStory wise its been improved and as previously stated, its a direct continuation from AS:2. More quirks and additions are in this packed game, so if you are an Assasin at heart, this is a MUST buy. If you have a controller, then all the best, good luck and remember, you are an elite assasin in the 1500's.\nWhere will the fight with Astergo lead you? What answers does Subject 16 still have for you? Where did Leonardo get to? All will be revealed in this action packed, beautifully detailed game.\nFinal Score: 4 / 5", "hours": 29.6, "username": "Darkus Canning", "products": 418, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 263, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-21", "text": "\u3088\u308a\u3088\u304f\u306a\u3063\u305f\u30a2\u30b5\u30b7\u30f3\u30af\u30ea\u30fc\u30c92", "hours": 27.8, "username": "EDILTE", "products": 343, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 263, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-21", "text": "A breathtaking open-world experience that's fun to explore, an intruiging entry into the series' story, and lots of new moves, skills, and additions to make this the best Assassin's Creed yet. Plus, AC:B has one of the most unique, challenging, and original Multiplayers to date.", "hours": 13.6, "username": "M1SF0RTUNE [Work]", "products": 738, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 263, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-21", "text": "Excellent game!", "hours": 55.4, "username": "NetWalkerBR", "products": 688, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 263, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-21", "text": "must buy if you liked assassins creed 2\nand the multiplayer is surprisingly fresh and unique a real blast to play.\nrecommanded for all the backstabbers under us :D", "hours": 45.3, "user_id": "76561197972599229", "username": "freakshowfreak", "products": 590, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 264, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-20", "text": "A game that entertain you for hours!", "hours": 64.2, "username": "Chiken | Gamdom.com", "products": 323, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 264, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-20", "text": "A must have for any Assassin's Creed fan!\nThe game adds substantial new content and improvements to make it worth the full price. While some people, myself included. Thought before launch that it would simply be a rehash of AsC 2 with little new content in terms of the singleplayer. We have definitely been proven wrong.\nThis game is also a proper PC port with vastly upgraded graphics in comparison to AsC-B on consoles. Proper UI, HUD and menus and for the first time in a while, the ability to play offline (yes, that's right the DRM that was so hated in AsC 2 is now gone!)\nThe multiplayer is extremely fun and while some might say it bears resemblence to the Ship, the similarities are small, if any at all. At most one could say it was inspired by the Ship.\nThe multiplayer mechanics work well and leave a lot of room for player skill to play a role. There is also a decent variety of modes, all of which provide different feel and play tactics.\nAll in all the best AsC to date!", "hours": 41.8, "username": "Neon InCole Anderson", "products": 426, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 264, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-20", "text": "Story is as better than in the earlier games. It also introduces multiplayer which is AWESOME. If you dont like the SP, then this game is actually good enough to only be an MP game. I highly recommend it. My favorite game modes are Wanted and Manhunt.", "hours": 19.5, "username": "MiniDude", "products": 477, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 264, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-20", "text": "Epic", "hours": 67.5, "user_id": "76561198032838963", "username": "Pablo Escobar", "products": 98, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 264, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-19", "text": "Even though Assassin's Creed 2 left me wondering what the feck just happened after the (anticlimatic) end fight, AC Brotherhood does a good job wrapping things up and explaining more stuff related to Desmond. After all, it's fun collecting all these bits of information and work towards an explanation for all that is happening.\nThis game would be perfect if it wasn't for the sloppy console-port - the controls feel stiff when using mouse & keyboard.\nApart from that I recommend this to fans of the Assassin's Creed series.", "hours": 20.0, "username": "Deathstar", "products": 484, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 264, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-19", "text": "Assassin's Creed II is a masterpiece of game design, vastly improving upon the original and somewhat bland Assassin's Creed.\nBrotherhood is a game in the vein of the traditional expansion - more of the same, but with a vast new game world, tweaked mechanics and more stuff to do - a huge serving that vastly outweighs any piecemeal DLC.\nAn absolute blast to play in a beautifully realised world, if you like action / adventure in a bit of a sandbox, you owe it to yourself to play this.", "hours": 28.2, "username": "DarkOwl", "products": 318, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 264, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-18", "text": "El mejor Assasin creed hasta la fecha\nthe best Assasin\u00b4s creed.", "hours": 77.2, "username": "Darth Villa", "products": 235, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 264, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-18", "text": "It took a while to release but the game is epic. The game looks amazing and as always the story is good.", "hours": 38.4, "username": "crazyjointje", "products": 65, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "48190", "page": 264, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-18", "text": "Okay you can buy this game but be warned my blade will reach your back faster than you sneeze", "hours": 253.6, "username": "Gunsmoke", "products": 119, "early_access": false}
